# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Units
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

oakcurric:unit-125
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Verb and adjective suffixes"@en ;
  curric:slug "verb-and-adjective-suffixes" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn spelling and grammar conventions associated with
  certain verb and adjective suffixes, like -ate, -en, -ify, -ise and -ous. Pupils will
  review and learn more examples of how the addition of a suffix can affect the grammar of a
  word, for example its word class or tense."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' knowledge of spelling and grammar
  conventions associated with the suffixes -ly, -ful and -less and the spelling of words with
  silent letters learnt in the Year 3 unit 'Year 3: More suffixes and silent letters'. Here,
  pupils learn verb and adjective suffixes, like -ate, -en, -ify, -ise and -ous, reviewing how
  the addition of a suffix can affect the grammar of a word, for example by changing its word
  class or tense. This unit prepares pupils for further suffix work in the Year 4 unit 'Year 4:
  Noun and adjective suffixes'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-125-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-125-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-125-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-125-4 ;
  curric:id "125"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.259234Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-developing-spelling-accuracy .

oakcurric:unit-226
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "'Jabberwocky': narrative writing"@en ;
  curric:slug "the-jabberwocky-narrative-writing" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils write a full narrative based on the nonsense poem
  'Jabberwocky' from 'Through the Looking-Glass' by Lewis Carroll. Pupils write an opening,
  build-up, climax and resolution, focusing on writing all parts of the narrative arc and
  devoting time to editing their writing."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' knowledge of the narrative writing
  style from the Year 4 unit ''A Christmas Carol': narrative writing and reading'. The unit
  starts with an analysis of the plot of the nonsense poem 'Jabberwocky' for pupils to clarify
  key plot events and to understand nonsense vocabulary used by Carroll. Pupils then write
  their own version of the complete narrative, writing an opening, build-up, climax and
  resolution. This unit prepares pupils for writing another complete narrative in the Year 4
  unit 'The Happy Prince': narrative writing'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-226-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-226-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-226-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-226-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-226-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-226-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-226-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-226-8 ;
  curric:id "226"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.264099Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-developing-fiction-writing ,
    oakcurric:thread-appreciation-of-poetry .

oakcurric:unit-666
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "'The Highwayman': narrative writing"@en ;
  curric:slug "the-highwayman-narrative-writing" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils use 'The Highwayman' by Alfred Noyes as the stimulus from
  which to write a character and setting description, a narrative build-up in third person
  prose and a section incorporating varied speech sentences. Pupils complete the unit
  reciting and memorising parts of the poem."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils' knowledge of narrative writing skills built in
  the Year 5 unit, 'The Viewer': narrative writing', in which pupils developed their use of
  cohesive devices and show-not-tell to convey character. Here, pupils develop their
  understanding of creating atmosphere and engaging the reader with figurative language. Pupils
  also practise a variety of speech punctuation, sentence structures and recital skills,
  reading and memorising from this classic narrative poem. This unit prepares pupils for the
  Year 5 unit, 'Shakespeare's 'Macbeth': narrative and soliloquy writing'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-666-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-666-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-666-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-666-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-666-5 ;
  curric:id "666"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.266673Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-appreciation-of-poetry ,
    oakcurric:thread-developing-fiction-writing .

oakcurric:unit-1041
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "'The Borrowers': narrative writing and reading"@en ;
  curric:slug "the-borrowers-narrative-writing-and-reading" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils explore 'The Borrowers' through reading and writing
  activities. They sequence key events, analyse the setting and characters and write a
  descriptive setting piece. Pupils also plan, write, and edit sections of the build-up,
  developing their narrative writing skills."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on the narrative writing skills developed in 'The
  Firework Maker's Daughter' by helping pupils further refine their use of descriptive language
  and complex sentence structures. By analysing the setting and characters in The Borrowers and
  writing descriptive and narrative sections, pupils develop their ability to create engaging
  stories. This focus develops pupils' narrative skills, preparing them for the next unit on 'A
  Christmas Carol', where they will apply and extend these skills by writing further sections
  of a narrative.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-1041-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-1041-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-1041-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-1041-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-1041-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-1041-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-1041-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-1041-8 ;
  curric:id "1041"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.268863Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-fiction-reading-spine ,
    oakcurric:thread-developing-fiction-writing .

oakcurric:unit-473
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "The aye-aye or wild cats: non-chronological report"@en ;
  curric:slug "the-aye-aye-or-wild-cats-non-chronological-report" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils research aye-ayes' diets and adaptations to write an
  informative non-chronological report about them. They spend a whole lesson editing their
  writing, focusing on key Year 5 punctuation, sentence structures and vocabulary choices.
  Finally, pupils present their reports."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' knowledge of writing in a formal
  informative style from the Year 4 unit 'Ancient Greeks or Anglo-Saxons: non-chronological
  report'. Pupils continue to write using the structure of an introduction, themed sections and
  conclusion; they also write using a range of formal and viewpoint fronted adverbials to
  ensure their writing flows cohesively. This unit prepares pupils to develop their
  understanding of structuring a long-form text in the first formal essay writing they will
  complete in the Year 5 unit, 'The Amazon Rainforest: essay writing'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-473-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-473-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-473-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-473-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-473-5 ;
