oakcurric:unit-881
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "'Princess Sophia Duleep Singh: My Story': reading"@en ;
  curric:slug "princess-sophia-duleep-singh-my-story-reading" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils read and explore the historical fiction text, 'Princess
  Sophia Duleep Singh: My Story'. They explore characterisation across the text and compare
  perspectives. Finally, pupils engage with the key theme of inequality and explore the
  legacy of the suffragettes."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on the prior unit, 'Escape from Pompeii: reading', where
  pupils read a fictionalised retelling of a historical event. In this unit, pupils will read
  about history through an imagined perspective, one which the author has researched
  extensively. Pupils continue to develop their inference skills by using evidence and will
  explore characterisation and perspectives. This unit prepares pupils for the future unit,
  'Harriet Tubman: biographical writing', where they will write to inform about a significant
  person's life, including the impact they had and legacy they left behind.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-881-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-881-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-881-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-881-4 ;
  curric:id "881"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.282792Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-reading-and-writing-texts-that-inform ,
    oakcurric:thread-fiction-reading-spine .

oakcurric:unit-915
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Poetry of place"@en ;
  curric:slug "poetry-of-place" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils read, respond to and perform classic and contemporary poetry
  about a range of settings. They explore imagery and form, whilst developing personal
  responses and comparing poems. Finally, pupils write their own poem about a place of
  significance."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on 'Poetry about migration', where pupils
  explored poetry through music lyrics. In this unit, pupils engage with a range of settings
  through several poets and their work. They explore form and imagery and give personal
  responses to the poems, including some evidence to justify their ideas. This unit prepares
  pupils for 'No Country and Frizzy: graphic novels exploring identity and belonging', where
  they will explore how identity and belonging can be portrayed through settings and
  characterisation in the graphic novel form.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-915-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-915-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-915-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-915-4 ;
  curric:id "915"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.287157Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-modern-literature-strand-1-identity-belonging-and-community ,
    oakcurric:thread-appreciation-of-poetry .

oakcurric:unit-128
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Letter strings, etymology and curriculum words"@en ;
  curric:slug "letter-strings-etymology-and-curriculum-words" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils review and learn a wide range of Year 6 spellings, including
  letter strings, words with the suffixes -ant, -ance, -ent, -ence, -able and -ible, silent
  letters, French and Greek origin words, curriculum words and words that use the hyphen in
  two ways."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' knowledge of noun suffixes and letter
  strings learnt in the Year 5 unit, 'Year 5: Noun suffixes, letter strings and homophones'.
  Here, pupils review and learn a wide range of Year 6 level spellings: letter strings; words
  with suffixes -ant, -ance, -ent, -ence, -able and -ible; words with silent letters; words
  with French and Greek origin; curriculum words; words hyphenated to join prefixes to root
  words; and words hyphenated to create adjectives. This unit prepares pupils for review in the
  Year 6 unit 'Year 6: Review and revision of all taught spelling'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-128-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-128-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-128-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-128-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-128-5 ;
  curric:id "128"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.294249Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-developing-spelling-accuracy .

oakcurric:unit-464
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Letter strings"@en ;
  curric:slug "letter-strings" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils apply their handwriting skills to writing words with
  prefixes, suffixes and other word endings.They identify which of the four joins are used
  within a letter string and focus on using consistent joins, pencil lifts and lead ins and
  lead outs in each letter string."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on their mastery of the four joins, this unit develops pupils'
  precision and control in using each join within complex letter strings, closely linking to
  the Year 3 spelling curriculum. Through refining smooth, consistent joins, lead ins, lead
  outs and accurate pencil lifts, pupils improve their fluency and attention to detail, while
  committing spelling patterns to memory. These refined handwriting skills directly support the
  next unit's focus on more challenging spelling patterns, including silent letters, homophones
  and common exception words.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-464-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-464-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-464-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-464-4 ;
  curric:id "464"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.308693Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-developing-handwriting-fluency .

oakcurric:unit-891
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "'A Kind of Spark': reading"@en ;
  curric:slug "a-kind-of-spark-reading" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils read and explore the novel, 'A Kind of Spark'. They gather
  evidence about the characters by inferring from the text and compare characters both
  within and between texts. Finally, pupils explore the key concepts and themes from the
  text."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' understanding of characterisation,
  which was explored in 'Girl of Ink and Stars', where pupils read a narrative with a
  strong-willed, female protagonist in a magical setting. In this unit, pupils read through the
  lens of a female protagonist in a contemporary, modern Scottish setting. Pupils explore
  characterisation through the lens of a neurodiverse individual and gather evidence to support
  inferences made. This unit prepares pupils for 'A Kind of Spark: narrative writing', where
  they will use the book as a stimulus for writing.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-891-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-891-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-891-3 ;
  curric:id "891"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.310725Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-modern-literature-strand-1-identity-belonging-and-community ,
    oakcurric:thread-fiction-reading-spine .

oakcurric:unit-702
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "'A Kind of Spark': narrative writing"@en ;
  curric:slug "a-kind-of-spark-narrative-writing" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils write a build-up and climax based on the text, 'A Kind of
  Spark'. They learn to switch tense to highlight a jump in perspective from narrative prose
  to an internal monologue and from present to past tense to indicate a flashback. These
  outcomes can be used for KS2 SATS writing."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on the Year 6 unit 'Beowulf': narrative
  writing', in which pupils built up techniques for increasing and maintaining tension in a
  build-up and describing powerful action in a climax. Here, pupils finesse their writing of a
  build-up and climax by learning to switch between tenses to move from third person narrative
  prose to internal monologue and to indicate a flashback. These sophisticated techniques allow
  pupils to write with creative authorial flair. This unit's outcomes can be used for pupils'
  KS2 writing portfolios as they demonstrate all taught cohesive devices.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-702-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-702-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-702-3 ,
