oakcurric:unit-127
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Homophones and tense"@en ;
  curric:slug "homophones-and-tense" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils build and review a range of spelling patterns with a focus on
  homonyms, homophones and a wide range of suffixes, including -ed, -ing, -er, -est, -s,
  -ies, -es, -ves, -le, -el, -il, -al, -cian, -tion, -sion, -ssion, -ous, -tious, -cious,
  -cial and -tial."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' knowledge of homophones learnt in the
  Year 5 unit 'Year 5: Noun suffixes, letter strings and homophones'. In this unit, pupils
  build and review a range of spelling patterns with a focus on homonyms, homophones and a wide
  range of suffixes. Pupils review how the addition of a suffix can affect the grammar of a
  word, for example its word class or tense. This unit prepares pupils to learn further
  spelling rules in the Year 6 unit, 'Year 6: Letter strings, etymology and curriculum words'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-127-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-127-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-127-3 ,
