    oakcurric:thread-appreciation-of-poetry .

oakcurric:unit-138
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Prefixes, homonyms and homophones"@en ;
  curric:slug "prefixes-homonyms-and-homophones" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn spelling and grammar conventions associated with
  prefixes meaning 'not', like dis-, non-, mis- and un-, as well as the spelling of
  homophones, homonyms and some compound words."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' knowledge of spelling rules
  associated with homophones learnt in the Year 2 unit 'Year 2: Alternative GPCs for consonants
  and homophones'. In this unit, pupils learn spelling and grammar conventions associated with
  prefixes meaning 'not', like dis-, non-, mis- and un-, as well as the spelling of homophones,
  homonyms and some compound words, applying newly taught spellings to a sentence context. This
  unit prepares pupils for further homophone work in the Year 4 unit 'Year 4: Suffixes,
  etymology and homophones'.""" ;
