oakcurric:unit-135
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Writing -ed and -ing suffixes"@en ;
  curric:slug "writing-ed-and-ing-suffixes" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn certain spelling rules associated with -ed and -ing
  suffixes. Pupils learn how the addition of a suffix can affect the grammar of a word,
  particularly in relation to a word's tense."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' knowledge of spelling rules
  associated with suffixes learnt in the Year 2 unit 'Year 2: Suffixes'. Here, pupils learn new
  spelling rules associated with -ed and -ing suffixes, learning relevant rules and how to
  apply new suffix spellings in a sentence context. They review how the addition of a suffix
  can affect the grammar of a word, for example by changing its word class or tense. This unit
  prepares pupils for further suffix work in the Year 3 unit 'Year 3: More suffixes and silent
  letters'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-135-1 ,
