oakcurric:unit-465
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Building fluency in silent letters, homophones, and common exception words"@en ;
  curric:slug "building-fluency-in-silent-letters-homophones-and-common-exception-words" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils practise their handwriting with a focus on increasing
  legibility, consistency and quality. They practise writing words with silent letters,
  homophones and common exception words. The unit culminates in pupils applying their
  handwriting skills to reviewing and copying poems."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this final Year 3 handwriting unit, pupils build on their work with
  letter strings, focusing on improving their handwriting quality and fluency. Through careful
  practice of more challenging vocabulary, pupils develop control and adaptability while
  strengthening their spelling memory through cursive writing. The final task, where pupils
  review and copy poems, allows them to showcase their refined handwriting skills and develop
  pride in producing polished work they can carry forward into other areas of learning.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-465-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-465-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-465-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-465-4 ;
  curric:id "465"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.705175Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-developing-handwriting-fluency .

oakcurric:unit-644
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Climate emergency: journalistic report writing"@en ;
  curric:slug "climate-emergency-journalistic-report-writing" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils get into role as a journalist attending a climate emergency
  protest, in prepartion for writing a journalistic report based on the event. In so doing,
  pupils practise integrating direct speech throughout their report to add credibility to
  the point of view they are writing from."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on writing in the journalistic style from the
  Year 5 unit, 'The Titanic: journalistic report writing'. Opportunities for wider political,
  geographical and scientific learning are on offer here; pupils get into role as a journalist
  attending a climate emergency protest, on which they write from the journalist's perspective.
  Pupils' reports are written cohesively with a range of sentence structures and speech
  punctuation is included with quotations. This unit prepares pupils for climate crisis essay
  writing in the Year 6 unit, 'Polar regions: essay writing'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-644-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-644-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-644-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-644-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-644-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-644-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-644-7 ;
  curric:id "644"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.712816Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-reading-and-writing-texts-that-inform .

oakcurric:unit-91
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Emotions words"@en ;
  curric:slug "emotions-words" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn a wider range of vocabulary to support writing
  descriptively about characters, settings and scenes, including ambitious vocabulary for
  emotions words that can be applied to descriptive writing passages."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on previously taught vocabulary for describing
  characters, settings and scenes, including action words in the Year 5 unit 'Action words'.
  Here, pupils learn new words to support the descriptive writing of varied characters and
  scenes, specifically for emotions words. This unit prepares pupils for learning a wider range
  of vocabulary to describe characters, settings and scenes in narrative writing, including
  more setting words in the Year 6 unit, 'Setting words'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-91-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-91-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-91-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-91-4 ,
