  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-developing-spelling-accuracy .

oakcurric:unit-656
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "'Crazy about Cats': reading"@en ;
  curric:slug "crazy-about-cats-reading" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils read and discuss the non-fiction text, 'Crazy about Cats'.
  They explore the features of a non-fiction text and build understanding of new vocabulary.
  Finally, pupils discuss the possible connections and purpose of the text."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' learning around the features of
  non-fiction texts, which was explored through the prior unit, 'Curious Creatures Glowing in
  the Dark'. In this unit, pupils explore more non-fiction, learning about purpose and layout
  and how the text is adapted to suit the intended audience. Pupils will develop their
  retrieval strategies to build comprehension. This unit prepares pupils for the future unit,
  'The aye-aye or wild cats: non-chronological report', where they will use information they
  read to write non-chronological reports on primates or wild cats.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-656-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-656-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-656-3 ;
  curric:id "656"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.337384Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-reading-and-writing-texts-that-inform .

oakcurric:unit-99
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Character: small, confident and shy words"@en ;
  curric:slug "character-small-confident-and-shy-words" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn a wider range of vocabulary to support writing about
  characters, including ambitious vocabulary for small, confident and shy words that can be
  applied to descriptive writing passages."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on previously taught vocabulary for describing
  characters, including big, beautiful and eye words in the Year 3 unit 'Character: big,
  beautiful and eye words'. Here, pupils learn new words to support the descriptive writing of
  small, confident and shy characters, passages or settings. This unit prepares pupils for
  learning a wider range of vocabulary to describe characters in narrative writing, including
  clever and clumsy words, in the Year 3 unit 'Character: clever and clumsy words'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-99-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-99-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-99-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-99-4 ,
