  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-developing-vocabulary-knowledge .

oakcurric:unit-126
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Anglerfish: non-chronological report"@en ;
  curric:slug "angler-fish-non-chronological-report" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils research the anglerfish's appearance and habitat in order to
  write a non-chronological report. Pupils focus on using a range of fronted adverbials,
  applying subject-specific vocabulary and writing in clear paragraphs. Pupils edit and
  publish their reports at the end of the unit."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds pupils' knowledge of non-chronological report
  writing from the Year 3 unit 'The Stone Age: non-chronological report'. Pupils write using
  the structure of an introduction, themed sections and a conclusion; they also write using a
  range of formal and viewpoint fronted adverbials and subject-specific vocabulary to ensure
  their writing flows cohesively. This unit prepares pupils for more non-chronological report
  writing in the Year 4 unit 'Ancient Greeks or Anglo-Saxons: non-chronological report'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-126-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-126-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-126-3 ;
  curric:id "126"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.386399Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-reading-and-writing-texts-that-inform .

oakcurric:unit-132
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Etymology and prefixes"@en ;
  curric:slug "etymology-and-prefixes" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn to investigate and spell words in English with Greek
  and Latin origins. Pupils also learn to spell polysyllabic words and words with a greater
  range of prefixes, like de-, re-, sub-, super-, inter- anti-, auto-, bi-, trans-, tele-
  and circum-."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' knowledge of spelling and grammar
  conventions associated with suffixes, their etymology and homophones learnt in the Year 4
  unit 'Year 4: Suffixes, etymology and homophones'. Here, pupils learn to spell words in
  English with Greek and Latin origins as well as polysyllabic words and words with a greater
  range of prefixes, like de-, re-, sub-, super-, inter- anti-, auto-, bi-, trans-, tele- and
  circum-. This unit prepares pupils for further etymological work in the Year 6 unit 'Year 6:
  Letter strings, etymology and curriculum words'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-132-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-132-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-132-3 ,
