oakcurric:unit-467
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Building  fluency in the four joins, suffixes and common exception words"@en ;
  curric:slug "building-fluency-in-the-four-joins-suffixes-and-common-exception-words" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils develop the quality and consistency of their handwriting.
  After reviwing the four joins, pupils write words with the suffixes -tion, -cian, -sion,
  and -ssion in cursive.They also practise cursive writing with homophones, common exception
  words, famous quotations and a poem."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on Year 3 by consolidating and extending pupils'
  handwriting skills. Reviewing the four joins gives pupils a solid foundation at the start of
  Year 4, preparing them to write words and longer sections of text with accuracy later in the
  unit. Expanding on Year 3's fluency work, this unit challenges pupils to apply conventions
  for writing quotations and poems while maintaining neat cursive writing. It also strengthens
  pupils' spelling knowledge through cursive writing. These skills ensure readiness for Year 5,
  where pupils will work on writing at greater speed.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-467-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-467-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-467-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-467-4 ;
  curric:id "467"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.527490Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-developing-handwriting-fluency .

oakcurric:unit-785
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "'A Christmas Carol': narrative writing and reading"@en ;
  curric:slug "a-christmas-carol-narrative-writing-and-reading" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils explore A Christmas Carol, learning about its context and
  developing comprehension through targeted questions. They analyse characterisation,
  themes, and the story's ending. Pupils then plan and write a setting description, along
  with the opening, build-up and climax."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils' narrative skills by developing their
  comprehension strategies and creative writing abilities. Pupils improve their reading skills
  through targeted retrieval and inference techniques, learning to analyse texts more
  critically and extract nuanced meanings. In writing, they develop more sophisticated
  communication by mastering varied sentence structures and selecting precise vocabulary that
  adds depth and clarity to their narratives. These skills prepare pupils for the next unit,
  where they will apply and develop narrative writing strategies.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-785-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-785-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-785-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-785-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-785-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-785-6 ;
  curric:id "785"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.600565Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-fiction-reading-spine ,
    oakcurric:thread-developing-fiction-writing .

oakcurric:unit-93
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Action words"@en ;
  curric:slug "action-words" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn a wider range of vocabulary to support writing
  descriptively about characters, settings and scenes, including ambitious vocabulary for
  action words that can be applied to descriptive writing passages."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on previously taught vocabulary for describing
  characters, settings and scenes, including taste and smell words in the Year 5 unit 'Taste
  and smell words'. Here, pupils learn new words to support the descriptive writing of varied
  characters and scenes, specifically for action words. This unit prepares pupils for learning
  a wider range of vocabulary to describe characters, settings and scenes in narrative writing,
  including emotions words, in the Year 6 unit 'Emotions words'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-93-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-93-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-93-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-93-4 ,
