  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-traditional-tales ,
    oakcurric:thread-fiction-reading-spine .

oakcurric:unit-916
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "'No Country' and 'Frizzy': graphic novels exploring identity and belonging"@en ;
  curric:slug "no-country-and-frizzy-graphic-novels-exploring-identity-and-belonging" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils read and explore two fictional graphic novel texts, 'No
  Country' and 'Frizzy'. They discuss the context of both graphic novels. Finally, pupils
  explore the visual, narrative and contextual elements of specific scenes and discuss the
  key themes within each text."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' understanding of the codes and
  conventions in graphic novels, which were explored in 'When Stars are Scattered: book club'.
  In this unit, they will explore the form in greater detail, ensuring pupils gain an
  understanding of key features and more complex terminology. Pupils will learn how both image
  and text can create meaning on their own. Both texts explore the themes of identity and
  belonging and will prepare pupils for the future unit, 'Cloud Busting: book club', where they
  will consider how reading a narrative in verse can convey themes.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-916-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-916-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-916-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-916-4 ;
  curric:id "916"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.300244Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-fiction-reading-spine .

oakcurric:unit-92
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Taste and smell words"@en ;
  curric:slug "taste-and-smell-words" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn a wider range of vocabulary to support writing
  descriptively about characters, settings and scenes, including ambitious vocabulary for
  taste and smell words that can be applied to descriptive writing passages."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on previously taught vocabulary for describing
  settings and scenes through weather, including cloudy, dark and rainy words in the Year 4
  unit 'Weather: cloudy, dark and rainy words'. Here, pupils learn new words to support the
  descriptive writing of varied characters and scenes, specifically for taste and smell words.
  This unit prepares pupils for learning a wider range of vocabulary to describe characters,
  settings and scenes in narrative writing, including action words, in the Year 5 unit 'Action
  words'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-92-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-92-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-92-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-92-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-92-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-92-6 ;
  curric:id "92"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.302457Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-developing-vocabulary-knowledge .

oakcurric:unit-130
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Verb, adjective and noun suffixes"@en ;
  curric:slug "verb-adjective-and-noun-suffixes" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn spelling and grammar conventions associated with
  certain verb, adjective and noun suffixes like -ing, -ed, -s, -ies, -es, -ves, -ate, -en,
  -ify and -less. Pupils review and learn more examples of how the addition of a suffix can
  affect the grammar of a word."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' knowledge of spelling and grammar
  conventions associated with certain suffixes learnt in the Year 4 unit 'Year 4: Verb and
  adjective suffixes'. Here, pupils review verb, adjective and noun suffixes, like -ing, -ed,
  -s, -ies, -es, -ves, -ate, -en, -ify, -ise, -ity, -ness, -ary, -ery -al, -ic, -ful and -less,
  reviewing how the addition of a suffix can affect the grammar of a word, for example by
  changing its word class or tense. This unit prepares pupils for further suffix work in the
  Year 5 unit 'Year 5: Noun suffixes, letter strings and homophones'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-130-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-130-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-130-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-130-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-130-5 ;
  curric:id "130"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.304805Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-developing-spelling-accuracy .

oakcurric:unit-97
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Weather: cloudy, dark and rainy words"@en ;
  curric:slug "weather-cloudy-dark-and-rainy-words" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn a wider range of vocabulary to support writing
  descriptively about the weather, including ambitious vocabulary for cloudy, dark and rainy
  words that can be applied to descriptive writing passages."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on previously taught vocabulary for describing
  settings and scenes through weather, including cold, calm and stormy words in the Year 4 unit
  'Weather: cold, calm and stormy words'. Here, pupils learn new words to support the
  descriptive writing of the weather, specifically for cloudy, dark and rainy scene-setting.
  This unit prepares pupils for learning a wider range of vocabulary to describe characters,
  settings and scenes in narrative writing, including taste and smell words, in the Year 5 unit
  'Taste and smell words'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-97-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-97-2 ,
