  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-developing-spoken-language .

oakcurric:unit-662
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "'Shackleton's Journey': reading"@en ;
  curric:slug "shackletons-journey-reading" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils read and explore the non-fiction picturebook text,
  'Shackleton's Journey'. They explore the context of the Antarctic expedition and examine
  the layout features of the text. Finally, pupils answer a range of comprehension questions
  and engage with the key themes."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on the Y5 unit, 'Curiosity: The Story of a Mars Rover:
  reading', where pupils read and discussed a non-fiction, picturebook narrative based on space
  exploration. In this unit, pupils will read and discuss a more complex non-fiction,
  picturebook narrative, based on true events of an Antarctic expedition led by Sir Ernest
  Shackleton in 1914. Pupils will use layout features and inference and retrieval skills to
  develop comprehension. This unit prepares pupils for the future unit, 'When the Sky Falls;
  reading', where they will read a text set during a similar time in history.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-662-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-662-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-662-3 ;
  curric:id "662"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.986280Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-reading-and-writing-texts-that-inform .

oakcurric:unit-925
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "'The Journey': diary writing"@en ;
  curric:slug "the-journey-diary-writing" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils write a diary entry based on the picture book 'The Journey'
  by Francesca Sanna. Pupils use the book as a starting point from which they write a diary
  entry, focusing on using the first person perspective consistently and practising the
  skill of varying tense accurately."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds pupils' knowledge of diary writing from the Year
  2 unit 'Florence Nightingale: diary writing'. The unit starts with an analysis of the plot
  and characters in the picture book 'The Journey' by Francesca Sanna in order for pupils to
  understand and discuss key themes in the text. Pupils review key features of diary entries,
  then they write their own version of a diary entry from the perspective of one of the girls.
  This unit prepares pupils for writing another diary entry in the Year 3 unit 'The Firework
  Maker's Daughter': reading and diary writing'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-925-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-925-2 ,
