oakcurric:unit-96
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Weather: cold, calm and stormy words"@en ;
  curric:slug "weather-cold-calm-and-stormy-words" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn a wider range of vocabulary to support writing
  descriptively about the weather, including ambitious vocabulary for cold, calm and stormy
  words that can be applied to descriptive writing passages."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on previously taught vocabulary for describing
  settings and scenes through weather, including wind and hot words in the Year 4 unit
  'Weather: wind and hot words'. Here, pupils learn new words to support the descriptive
  writing of the weather, specifically for cold, calm and stormy scene-setting. This unit
  prepares pupils for learning a wider range of vocabulary to describe settings and scenes in
  narrative writing, including cloudy, dark and rainy words, in the Year 4 unit 'Weather:
  cloudy, dark and rainy words'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-96-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-96-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-96-3 ,
