    oakcurric:thread-reading-and-writing-texts-that-inform ,
    oakcurric:thread-fiction-reading-spine .

oakcurric:unit-222
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Apostrophes and speech punctuation"@en ;
  curric:slug "apostrophes-and-speech-punctuation" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils review rules for apostrophes for contraction, singular
  possession and plural possession and punctuation conventions for speech first sentences.
  The new learning is around the rules for punctuating direct speech when it comes second
  after a reporting clause in a sentence."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds directly on learning how to punctuate speech
  first sentences in the Year 3 grammar unit 'Speech first punctuation and apostrophes', where
  direct speech comes first and reporting clauses come second in a sentence. New learning
  includes rules around punctuating speech second sentences, where the direct speech follows
  the reporting clause. Pupils review how to use apostrophes for contraction, singular and
  plural possession. This unit prepares pupils for further review of this punctuation in the
  Year 5 grammar unit 'Speech punctuation, parenthesis and apostrophes'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-222-1 ,
