  steps of the process happen."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.423892Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:priorknowledge-474-4
  a curric:PriorKnowledgeRequirement ;
  rdfs:label """Explanation texts can contain visual information, most commonly diagrams or
  photographs accompanied by a caption."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.423897Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:priorknowledge-474-5
  a curric:PriorKnowledgeRequirement ;
  rdfs:label """Important features of explanation texts include apostrophes for possession,
  subject-specific, factual vocabulary, numerical facts, sequencing and causal conjunctions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.423903Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:priorknowledge-474-6
  a curric:PriorKnowledgeRequirement ;
  rdfs:label "Nouns can be referred to in a range of ways to avoid repetition."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.423908Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

