# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Misconceptions
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-know-meaning-words-encountered
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not know the meaning of words encountered in the lesson."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure to gloss the meaning of all vocabulary used in the lesson and say in
  full sentences to help embed the meaning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084028Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-editing-means-correcting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that editing means correcting spelling and
  handwriting only."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Editing involves improving language choices, sentence structure and enhancing
  the overall quality and effectiveness of the writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084045Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-incorrectly-structured-clauses-adverbial
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may have incorrectly structured clauses or adverbial detail within
  speech sentences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Repeatedly remind pupils which is the direct speech part of a speech sentence
  and which is the reporting clause part of a speech sentence. Knowing where the reporting
  clause is will help eliminate mistakes within it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084051Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-distinguish-feelings
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to distinguish between feelings and character
  traits."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that feelings tend to be temporary and shifting but character traits
  are more permanent. Explore how lots of people feel 'nervous' from time to time, but that
  it appears as a regular part of Homily's interactions, making it a character trait."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084066Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-speak-quickly-quietly-look
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may speak very quickly, quietly and not look up from their page when
  presenting their report."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Techniques for effective presenting are explicitly identified, explained and
  modelled throughout both learning cycles."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084072Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-take-plans
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to take plans written in note form and construct
  sentences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Lesson gives the opportunity to explicitly model the thinking process when
  turning notes into full sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084078Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-one-verb-sentence
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may believe that there can only be one verb in a sentence."@en ;
  curric:correction """Auxiliary verbs are 'helping' verbs that connect to the main verb to help
  change the tense or meaning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084086Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-mistake-rolling-verb-misuse
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may mistake 'rolling' for a verb and misuse it in a sentence in this
  lesson."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model using 'rolling' in a sentence as an adjective and as a verb. Compare
  the difference."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084106Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-conclusion-simply-summarises
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that a conclusion simply summarises what has already been
  said, in the same way as the summary section of the PEPS structure."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that the conclusion can continue to have a persuasive impact by
  using linguistic techniques such as presumption and veiled threats."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084112Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-passive-sentence-contains
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that a passive sentence always contains the old subject of
  the active sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Sometimes the old subject is removed completely like in this example: 'We
  passed the ball.' > 'The ball was passed.'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084121Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-note-qualities
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to note down qualities for each of the Duleep
  Singhs."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Mind maps could be displayed for each family member with information added as
  pupils read."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084127Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-come-imagery
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to come up with imagery to describe their
  individual settings."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It would be useful to have a word bank with specific words or phrases to
  describe some key settings (for example, city, rural and coastal)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084134Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-assume-words-ending-ible
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may assume all words ending in -ible do not have a root word."@en ;
  curric:correction """Demonstrate that some words ending in '-ible', like 'sensible', are derived
  from recognisable English root words. However, there are also '-ible' words whose roots
  are not complete English words but may originate from Latin, like 'vis' to 'visible'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084145Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-want-take-their-pencil
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may want to take their pencil off before forming the suffix as they
  see it as separate to the root word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage children by modelling and emphasising that the pencil only comes
  off the page once the letter string is complete. Getting them to identify the last letter
  before starting can help to remind them of this."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084166Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-autistic-people-similar
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think all autistic people will be similar to Addie in the book or
  that all autistic people will experience the world in the same way."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that autistic experiences are diverse and that Addie's experiences
  are not universal. The book is written by an autistic writer, who drew on her own
  experiences when writing the book. No autistic person 'represents' all autistic people."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084171Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-get-gap-size
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children can struggle to get the gap size between the letters correct with
  this join."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model this join lots emphasising 'we dip down and across and then form the
  next letter so they can still hold hands, we don't want them to be far away from each
  other'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084251Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-convert-their-plan
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to convert their plan into complete sentences."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils have plenty of time to orally rehearse using their
  plans."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084271Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-relative-clause-placed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that a relative clause can only be placed in the middle of
  a sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Relative clauses can be placed after any noun or noun phrase that they refer
  to, including at the end of a sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084282Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-come-suitable
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it challenging to come up with suitable motions."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils could work in small groups for this task. As a class, come up with
  some ideas of what you might change or discuss related to the different aspects and have
  these visible for children when coming up with their motions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084289Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-certain-types-literature
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often think that only certain types of literature are valid such as
  novels."""@en ;
  curric:correction "Help pupils to celebrate a wide range of text types."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084295Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-veiled-threat-persuasive
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may use veiled threat as a persuasive technique, but they may use it
  clumsily or inappropriately."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The scaffolding and modelling of what appropriate veiled threat looks and
  sounds like is explicit in the lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084348Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-root-word-help
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may think the root word will help determine the spelling, but this
  does not always help."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Review links to root words when helpful, but encourage use of the rule about
  vowels and consonants to determine the spelling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084356Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-examples-imagery-language
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find some examples of imagery and language challenging to
  understand."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It may be useful to provide a visual sheet accompanying the poem, exploring
  some of the more complex terms (anvil, furnace)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084364Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-words-compound-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may think words are compound words if they can spot one word
  within another word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Show examples e.g. 'yesterday'. Whilst it has the word 'day' in it, if you
  were to separate this, the word 'yester' would not make sense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084370Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-words-word-hidden-word
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Not all words have a word hidden in a word."@en ;
  curric:correction """Show that this is a useful strategy to use when you can spot a word in a
  word, but it isn't always suitable."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084376Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-know-speech-first-means
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not know what 'speech first' means."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that if the direct speech opens or comes first in the sentence with
  the reporting clause afterwards or second, this can be referred to as a speech first
  sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084382Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-non-chronological-reports
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that non-chronological reports can be informal."@en ;
  curric:correction """Identify key linguistic features, such as subject-specific vocabulary and
  fronted adverbials, which contribute to formal tone."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084387Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-taught-exclamation-sentences-contain
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will have been taught that exclamation sentences must contain a verb,
  as in 'What a mess there is!'"""@en ;
  curric:correction """We use the term exclamative to include verbless construction like 'How cool!'
  alongside 'proper' exclamation sentences like 'How warm it is!'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084405Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-rush-planning-process-miss
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may rush through the planning process and miss opportunities to
  describe and extend key moments."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The planning worksheet breaks down each section into smaller parts, prompting
  pupils to focus on key details."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084420Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-place-time
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to place the time period in which the poem is
  set."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explicit discussion of features of the 18th Century and visual
  representations on a timeline will help pupils' understanding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084443Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-right-wrong-answer
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that there is a 'right' or 'wrong' answer when identifying
  themes within a text."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to the children that different people will identify different themes
  within the same text. As themes are not explicitly stated within a text, pupils may
  interpret them differently. Share everyone's ideas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084466Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-try-include-specific-facts
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils try to include specific facts in the introduction."@en ;
  curric:correction """An introduction's purpose is to introduce the topic and should only include
  general facts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084475Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-verbs-sentence-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may believe all verbs in a sentence are always in the same tense."@en ;
  curric:correction """Use the examples in the lesson to draw out the point that to maintain sense,
  we sometimes vary the tense of verbs in a sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084486Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-miss-double-letters-middle
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often miss the double letters in the middle of words that have a
  suffix."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Drawing attention to the patterns of how words are spelt when suffixes are
  added will help them to remember the double letter."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084499Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-adopt-positive-mindset
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to adopt a positive mindset towards editing."@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to see this as an opportunity to push themselves towards
  producing a polished piece of work that shows off all their skills. Having a real audience
  for the text in mind will help them with this."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.085288Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-copying-poem-children-forget-new
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When copying a poem, children can forget where the new line is or where a
  capital letter is needed."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model to the children that you must take time to review the poem first before
  copying it. Where are the new lines? Where are the capital letters? Is there any
  punctuation needed? This will help to prepare them for copying."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.085296Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-provide-answers-journalists-questions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may provide 'answers' to the journalist's questions rather than a full
  quotation that stands alone."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You may wish to model writing one of the quotations to show pupils that it
  needs to stand on its own without the questions as prompts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.085316Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-work-word
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might find it difficult to work out which word fills each gap in Task
  C, question 9, as more than one option can work in some of the sentences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to leave one out if there is more than one option that could
  work and return to it when there are less options to choose from."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.085464Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-commas-used-demarcate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that commas are only used to demarcate clauses or for
  'pauses'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to think about the specific rules for comma use, including
  for clauses, in lists and between adjectives in ENPs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.085490Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-identify-elements
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to identify which elements of their writing to
  edit."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils know the difference between different punctuation marks,
  different sentence structures, the meaning of 'ambitious vocabulary' and age-appropriate
  spelling rules."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.085516Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-difficulty-understanding-characterisation-body
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may have difficulty understanding characterisation through body
  language."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Play a game where children use body language to convey different feelings and
  thoughts and their partner needs to guess."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.085571Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-familiar-g-ck-end
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will be more familiar with 'g' and 'ck' at the end of words so may
  spell words incorrectly."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The ‘gue’ and ‘que’ sounds nearly always appear at the end of words e.g.
  vague and antique. The ‘g’ and the ‘k’ sound with the more common spellings, can appear
  anywhere within a word e.g. eagle, kid and back."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.085981Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-letter-string-represent
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Some children may think a letter string can only represent one sound."@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils of the key phonics principles: a sound can be represented by
  more than one letter, one sound can be represented by more than one spelling and one
  spelling can represent more than one sound. It is why the English language is so hard!"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.085987Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-poems-punctuated-like
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that poems are punctuated like prose."@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that different types of poetry follow different patterns.
  Punctuation is still used to help the reader and lines in poems often start with a capital
  letter."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086093Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-adopt-formal-tone
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to adopt the formal tone required for this letter."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure all pupils re-read Jean's letter in order to 'tune them in' to the
  formal tone. You may wish to generate more examples of similar letters for them to read."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086127Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-words-such-feathery
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may think words such as 'feathery' have the -ery suffix."@en ;
  curric:correction """Reinforce that most words ending in -ery have a root word. Encourage children
  to spot the root word before the -ery."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086133Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-illustrations-depict-exactly
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that illustrations always depict exactly what is mentioned in
  the words the author writes."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Show examples throughout the illustrated chapter book where the illustrations
  add in additional details, for example, the depiction of a car on pages 90 and 91."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086160Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-titanic-departed-its
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that the Titanic departed on its maiden voyage from
  Belfast."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explicit references should be made throughout the lesson to the maiden voyage
  beginning at Southampton."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086519Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-write-key-moments-resolution
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might not write about all the key moments from the resolution."@en ;
  curric:correction """The resolution follows a chronological order that includes four key moments
  that are detailed in pupils' plans."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088329Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-spelling-ize-represent
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils use the spelling 'ize' to represent the -ise suffix."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explicitly reference the difference between how the word is spelt and how it
  is pronounced. In American English, the spelling -ize is used."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088357Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-spot-progressive-tenses
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to spot progressive tenses in negative forms like 'won't
  be waiting'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Highlight that we still have an auxiliary verb and an -ing verb even when a
  negative interrupts like in 'were not watching/aren't looking'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088387Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-assume-evolution-refers-internal
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may assume 'evolution' refers to an internal or physical change in
  the Iron Man."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ask the children to consider whether they think the Iron Man always had the
  positive qualities we witness at the end. This is a great opportunity to explore the
  concept of 'perception'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088395Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-generate-varied
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it hard to generate varied speech ideas for Hogarth and
  ambitious vocabulary for the reporting clause that conveys the appropriate tone."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Get children to hot seat as Hogarth and imagine what they would say to the
  Iron Man in order to persuade him and win his trust. Ask children to consider how they
  said it in order to generate ideas for the reporting clause. Create a shared bank."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088401Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-necessary-give-advice
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think it is always necessary to give advice when someone shares
  their feelings."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to consider that they may not be well-placed to advise in
  some situations; it can be absolutely fine to just show that you understand the person's
  feelings and that you will support them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088424Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-plot-confusing-particularly
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find the plot confusing, particularly the idea that Ryder 'framed'
  Horner."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model your own 'reader talk', talking through the process of how you
  connected up information to work out what has happened in the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088447Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-become-confused-try-use
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may become confused and try to use a conditional clause without a main
  clause."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use the visuals of the superheroes to help emphasise that the conditional
  clause needs the main clause to make the sentence make sense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088489Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-know-free-verse-poems
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not know what free verse poems are."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that free verse poems have no fixed rhyme scheme or structure.
  However, this doesn't mean they can't include rhyming words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088506Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-choose-appropriate-cohesive
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to choose appropriate cohesive devices to connect
  ideas."""@en ;
  curric:correction "Give pupils access to the Cohesive Devices Bank throughout their writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088609Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-try-write-their-notes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may try to write their 'notes' in full sentences."@en ;
  curric:correction """Oral rehearsal of sentences using very short notes will help them in writing
  tasks using these facts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088614Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-able-think-related-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may not be able to think of related words to create word maps
  independently."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use a dictionary to support generating words and to check spelling. This will
  help pupils to find words with different suffixes as the start of the spelling will be the
  same."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088747Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-miss-letters-century-because
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils miss out letters in 'century' because they cannot hear all the
  sounds."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Say the word slowly, as it is spelt, in order to empahsise all the letters:
  cen -tur -y."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088898Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-text-recommendations-quite-short-length
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Text recommendations might be quite short in length, initially."@en ;
  curric:correction """Develop pupils' awareness of reasons and possible responses they could
  include to develop recommendations further."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088906Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-retrieving-answers-question-pupils-re
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When retrieving answers to a question, pupils may re-read the entire text each
  time."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise through modelling that pupils can use skimming and scanning
  strategies to quickly locate the information they require."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088967Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-two-prefixes-pre
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might think that the two prefixes 'pre' and 'un' have the same effect
  on a root word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Spend time teaching that each prefix has a different purpose and changes the
  root word in a different way."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088989Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-feel-stick-rigidly-dialogues
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may feel they have to stick rigidly to the dialogues and Addie's
  thoughts as shown in the book."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain and model how we can use our own imagination to build on the ideas in
  the book and make the drama our own."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089084Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-planning-needs-detailed-plans-written
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Planning needs to be detailed and plans should be written in full
  sentences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Planning should log key vocabulary, linguistic devices and be written in
  note-from using bullet points."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089253Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-copy-notes-directly-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils copy notes directly from their plans without forming full
  sentences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should say the sentence aloud first, then write it out. Finally,
  pupils should check their writing for sense and punctuation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089326Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-words-letters-strings
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may think all words with the letters strings have prefixes."@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss words using the letter sequence but not as a prefix, e.g. disturb,
  imp and uncle. Reinforce the definition of 'root word' and 'prefix'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089337Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-sentence-beginning-ing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that any sentence beginning with an -ing word contains a
  non-finite clause."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that a non-finite clause is a subordinate clause so cannot make
  complete sense - 'Singing is great!' is not a non-finite clause."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089354Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-whenever-use-using
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that whenever we use 'those' or 'this', we are using a
  determiner."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Demonstratives are only determiners if they are introducing a noun in a
  sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089371Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-same-words-act-prepositions-adverbs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The same words act as prepositions and adverbs or as prepositions and
  subordinating conjunctions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Prepositions are followed by nouns; subordinating conjunctions are in
  clauses; adverbs modify verbs and adjectives."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089383Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-simple-sentences-statements
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that simple sentences that are statements can only give
  facts."""@en ;
  curric:correction "Simple sentences can be used to state facts, opinions and emotions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089476Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-way-learn-something
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that the only way to learn something by heart is to keep
  reading it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that they can also check their progress with cloze procedure
  exercises."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089677Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-complex-character-trait
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle with some of the complex character trait vocabulary."@en ;
  curric:correction """Use the vocabulary pictures to tell a very short story about how what the
  character is doing reflects the word - or choose your own images which do this in another
  way if you prefer."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089704Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-add-parenthesis-sentence
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to add parenthesis to a sentence in the correct
  position."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Parenthesis often follows a noun to add extra information; it can be removed
  and the sentence will still make sense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089737Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-words-end-s-need-apostrophe
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "All words that end in -s need an apostrophe before the -s."@en ;
  curric:correction """An apostrophe before the 's' is only used for indicating possession in
  singular nouns, not for all words ending in 's'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089742Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-assume-word-short-vowel
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might assume that every word with a short vowel sound should have a
  double consonant."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that this is not always the case and give them examples of
  words such as 'hot' not 'hott' and 'shut' not 'shutt'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089765Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-need-write-full
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think they need to write full sentences on their plan."@en ;
  curric:correction """Plans are written to support pupils with future writing. Plans include
  ambitious vocabulary in note form."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089798Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-show-incorrect-speech-punctuation
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may show incorrect speech punctuation skills."@en ;
  curric:correction """The first learning cycle is focused on punctuating speech first and second
  sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089884Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-get-confused-join-use
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some children might get confused with which join to use and try joining
  letters with the incorrect join."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Showing the children a visual of the four joins can help them to decide which
  join should be used."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.090215Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-realise-significance-scrooges-transformation
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not realise the significance of Scrooge's transformation in the
  ending."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils in lots of detail how Scrooge behaved and treated others in
  Chapter 1. Re-reading Chapter 1 would be helpful."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.090923Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-word-pairs-need-extra-explanation
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some of the word pairs will need extra explanation such as 'squint
  suspiciously'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide an example of when someone might 'squint suspiciously'. For example,
  'She squinted suspiciously at the unfamiliar figure lurking in the shadows, unsure of
  their intentions.'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.090934Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-words-similar-meaning-pupils-answers
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """As most of these words have a similar meaning, pupils answers may vary in Task
  C, question 9."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that there is more than one option that can work in each
  sentence. The word maps from previous tasks might help them to find the best answers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.090951Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-writing-quotations-children-forget-start
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Sometimes when writing quotations, the children may forget to start with a
  capital letter as they are concentrating on using the inverted commas."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model clearly by saying your thought process out loud to remind the children
  that a capital letter is needed. For example, 'quotation mark, capital letter, lift my
  pencil...'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.090965Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-write-words-like-basically
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children write words like 'basically' how they sound: 'basicly'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Show the root words ending in 'ic' and how -ally is added. Say the words how
  they are spelt to help remember."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.090971Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-create-clause-instead-phrase
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may create a clause instead of a phrase by using a verb in their
  fronted adverbial."""@en ;
  curric:correction """This is not wrong, but explain to children we are focusing on phrases and
  words today."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.090976Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-generate-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to generate some of their own ideas for precise
  and ambitious vocabulary."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model use of a thesaurus to up level simple pieces of vocabulary. For
  example, instead of 'hot', children might use 'scorching', 'blistering' or 'burning'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.090987Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-non-finite-complex-sentences
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils' non-finite complex sentences won't make sense if both clauses have
  different subjects."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make explicit reference to the subject that performs the verb in each
  non-finite clause being the same subject in the main clause."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.090996Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-see-connections-joseph
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to see connections between Joseph and Adonis in the second
  task."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You may wish to discuss the idea of a metaphorical 'cage' midway through
  pupils' discussions, discussing ways in which Joseph is 'caged' by his difficulties."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091040Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-words-gargantuan-bulky
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might think the words 'gargantuan' and 'bulky' can be used
  interchangeably."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use the word pairs to help pupils see and hear the words in nuanced
  contexts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091477Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-try-include-subject-specific
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils try to include subject-specific information in the introduction."@en ;
  curric:correction """An introduction's purpose is to introduce the topic and should only include
  general facts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091838Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-become-concerned-rules-use
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some children can become concerned that there are rules about when to use a
  pen and when to use a pencil. This can slow them down and take the focus from the task."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind the children of the questions in this lesson. What are the attributes
  of the tools and which is best suited for the task? Remind them that there are no set
  rules and sometimes it can come down to personal preference."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091858Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-curriculum-words-reigh-island-february
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The curriculum words 'reigh', 'island' and 'February' can be mis-spelt,
  without the silent letters."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Practise saying the word how it is spelt, e.g. Feb-ru-ar-y. Use the 'naughty
  letters' strategy to emphasise unusual letters in the words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091928Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-mis-spell-words-ending
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The children mis-spell words ending in -ness with root words ending in
  'y'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Focus on the pronounciation of the word. Stretch it slowly: happ-i-ness. The
  'i' can be heard clearly making the 'ee' sound."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091936Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-notice-patterns-associated-poem
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not notice the patterns that can be associated with each poem when
  reading aloud."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils to think about rhythm and rhyme when considering how to
  interpret a poem to be read aloud. Do they notice a particular rhythm when they read?"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091942Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-overuse-gestures-movement-performing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may overuse gestures and movement when performing poetry."@en ;
  curric:correction """Gestures and movement used in the performance should add rather than detract
  from the focus, which is the poem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091956Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-illustrations-drawn-pencil
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that illustrations are always drawn in pencil."@en ;
  curric:correction """Include access to a wide range of materials which pupils can use to create an
  illustration for their poem. This might include colouring pencils, charcoal, watercolour,
  oil pastel, clay etc."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091962Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confuse-rhetorical-questions-standard
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may confuse rhetorical questions and standard questions."@en ;
  curric:correction """Most questions demand an answer; in a rhetorical question, the question
  itself contains the implied, expected answer."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091968Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-expected-say-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe they are expected to say their text map the same each time
  they repeat it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The purpose of the text map is to remember the events; ideally, pupils would
  have repeated opportunities to rehearse the text map, trying out different language each
  time. You will find pupils readily copy language you used in your own retelling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091996Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-write-moments-take-place
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might write about moments that take place in the opening, build-up or
  resolution."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The climax follows a clear, chronological order that includes the three key
  moments from pupils' plans."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092004Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-reflect-characters
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to reflect on a character's identity and sense
  of belonging in Task B."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that identity and belonging can be shown through the boys'
  character traits, their relationships with their families and the actions they perform."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092274Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-remember-one-loops-f
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children will often remember one of the loops for the f but forget the
  other."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide lots of modelling and emphasising that the letter f needs to 'hold
  hands' with the letter in front and behind it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092406Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-identify-develop
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to identify or develop appropriate prepositions
  to precisely describe details about nouns within the setting."""@en ;
  curric:correction """After revealing the prepositions 'beneath' and 'towards', brainstorm a range
  of helpful prepositions as a class and create a shared bank that the children can use."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092587Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-label-characters-like-emily
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may label characters like Emily and Miss Murphy as simply 'bad',
  instead of trying to see their motivations."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that giving reasons for someone's actions is not the same as
  excusing them; most things we do have a reason - that reason might just be a bad one!"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092593Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-non-chronological-reports-written-first
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Non-chronological reports can be written in the first person."@en ;
  curric:correction """Non-chronological reports are only written in the third person. A
  non-chronological report is not a biography or recount."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092604Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-connect-ideas-together
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to connect ideas together using cohesive devices."@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide plenty of time for oral rehearsal using the bank of cohesive devices
  and model selecting different options for connecting ideas together."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092615Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-correct-answers-using
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find correct answers using the strategies but might not understand
  the meaning of them."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Offer students an opportunity to ask questions about the text and explore the
  definitions of unfamiliar vocabulary."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092623Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-identifying-moral-message
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find identifying a moral message from the text challenging."@en ;
  curric:correction """You could support identification by drawing pupils' attention to moral
  messages they might have gained from previous texts shared with the class."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092634Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-create-formal-tone
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may struggle to create a formal tone without knowledge or exposure to
  formal vocabulary."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Offer opportunities for children to self-correct with the use of a thesaurus
  for more formal synonyms."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092640Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-spell-ending-professions-cion
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils spell the ending of professions 'cion'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Focus on the difference between -ion and -ian endings. Say the word how it's
  spelt to reinforce this: mu -si -ci -an."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092651Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-difficulty-identifying-word-class
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may have difficulty identifying the word class of focus words in the
  lesson."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Help the children to put the words into simple sentences in order to help
  identify the word class. Is it a naming word for a person, place, thing or idea? Is it
  describing a noun? etc."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092665Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-generating-introductory-sentence
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle with generating an introductory sentence for each
  section."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ask pupils to think about the main point of the paragraph, e.g. What is most
  obvious about the penguins' appearance? Are penguins well-adapted? If so, to what?"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092683Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-essay-two-sided
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that an essay is always a two-sided discussion leading to
  the writer's own conclusion."""@en ;
  curric:correction """In this unit, we will write a one-sided essay, which makes the argument posed
  in the title; we will avoid presenting this as the writer's own opinion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092691Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-many-words-high-frequency-common
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Many of these words are high frequency or common exception words."@en ;
  curric:correction """Be explicit about the difficulties in spelling these words and give time to
  practise spelling these common exception words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092699Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-use-word
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to use the word 'impenetrable' effectively.
  They might find it difficult to use it to describe a 'mystery' or 'darkness'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that 'impenetrable' can also be used to describe
  something as 'extremely difficult to understand'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092705Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-switch-tenses
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to switch between tenses in the final
  paragraph."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure you share your thoughts as a writer as you do the shared writing for
  this paragraph, showing that it is normal to switch tenses in this way when we are
  describing present emotions with a retelling of past events."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092711Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-homophones-sound-same-rely-previous
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Homophones sound the same, so they may rely on previous spelling rules and so,
  spell them the same."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Spend time showing each word in a sentence, use images to support
  understanding and make sure each homophone is practised using a strategy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092725Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-make-wish-themselves-personally
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may make a wish for themselves personally in Task A."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ask pupils to consider the impact that they could have on their local
  community and wider world when discussing their wishes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092736Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-repetitive-language-choices
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may use repetitive language choices."@en ;
  curric:correction """Exposure to a range of compound adjectives and synonyms in the teacher model
  will support with language variation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092747Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-forget-refer-iron-man
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may forget to refer to the Iron Man using a variety of nouns."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ask children to brainstorm a variety of different nouns for the Iron Man.
  They can use their plan to help them with this. Create a shared bank for children to refer
  to during writing. Examples: figure, creature, lifeform."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092753Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-planning-needs-detailed-include-full
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Planning needs to be detailed and include full sentences."@en ;
  curric:correction """Planning should only log key vocabulary and it should be written in note-form
  using bullet points."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092758Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-blistering-used-describe
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think 'blistering' can only be used to describe heat."@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss the word pairs such as 'blistering words' and 'blistering pace' and
  ask pupils to describe how they might be 'blistering'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092766Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-need-use-new
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think they need to use new ideas when publishing their writing."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should use the sections they have written in previous lessons that
  have been planned, drafted and edited."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092772Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dip-third-join-challenging-first
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The dip down for the third join can be challenging at first, especially when
  joining to the letter e."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model with emphasis the dip down so that children can see its importance and
  purpose. Give them time to really look at the join to the letter e. Allow them to realise
  themselves that the dip down begins the formation of the letter e."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093331Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-include-details-information-kept
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may include details and information that should be kept for the second
  part of the main body."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils' planning documents clearly outline which key events should be
  described in part one. The planning document is re-visited and shared in learning cycle
  two."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093356Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-come-ambitious
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it hard to come up with ambitious vocabulary for each part of
  their plan."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Come up with precise and ambitious vocabulary as a class first and create a
  word bank for display. Pupils could work in pairs or small groups to complete their plans."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093362Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-include-facts-specific
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may want to include facts that are too specific for the opening."@en ;
  curric:correction """Make explicit and repeated reference to only including general information.
  Use the 5 Ws (who, what, where, when, why) to help embed this."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093483Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-find-examples
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to find examples of personification and explain
  the impact of using this."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You could show the whole poem on the slides and work as a class to find
  different examples. Then children can work in pairs to find more examples at their tables."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093548Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-use-colon-explain
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to use a colon to explain correctly."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that there must be what could be a complete sentence on either side
  of the colon and the section after the colon must explain what comes before the colon."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093554Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-try-include-one-features
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may try to include every one of these features in their speech."@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that a speech does not need to contain all of these features.
  Encourage pupils to choose three features to include."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093595Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-familiar-sh-digraph-spell
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will be more familiar with the 'sh' digraph so may spell words
  containing 'ch' incorrectly."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Talk about the origin of words drawing links between spellings containing the
  'ch' spelling sounding like the /sh/ sound."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093601Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-start-describing-details-clock
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may start describing the details of the Clock home in the frst
  paragraph."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Clearly remind pupils that paragraph one should be describing where the Clock
  family home is located in relation to the main house. Paragraph two will give details of
  their home."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093623Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-character-traits-remain
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that character traits remain fixed throughout the
  narrative."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that character traits do not usually stay static. Adults could
  display a 'role on the wall' to note changes in characterisation of Nate as pupils
  progress through the narrative."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093642Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-character-looks-determines
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that how a character looks determines whether they are friend
  or foe."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When discussing the character of Sally Bones, focus on character traits that
  intimidate Varjak, not solely her appearance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093667Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-use-full-range
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to use the full range of cohesive devices and punctuation
  expected from them."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Our Y6 Grammar 'Revision' unit covers the full range of cohesive devices and
  punctuation expected of pupils in Year 6. You might wish to use these lessons to remind
  pupils of certain features they may wish to include."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093700Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-non-fiction-texts
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think all non-fiction texts are entirely factual."@en ;
  curric:correction """'A Journey Through Greek Myths' is a non-fiction text that includes fictional
  retellings of ancient Greek myths."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094177Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-identify-key-thrust
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to identify the key thrust of Addie's speech and instead
  focus on minor details."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When reading the text, say aloud your thoughts as a reader, for instance 'Ah,
  I can see Addie is trying to show the connection between what happened in the past and
  what's happened to Bonnie ...'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094196Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-accustomed-teacher-modelling-written
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may be accustomed to teacher modelling of written work."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure plenty of time for oral rehearsal and encourage pupils to constantly
  refer back to their plan."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094201Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-conclude-cant-make-mistakes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may conclude that they can't make any mistakes with pens."@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise to the children that pencils are used if there are going to be a
  lot of mistakes or changes like a sketch or a calculation. Explain that it's OK to make
  some mistakes with a pen and that these will need to be crossed out neatly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094207Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-spellings-such-practice-advice-device
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Spellings such as 'practice', 'advice' and 'device' can be more difficult for
  children."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explore words ending in -ice and words ending in -ise. Listen to the
  difference in pronunciation of these words and discuss the difference in word class too
  e.g. practice, advice, device = nouns, practise, advise, devise = verbs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094225Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-mix-double-letters-disappear
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils mix up the double letters in 'disappear'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that 'disappear' is made of the prefix dis- and appear. That
  way, you know there will only be a single 's'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094245Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-select-wrong-spelling-wrong
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may select the wrong spelling for the wrong sentence."@en ;
  curric:correction """Spend time talking about the meaning of the words as you come across them.
  Show pupils how to use the context of the sentence to help you decipher the meaning and if
  relevant, discuss its etymology."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094278Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-archaic-unfamiliar-language-pupils-recognise
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """There is archaic and unfamiliar language that pupils will not recognise or
  understand in the poem."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that it is normal to not understand all the language in an
  archaic text, especially when we first read it. That is OK. There will be lots of
  opportunities to build our understanding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094304Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-fully-understand-legacy-people
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not fully understand the legacy of people, events or actions that
  happened in the past."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Refer pupils to examples that they have studied so far of people, events or
  actions that have left a legacy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094309Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-words-antonym-e
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe all words have an antonym e.g. chicken/duck;
  tree/plant."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that these are not strictly opposites - they are just
  different! Most antonyms are nouns and verbs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094333Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-difficulty-making-edits-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may have difficulty making edits to their work in a practical way -
  where to write extra words etc."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Writing double-spaced is a good way of allowing room for editing - or you may
  want to have pupils re-draft the opening completely, depending on your school's approach."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094339Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confuse-exclamatory-phrase-exclamation
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils confuse an exclamatory phrase with an exclamation sentence."@en ;
  curric:correction """A phrase is a group of words with no verb. Any simple sentence must include a
  verb. Verbs in exclamation sentences are often being verbs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094344Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-different-ideas-parts-bfg
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may have different ideas about which parts of 'The BFG' constitute the
  opening, build-up, climax and resolution."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Summarising means pulling out the key events and ideas from a text. Ensure
  that pupils know that the way one person summarises may be different to another person's
  summary."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094350Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-identify-opinions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to identify opinions and reasons in a
  persuasive letter."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Look for sentences where the writer expresses their emotions and a reason for
  why they are feeling that way."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094376Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-get-confused-whether-put
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may get confused about whether to put their ideas about Hogarth on the
  inside or the outside of the character outline."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model completing the activity as a class and allow children to work in pairs
  or small groups using big sugar paper."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094396Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-using-accurate-punctuation
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle with using accurate punctuation in direct speech
  sentences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Give pupils an opportunity to practise writing speech on mini-whiteboards and
  provide a visual scaffold to support them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094402Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-specific-facts-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may use specific facts from their research in the introduction."@en ;
  curric:correction """Make explicit reference to 'general information' with clear modelling of what
  this looks like as exemplified in learning cycles one and two."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094889Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-remember-events
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it difficult to remember the events of the narrative."@en ;
  curric:correction """You may wish to work with a group of pupils to create a shared text map
  together, meaning it will be easier for you to rehearse with these pupils, modelling the
  process using a shared text map instead of individual ones."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094894Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-speech-either-good
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that a speech is either good or bad."@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that a speech can have strong elements, but still have areas for
  improvement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094900Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-mix-representations-l-forget
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils can mix up the representations of 'l' and forget the representations
  which are most likely."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Frame any new learning on -al in the context of prior knowledge around
  representations of 'l', highlighting the most common representations."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094915Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-double-consonant-adding
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils often forget to double the consonant when adding the suffix -er."@en ;
  curric:correction """Show non-examples when the consonant has not been doubled after a short vowel
  sound (hot-hoter). Explain how this alters our pronunciation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094921Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-explanation-texts-written-order
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Explanation texts  can be written in any order."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explanation texts are written in chronological order; they explain a process
  in the order in which it happens."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094937Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-remember-order
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to remember the order in which the steps
  happen."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Review the steps in order lots of times together before completing the
  ordering board."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094945Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-ei-spelling-represents
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that the 'ei' spelling only represents the 'ee' phoneme."@en ;
  curric:correction """Show a range of words with 'ei' representing different sounds. You can
  stretch and sound button to show the direct phoneme - grapheme correspondence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094951Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-structure-content
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it hard to structure the content of their letter."@en ;
  curric:correction "Provide a model or structure for the pupils to follow."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094970Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-know-birds-described-prior
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not know the birds described prior to reading the poems."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils could research the three species before reading. Alternatively, the
  poem could act as a stimulus to prompt further reading."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094975Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-poem-inaccessible-because
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that this poem is inaccessible because the language is
  difficult to understand."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that poems can be easier to understand once we work out the
  meaning of each line and explore the vocabulary used. This is modelled in LC1."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094981Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-note-two
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to note two different impressions when asked in
  Task B."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to think about Emmeline from Sophia's perspective. Verbally
  model rephrasing Sophia's thoughts into an impression a reader might make about Emmeline."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095076Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-editing-involves-re
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that editing involves re-writing most or all of the text."@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that editing involves checking for mistakes and making small
  tweaks to the text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095082Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-know-use-comma-demarcate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils do not know when to use a comma to demarcate between the adverbial and
  main clause."""@en ;
  curric:correction """If the adverbial clause is first in the sentence, a comma is placed after it.
  If the main clause is first, no comma is placed after it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095087Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-speeches-include-features-included-lesson
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "All speeches must include all of the features included in this lesson."@en ;
  curric:correction """A good speech may include some of these features but it is not essential that
  all are used."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095093Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-know-spelling-due-able
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may not know the spelling due to not always being able to rely on
  rules."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind children of the range of spelling strategies they could use to
  remember the spellings, such as naughty letters or big letters."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095098Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-want-copy-teacher-model
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may want to copy the teacher model and teacher plan."@en ;
  curric:correction """Incorporate opportunities for paired talk and suggest a range of possible
  vocabulary choices to support pupils in using their own ideas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095104Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-include-information-specific-conclusion
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may include information that is too specific for the conclusion."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explicit reference to 'general information' must be made and visual prompts
  across planning slides will help remind pupils."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095132Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-finding-evidence-shows
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that finding evidence that shows a person is feeling a
  certain way is the same as finding the motives behind their actions and feelings."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils are clear that, for instance, finding evidence that a character
  is sad is different to explaining why they are sad (the motive)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095137Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-write-ideas
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it hard to write ideas for Scrooge's inner thoughts in this
  lesson."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils have a plan to use with ideas for Scrooge's inner thoughts and
  model how to write these."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095668Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-focus-much-speed-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may focus so much on the speed of their writing that they use the
  incorrect cursive joins."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When modelling, emphasise that the flow is smooth because the correct joins
  are being used. Clear reminders about letter formation and joins will support the
  children."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095674Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-words-colossal-robust
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might think the words 'colossal' and 'robust' can be used
  interchangeably."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use the word pairs to help pupils see and hear the words in nuanced
  contexts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095702Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-bulging-used-verb-well-adjective
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Bulging can be used as a verb as well as an adjective so children might use it
  as a verb."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When used as a verb, 'bulging' typically describes the act of swelling,
  protruding, or sticking out, often in a rounded or prominent way."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095708Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-used-analysing-picturebook-texts
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not be used to analysing picturebook texts in finer detail."@en ;
  curric:correction """Adults could model text marking - asking questions and interrogating certain
  pages. Thoughts could be verbalised to model possible processes that you would encourage
  the pupils to use."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095713Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-try-use-many-gestures
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may try to use too many gestures throughout their performance."@en ;
  curric:correction """Gestures used in poetry performance should add depth and visual interest
  rather than overshadowing the spoken words of the poem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095727Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-see-words-unconnected-dont
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children see words as unconnected and so don't see the link between 'write'
  and 'wrote'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explicitly show how the spelling of connected words is linked, such as 'know'
  and 'knowledge' and 'write and 'wrote'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095732Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-negative-attitudes-towards-publishing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may have negative attitudes towards publishing their work."@en ;
  curric:correction """Publishing becomes highly motivating when there is a real audience for the
  work - for instance, you could copy the reports and illustrations and gather them into a
  presentation book that can be taken home by each child in turn."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095738Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-lesson-difficult-secure
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will find this lesson difficult if they do not have a secure
  understanding of what a syllable is."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ahead of the lesson, ask pupils to show you how many syllables there are in
  three different words (using their hands to 'clap the syllables') so you can assess if
  there are any pupils who need support prior to the lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095749Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-using-creates-adverbial
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that using 'before' and 'after' always creates an adverbial
  complex sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """These words often create phrases, rather than adverbial clauses; a clause
  requires a verb."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095754Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-need-include-explanation
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that they need to include all the explanation for their
  opinion in their point."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A point is just the speaker saying what they think or believe and giving one
  short reason to justify that opinion using the word because."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095765Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-compromise-solve-dispute
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that they should always compromise to solve a dispute."@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that compromise is used when **both parties** have something they
  can give up or offer."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095771Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-verbs-formed-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that all verbs are formed the same."@en ;
  curric:correction """Some verbs in English are irregular like 'be', 'say', 'come', 'bring',
  'catch', 'choose', 'do', 'drink', 'eat', 'find', 'keep' and 'leave'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095781Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-secure-asia
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils are not secure on where Asia is."@en ;
  curric:correction "Refer to Asia on a world map."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095789Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-second-bracket-parenthesis
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may forget the second bracket after parenthesis."@en ;
  curric:correction """Teacher explicitly models making this mistake and correcting it when
  re-reading the final written outcome at the end of the lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095819Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-develop-appropriate-show
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may struggle to develop appropriate 'show and tell' language for a
  range of emotions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Identify the emotions of characters during this section first and ask
  children to imagine how they might convey that feeling. E.g. Homily is feeling stubborn
  and firm. 'Show and tell' for this might be: She gave Pod a stern and silent look."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095830Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-identify-why
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to identify why a poem may be laid out in a
  certain way."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Present the poems on a class board or visualiser so that the children can
  clearly see how the poems have been presented on the page. Ask pupils what they notice and
  text mark the pages together."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095836Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-put-highwaymans
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to put the Highwayman's words into
  their own."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Key unfamiliar language is explained in the previous lesson (L10) and
  paraphrasing the Highwayman's words is modelled in this lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095847Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-write-much-detail
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may want to write with too much detail in the opening."@en ;
  curric:correction """Make explicit reference to 'general information' and remind pupils to keep
  information in the opening general."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095883Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-editing-simply-checking
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that editing is simply checking for things that are missing
  rather than editing and improving what is already there."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils to analyse their language choices to be sure each word is
  appropriately descriptive and ambitious."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095888Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-know-understand-meaning-many
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not know or understand the meaning of many words encountered in the
  lesson."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Put all unfamiliar vocabulary into simple sentences to expose children to the
  meaning. Make links to root words where possible."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095894Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-emotive-piece-narrative-overuse-melodrama
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """An emotive piece of narrative can sometimes overuse melodrama, exaggerating
  characters' feelings and actions too much."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils' representations of characters’ emotions and reactions are
  believable and consistent with their personalities."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095902Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-understand-difference
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to understand the difference between stories
  within the genre of folklore."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explore the differences between folktales and fairytales. For example,
  fairytales are more likely to involve magical or enchanting elements whereas folktales
  tend to reflect real-world settings and events."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096136Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-introduce-new-ideas
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may want to introduce new ideas or information in the conclusion."@en ;
  curric:correction """A conclusion does not introduce new information. Its purpose is to summarise
  the key points made previously throughout the text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096151Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-lift-their-pencil-middle
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may lift their pencil in the middle of the letter string to 'dot' the
  letter i or put the 'cross' on the letter t."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model to the children that you wait until the end of the letter string before
  adding the 'cross' or the 'dot'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096157Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-start-write-quicker-begin
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When children start to write quicker then they can begin to make more mistakes
  with the formation of their letters."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind the children of the importance of finding their balance between speed
  and accuracy. Model reviewing your writing so the children can become familiar with
  checking the legibility of their writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096162Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-feel-need-record-direct
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may feel that they need to record the direct speech in full to ensure
  it is 'accurate'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Although real journalists would want to keep the quotations exactly the same,
  it is fine for us to write notes in a plan."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096168Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-familiar-s-beginning-ss
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will be more familiar with 's' at the beginning and 'ss' in the middle
  of words so may spell words incorrectly."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Talk about the origin of words drawing links between words containing the
  'sc' spelling and looking at examples where it appears at the beginning and in the middle
  of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096189Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-clothing-mentioned-slides
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that the clothing mentioned in the slides are the only styles
  worn in Australia and Morocco."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Both countries have other forms of dress/attire - seen in the two scenes
  (hardware store, market). You could ask pupils to conduct more research into both
  cultures."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096195Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-thinking-speaking-role
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find thinking and speaking in role as the father or Beatrice
  challenging."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Drama activities, such as 'thought tapping' or 'hot seating' may be useful to
  provide pupils with examples of thoughts and speech."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096272Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-misspell-root-word-rather
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may misspell the root of the word, rather than the suffix."@en ;
  curric:correction """Spend time discussing what is unexpected or challenging about the stem of the
  focus words as well as the -tion endings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096278Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-able-record-themselves-second
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not be able to record themselves during the second strategy."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils could find a recording of the poem online. Hearing different
  interpretations of the poem from other performers can expose them to various styles and
  emotional expressions, which can inspire and inform their own recitals."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096283Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-assume-combination-words-create
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might assume any combination of words they create forms a compound
  word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Look at some non-examples such as 'starwhere' and 'somefish' to teach them
  that not every combination makes a compound word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096294Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-spell-savoury-without-u
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might spell 'savoury' without a 'u': 'savory'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Savory and savoury are both English terms. Savory is predominantly used in
  American English while savoury is predominantly used in British English."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096316Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-time-word-ends
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that any time a word ends with -ing, it is a verb in the
  progressive tense."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Sometimes, words ending -ing are acting as adjectives. We must look at the
  word before the word ending in -ing to check if it's a verb."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096331Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-remember-comma
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to remember the comma rule in a complex
  sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Commas are only needed in a complex sentence when the subordinate clause
  comes first. Remind pupils that if the subordinate clause comes second, they do not need a
  comma before the subordinating conjunction."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096343Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-know-related-root-word
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may not know the related root word or see how they are
  connected."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Put the /shun/ word and the associated root word into a simple sentence to
  help secure their meaning. This will help pupils see the connections in meaning and
  spelling between the words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096349Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-words-used-describe
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think these words can only be used to describe clouds."@en ;
  curric:correction """Draw attention to all the word pairs that aren't linked to the weather to
  highlight how useful these words are and how they can be used in multiple contexts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096362Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-internal-thoughts-written-first-person
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Internal thoughts are always written from the first person perspective of the
  character."""@en ;
  curric:correction """In this piece, pupils will not switch between the third person and the first
  person perspective. Ensure pupils use their plan with ideas for Paikea's internal thoughts
  and model how to write these in the third person."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096368Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-using-co-ordinating
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe using a co-ordinating conjunction always creates a compound
  sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Using a co-ordinating conjunction only creates a compound sentence if the
  conjunction is joining main clauses."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096792Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-mistakenly-use-ce-endings
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will mistakenly use -ce endings for verbs instead of -se endings or
  vice versa."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Look at a selection of words that fit this spelling pattern and help them to
  recognise that -ce typically indicates a noun, whilst -se indicates a verb."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096940Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-words-used-interchangeably
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might think these words can be used interchangeably. A 'mesmerising
  reputation' for example."""@en ;
  curric:correction "Encourage pupils to use the word pairs when they write their sentences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096959Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-spot-determiner-adjectives-used
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not spot a determiner if adjectives are used between the determiner
  and the noun."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that adjectives can be placed between the determiner and
  the noun."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096971Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-words-simply-synonyms
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think all these words are simply synonyms of 'disgusting'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand the nuances of each word i.e. 'rancid' implies
  something has gone rotten whilst 'repulsive' is used more to describe something that looks
  disgusting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096979Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-add-additional-information
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils want to add additional information about aye-ayes' diets or adaptations
  to the conclusion."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Information in the conclusion must be kept general and must summarise the
  rest of the report."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096986Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-previously-seen-relative-clause
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may have previously only seen a relative clause interrupting a main
  clause."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A relative clause can be placed after any noun it refers to, including at the
  end of a sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096998Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-sequencing-retelling-story-involves-recounting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Sequencing and retelling a story only involves recounting the events in the
  exact order that they occurred."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Effective sequencing and retelling requires pupils to know the plot deeply
  and to understand some key themes that are threaded through it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097007Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-integrate-direct-reported
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to integrate direct and reported speech into a paragraph
  that also contains factual information."""@en ;
  curric:correction """During shared writing, model how we can switch between direct and reported
  speech."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097332Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-editing-writing-involves-correcting-grammatical
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Editing writing only involves correcting grammatical errors and spelling
  mistakes."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Effective editing goes much deeper. Ensuring the overall structure is logical
  and the content flows smoothly is crucial. This involves checking the organisation of
  ideas, the coherence of paragraphs and the transitions between them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097337Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-group-words-main
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that any group of words that is not a main clause is a
  subordinate clause."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that knowing the difference between clauses (groups of words that
  contain verbs) and phrases (groups of words that do not) is key."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097343Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-character-book-person
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that a character in a book has to be a person or animal."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that objects can be personified; the illustrations visually
  bring to life the personalities and emotions of each crayon character."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097348Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-plural-nouns-end
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may believe all plural nouns end in s."@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that several very common plural nouns do not end in s - make a list
  of these to keep."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097359Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confused-structure-diary-entries
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may be confused by the structure of the diary entries proposed."@en ;
  curric:correction """We will be writing a diary entry for Juliet written after the ball and then a
  short second entry in which she reflects on the marriage agreement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097383Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-identify-prepositions-within
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to identify prepositions within a sentence & distinguish
  them from determiners."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Prepositions always come before a noun or noun phrase to say when, where or
  why; they are distinct from determiners, which show specificity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097400Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-comma-separate-main
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may use a comma to separate any main and subordinate clause."@en ;
  curric:correction """When an adverbial subordinate clause comes after a main clause, no comma is
  needed; relative subordinate clauses don't always need commas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097427Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-abdul-karims-description
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think Abdul Karim's description of India is fully linked to his own
  experiences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that Abdul Karim was born in the village of Lalitpur in the North
  Indian state of Uttar Pradesh. His family background was modest. His description is likely
  influenced by who he is talking to."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097432Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-much-experience-associating-colours
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not have much experience associating colours with feelings and
  emotions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """To support pupils, adults could discuss feelings and emotions and their
  associations to colour prior to the lesson. The Disney Pixar film 'Inside Out' would be a
  suitable starting point for this."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097438Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-use-vocabulary-original
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may only want to use vocabulary from the original story."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that we are retelling our own version of the story and
  therefore we can include our own precise and descriptive vocabulary."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097455Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-familiarity-either-setting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not have familiarity with either setting."@en ;
  curric:correction """Use Google Earth to explore the satellite view of the Valley of the Roses in
  Morocco and Rozelle, Sydney (which the city suburb is based on)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-performance-poetry-done-one-way
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Performance of poetry must be done only one way."@en ;
  curric:correction """Whilst poetry performance should adhere to the poem's original structure and
  rhythm, it is an art form that invites personal interpretation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097477Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-advert-sell-product
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children might think that an advert is always to sell a product."@en ;
  curric:correction """Expose children to a variety of adverts that have different purposes, e.g. to
  change behaviour (environment, diet, health, etc.)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097483Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-recommendation-comes-peer
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may just think a recommendation comes from a peer or teacher."@en ;
  curric:correction "Recommendations can come from a wide range of people and places."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097493Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-est-suffix-spelt
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils can think the -est suffix is spelt 'ist' or 'st' because that is what
  you can hear."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Review pupils' misconceptions after practice tasks. Even though the word can
  sound different, -est is always spelt in the same way."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097703Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-understand-term-strength-relation
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may only understand the term 'strength' in relation to physical
  strength."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Clearly explain the meaning of strength in terms of characters and provide
  children with examples. Pupils could discuss every day examples of strength of character."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097714Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-expect-heroes-embody-heroic
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may expect heroes to embody all of the heroic traits."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that heroes can go against stereotypes and expectations.
  These make characters complex and multi-faceted."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097730Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-use-yearning
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to use 'yearning' correctly in a sentence as it
  can be used as both a noun and an adjective."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Look at the word 'yearning' being used as an adjective and as a noun in
  sentences and discuss the difference. This is a good opportunity to revise word class."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097735Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-repetition-involves-repeating
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that repetition involves repeating just one word."@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that repetition is often most impactful when repeating a phrase
  at the start of a sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097741Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-questions-around-good-vs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may have questions around who the 'good' vs 'evil' characters
  are."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Goldilocks is the one who breaks into the bears' home and uses their things,
  therefore she would be considered the 'evil' character. However, ask/discuss whether her
  behaviour actually constitutes 'evil' and what her motivations might have been."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097754Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-understand-elements
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to understand elements from the opening due to
  unfamiliar vocabulary."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pre-teach unfamiliar vocabulary from the opening, using visual images to
  support student understanding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097774Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-realise-multiple-answers-open
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not realise that there are multiple answers to open-ended or
  personal reflection questions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to refer to the text as they discuss the questions. If a
  pupils' perspective can be justified by evidence in the text, it is a valid response."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097796Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-y-removed-replaced
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think 'y' is removed and replaced with an 'i', like with the suffix
  -ed e.g. carry"""@en ;
  curric:correction """Show that we end up with two 'i's in a row if this happens: fly becoming
  fliing, so we keep the 'y'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097815Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-feel-cover-event-part
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may feel they have to cover every event from this part of the book in
  this piece of writing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to zoom in on just two moments, drawing out all the details
  from these; this will allow them to really focus on the quality of writing rather than the
  plot details."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098530Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-find-evidence-within
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to find evidence within the text to support an idea."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils have read or followed the text themselves before attempting the
  tasks so that they are familiar with where to look for information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098552Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-inspirational-characters-found
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might think that inspirational characters are only found in two genres
  of texts."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Characters can inspire children regardless of the genre they are
  written in."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098558Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-persevere-verb-set-words-pupils
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """As 'persevere' is the only verb in this set of words, pupils may find it hard
  to use it effectively in a sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide pupils with additional sentences using this word so they can hear how
  to use it in context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098563Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-confuse-homophones-stationary-stationery
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children can confuse the homophones 'stationary' and 'stationery'."@en ;
  curric:correction "Use the mnemonic 'the stationer sells stationery' to help remember."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098569Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-one-correct-interpretation-poem
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "There is only one correct interpretation of a poem."@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise to pupils that each reader brings their unique perspective,
  experiences and emotions to the poem. There is no 'right or wrong'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098575Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-discuss-themes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to discuss themes part way through a
  narrative."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model examples of themes with how they are portrayed in the graphic novel
  text. For example, war and politics can be seen in the newspaper clippings and the
  discussion between Beatrice's parents."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098580Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-cannot-see-words-grave
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children cannot see how the words 'grave' and 'gravity' are connected."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain the different meanings of the word 'grave', including serious or
  heavy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098658Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-creating-their-own
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find creating their own repeated phrase during Task A
  challenging."""@en ;
  curric:correction "Adults may wish to provide a scaffold for pupils with some example lines."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098666Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-new-school-missed-secured
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils new to school may have missed or not secured prior learning, so will
  struggle to access the review lessons."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure you have a grasp on the coverage of the spelling content. Depending on
  your pupils' acquisition of spelling, you may wish to use these lessons as a basis for
  re-teaching or reviewing prior learning. Use the starter quiz to inform planning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098678Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-because-co-ordinating
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that \"because\" is a co-ordinating conjunction."@en ;
  curric:correction """There are three co-ordinating conjunctions that are most frequently used in
  English. These are \"and\", \"but\" and \"or\"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098706Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-different-ideas-parts-borrowers
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may have different ideas about which parts of 'The Borrowers'
  constitute the opening, build-up, climax and resolution."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils know that the way one person summarises may be different
  to another person's summary. If possible, print the story staircase on A3 sized paper to
  make Task B more accessible."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098713Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-identify-types
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it challenging to identify the types of complex sentences."@en ;
  curric:correction """The first learning cycle focuses on reviewing the three types of complex
  sentence previously learnt in the unit."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098720Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-able-spell-root-word
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may not be able to spell the root word or stem."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure to focus on all the difficult elements of the words presented, not
  only the -ous ending that demonstrates the spelling rule."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098734Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confused-presence-modal-verbs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may be confused by the presence of modal verbs at the start of
  questions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that in questions the modal verb can come first followed by the
  person we're referring to, then the main verb."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099572Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-use-accurate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to use accurate punctuation when writing direct
  speech that is part of a complex sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Refer to the Year 4 Grammar unit 'Apostrophes and speech punctuation' to
  support pupils with writing direct speech correctly. Remind pupils to start a new line
  each time there is a new speaker."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099604Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-know-highest
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to know what to do for highest quality
  editing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Each learning cycle identifies key areas to edit and provides isolated models
  of editing punctuation, sentence structure and vocabulary."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099624Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-adverbial-clause-comes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think the adverbial clause always comes second in an adverbial complex
  sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The position of the adverbial clause can swap. The adverbial clause can come
  first or second in an adverbial complex sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099641Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-nuanced-idea-pandas
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle with the nuanced idea that pandas' population declined and
  is now rising again."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that pandas are revered in China and that huge efforts have gone into
  their conservation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099664Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-tempted-use-short-sentences
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may be tempted to over-use short sentences in their writing."@en ;
  curric:correction """Show in your shared writing that short sentences are impactful **because**
  they contrast with the longer or more complex sentences we tend to use in formal narrative
  writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099754Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-taking-notes-children-feel-pressure
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When taking notes, the children may feel pressure to write at speed, creating
  mistakes with their letter formation and therefore the legibility of the notes."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Get the children to keep reading their notes back. Remind them that if they
  can't read the notes then they need to slow down and find a balance between speed,
  accuracy and legibility."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101104Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-write-facts-non-coherent
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils write facts in a non-coherent order."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils are following the order of the facts on their plans when
  writing full sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101447Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-write-their-facts-non
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils write their facts in a non-coherent order."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils are following the order of the facts on their plans when
  writing full sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101452Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-understand-emotions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to understand the emotions that often exist
  beneath anger. They may also find it difficult to distinguish between 'feeling' anger and
  'responding with' anger."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ask the children to consider a time they have felt angry and what emotions
  may have triggered the anger. E.g. loneliness or sadness. Explain that anger is a normal
  emotion to feel but understanding the cause of it can help us respond differently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101458Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-understand-vocabulary
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to understand some of the vocabulary in stanzas
  one and two."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Reading and listening to unfamiliar vocabulary should not put us off studying
  poetry or texts that contain it!"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101472Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-writers-start-writing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that all writers start writing and are successful from a
  young age."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that Coelho wrote poems for a long time before he became
  successful."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101498Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-negative-attitudes-towards-editing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may have negative attitudes towards editing their work."@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage a growth mindset, modelling the idea that all work can be improved
  and avoiding negative responses to mistakes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101520Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-need-include-name
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may think they need to include the name of the witness in the
  reported clause."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model to the pupils if the sentence preceding the reported speech introduces
  the witness, the reporting clause can use a pronoun instead."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101526Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-determine-suffix
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to determine which suffix or word to use to
  turn an adjective into its superlative form."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage the children to practise saying the superlative form of an
  adjective out loud to check it sounds right. Model and demonstrate the rules for how to
  turn adjectives into their superlative form."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101546Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-describe-darwins-theory
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to describe Darwin's theory of evolution in simple
  terms."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You may wish to allow time to model this section to pupils, showing them that
  a simple explanation can cover the main points briefly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101565Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-realise-story-contain-multiple
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may not realise that a story can contain multiple themes which
  sometimes overlap."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss a simple but well known tale and its many themes in advance of the
  lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101571Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-verse-novel-fixed-free-verse
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A verse novel has to be fixed or free verse. It cannot contain both."@en ;
  curric:correction """'Cloud Busting' has fixed and free verse poetry. The text includes a range of
  forms, including haikus, concrete poems and limericks."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101783Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-hard-determine-suffix
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children find it hard to determine which suffix or word to use to form
  comparatives and superlatives"""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage children to orally rehearse the comparative and superlative forms
  of adjectives to check that they sound correct."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101791Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-wish-directly-replicate-language
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may wish to directly replicate the language, style and vocabulary used
  in the poem."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The process of generating vocabulary from another poem is a source of
  inspiration to expand one's own vocabulary in a meaningful manner."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101806Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-aware-dates-chronology-within
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not be aware of the dates and chronology within global history of
  Ancient Egypt."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Show pupils where Ancient Egypt fits into a broader timeline of global
  history."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101820Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-words-letter-strings
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might think that all words with the letter strings 'ough' and 'au' are
  pronounced the same way."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Show pupils that these letter strings can sound different depending on the
  word they are in. Explore different words and talk about which sounds are the most and
  least common."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101844Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-grasp-different-types-subordinate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not grasp that the different types of subordinate clause are all
  subordinate clauses."""@en ;
  curric:correction "Reinforce the point that these are sub-types of subordinate clause."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101859Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-editing-process-correcting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may think that the editing process is just about correcting
  mistakes."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to the children that all writers use editing as an opportunity to
  improve their work as well as correcting mistakes. Even renowned authors make changes to
  their writing (vocabulary choice/sentence structure) in order to improve it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101870Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-miss-e-words-ending
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often miss out the 'e' or 'a' in words ending in -ery or -ary, as they
  are not always clearly pronounced."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Identify the endings -ary and -ery in focus words. Say the words how they are
  spelt to help emphasise the vowel spellings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101875Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-get-confused-adjective-suffocating
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might get confused with the adjective 'suffocating' and the verb
  'suffocate'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You could include a sentence where you have used a verb from the infinitive
  'to suffocate' and discuss what word class this is and why."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101881Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-include-unnecessary-details-summarising
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may include unnecessary details when summarising the story."@en ;
  curric:correction """Model non-examples when summarising the story. For example, model a sentence
  where an unnecessary detail has been included and ask the children to spot which piece of
  information could be taken out."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102474Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-realise-characterisation-complex-adjective
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may not realise that characterisation is more complex than just
  adjective choice. It is also about how they treat other people and how they are treated by
  other people."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Practise drawing from real life examples of how you develop an impression of
  a person and their characteristics."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102929Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-identify-differences
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it hard to identify the differences between the original
  Cinderella and the one in the poem."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Recap the traditional Cinderella story and how Cinderella is made to do all
  the chores. Highlight that she needed a prince to save her whereas in the poem she takes
  control of her own future."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102943Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-know-meaning-words-reviewed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may not know the meaning of some words reviewed, such a 'precision'
  or 'beautician'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain the meaning of unfamiliar vocabulary by giving a simple definition
  and applying in the context of a sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102948Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-able-identify-journalistic-tone
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not be able to identify journalistic tone."@en ;
  curric:correction """Journalistic tone is explicitly identified and modelled in explanation and
  check slides throughout the lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102959Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-need-extra-explanation-oppressive
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will need some extra explanation for some of the oppressive word pairs
  such as 'system'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide pupils with examples of how a system, a ruler or a government might
  be oppressive in nature."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102979Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-generate-ideas-josephs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to generate ideas for Joseph's feelings and emotions at
  different points of the climax."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You may want to add in role-play tasks as a 'way in' to the different points,
  modelling your thoughts in role as Joseph before giving pupils the chance to do the same."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103007Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-add-es-ies-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may add -es or -ies to all words ending in the letter 'y'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that words ending in a vowel, then a 'y', follow a
  different rule. Remind them we just add -s to make them plural."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103820Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-incorrectly-include-information-relevant
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may incorrectly include information that is not relevant to section
  one."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Learning cycle 1 explicitly outlines which aspects of prior research are
  appropriate for this section."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103867Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-word-classes-difficult
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might find the word classes difficult for these words. For example,
  they might think 'fragrance' is an adjective, confusing it with the word 'fragrant', or
  that 'reek' is an adjective."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to look at the word pairs to help to understand that most of
  these words are nouns. This is because the word pairs are adjectives."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103884Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-see-conversations-way-share
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may see conversations as only a way to share their interests with
  others."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind them that conversations are about 'receiving' as well as
  'transmitting' and that listening is a big part of what makes good conversation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103982Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-used-ck-representing-c
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will be used to the 'ck' representing the 'c' phoneme when at the end
  of the word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that in most words where the 'c' is at the end, it is represented as
  'ck'. As this is a suffix, it doesn't follow usual rules."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103999Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-get-carried-using-shakespearean
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils could get carried away with using Shakespearean style language and use
  it too frequently, taking away from them showing their understanding of the character of
  Macbeth."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use your shared writing section to exemplify only using a few words or
  phrases to give it a 'Shakespearean feel'. Remind pupils that we still want to include
  different sentence types to achieve text flow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104016Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-introduction-involves-explaining
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that an introduction involves explaining their points in
  detail."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that an introduction only needs to be three sentences long and
  it provides a general overview of the letter, rather than specific facts and details."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104030Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-ending-ture-easily-mixed-t
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The ending -ture can be easily mixed up with (t)cher."@en ;
  curric:correction """Help pupils to spot words with a root ending in 'ch' or 'tch' with the suffix
  -er."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104049Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-connect-ideas-appropriate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to connect ideas with appropriate linguistic features."@en ;
  curric:correction """When completing shared writing, show how the same ideas can be connected in
  different ways; focus on looking at the relationship between the ideas being connected."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104066Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-discuss-other-similarities-differences
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may discuss other similarities and differences between the songs (such
  as song structure, genre)."""@en ;
  curric:correction "Verbally model examples based on themes and imagery used."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104115Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confident-idea-paragraphs-composed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not be confident with the idea of paragraphs being composed of
  several linked sentences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """As you read, draw out the idea that all the sentences in each section are
  related to each other and deepen the reader's understanding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104130Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-lead-letter-r-challenging-children
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The lead out for the letter r can be challenging for children."@en ;
  curric:correction """When introducing the suffix -er and its formation, take time to allow the
  students to investigate and practise the 'dip down' for the lead out."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104136Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-person-either-good
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think a person is either 'good' or 'bad' at performing."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that successful performances need practice, like any skill. By
  identifying the elements that contribute to a successful performance, we can then practise
  them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104141Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-turn-simple-past
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may struggle to turn a simple past tense sentence into a perfect
  present tense sentence, especially when this involves changing the main verb."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explore simple past tense examples where the main verb needs changing as
  well. E.g. 'It was' becomes 'It has been'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104147Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-exhilarated-hard-use
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find 'exhilarated' hard to use in a sentence with the word pairs
  provided."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide pupils with additional sentences using this word so they can hear how
  to use it in context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104155Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-need-support-role-playing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may need some support in role playing as a Norse god."@en ;
  curric:correction """Teachers could go over some drama strategies/tips, alongside exploring how
  pupils could use 'show not tell' to explore character traits."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105442Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-begin-writing-character-standalone
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may begin writing about a character in a standalone text, rather than a
  series."""@en ;
  curric:correction """If a pupil has not encountered series fiction before, they will develop
  greater awareness through discussion with their peers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105582Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-try-include-many-persuasive
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may try to include too many persuasive linguistic techniques in one
  sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to the children that their sentences still need to make sense, so
  focus on one linguistic technique per sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105601Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-identify-transition-present
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children might struggle to identify how to transition into the present tense
  smoothly in a way that supports text flow."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Highlight the use of the compound sentence using 'but' to contrast between
  past and present emotions. Encourage children to orally rehearse a similar sentence as
  their transition point to the present tense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105607Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-rebuttal-points-argued-against
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Rebuttal points can be argued against."@en ;
  curric:correction """A rebuttal point comes at the start of a speaker's speech and cannot be
  responded to."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105624Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-understand-function-words-e
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not understand that the function of some words (e.g. before/after)
  depends on context."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that sometimes these words are acting as subordinating conjunctions
  and sometimes they start phrases."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105644Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confuse-silent-letters-digraphs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may confuse 'silent letters' and 'digraphs'."@en ;
  curric:correction """'kn' is a digraph making the /n/ sound but, in general, silent letters are
  individual letters in a word that are not pronounced, whereas digraphs are pairs of
  letters that represent a single sound."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105689Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-discuss-perspective
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to discuss how perspective can have an effect
  on their understanding of the poem and its themes."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It may be useful to remind pupils of the different perspectives that writing
  can take and the effect they can have on a reader or listener."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105698Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-completing-task-pupils-struggle-generate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "When completing Task A, pupils may struggle to generate ideas."@en ;
  curric:correction """Adults could provide a word bank and work with pupils to create a mind map of
  ideas. Examples can be included from 'Tempest Avenue' to further support."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105704Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-know-feminism-feminist-means
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not know what 'feminism' or 'feminist' means."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that before beginning this lesson, you have developed pupils'
  understanding of what feminism is. You could use PSHE sessions to explore this in more
  depth."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105734Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-describe-range
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to describe a range of aspects of Tim's
  appearance and feelings."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explicit modelling of adjectives, including compound adjectives, and
  show-not-tell will help pupils with their descriptions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105761Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-get-confused-writing-sentences
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may get confused when writing some sentences in present tense and some
  in future tense."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teacher models must make use of both the present and the future tenses. This
  must be explicitly explained when scaffolding the writing task."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105773Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-know-associated-root-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children do not know the associated root words."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure children understand the meaning of all root words used with the suffix
  -ous and practise saying them in sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105789Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-provide-two
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to provide two contrasting impressions of a
  character."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It may be helpful to visually mind map how readers might describe a character
  (using adjectives). Impressions can also be modelled verbally to develop pupils'
  understanding of character."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106525Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-adjective-choices-precise
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may use adjective choices that are not precise enough or appropriate
  for a certain moment."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Create a shared word bank for the characters at different moments that pupils
  can refer to."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106538Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-write-narrative-briefly
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think they can write a narrative by briefly explaining each key
  moment."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It is important we choose a range of adjectives, verbs and adverbs to include
  in our plan that creates a full, descriptive narrative. The reader needs to be able to
  'see' the pictures we paint with our words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106544Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-take-drama-activities-seriously
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not take drama activities seriously or may give only surface-level
  responses."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model the standard of response you expect and clarify expectations; remind
  pupils that we are empathising with real people and we should respect their experiences.
  Constantly showcase good examples from the class."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106576Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-shift-writing-third-person
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may shift into writing from the third person perspective."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pause at regular intervals during the writing process and have pupils read
  back and check for use of the first person."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106581Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-convert-notes-complete
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to convert notes into complete sentences."@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide lots of time for oral rehearsal at each stage of the lesson and
  ensure children have access to vocabulary and plans used earlier in the unit."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106587Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-use-nouns
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to use the nouns 'twilight' and 'dusk'
  effectively with the verb word pairs."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model using 'twilight' and 'dusk' in a sentence with different verbs (in
  differing forms) as examples."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106593Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-include-information-their-research
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may only include the information in their research notes and not draw
  ideas together into a conclusion."""@en ;
  curric:correction """While shared writing this section, constantly refer back to the essay
  question to ensure the conclusion addresses it head-on."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106600Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-identify-visual
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to identify visual, narrative and contextual
  elements in Task A."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Task A could be done in pairs or small groups, with adults supporting with
  modelled examples."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106609Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-avoid-repetition-describing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may struggle to avoid repetition for describing each encounter."@en ;
  curric:correction """Model a range of ways for saying the same thing. For example 'bumped into',
  'came across', 'encountered', 'stumbled across', etc. Create a class bank of phrases and
  ideas they can use in their plan."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106634Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-incorrectly-use-apostrophe-hear
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often incorrectly use an apostrophe when they hear an 's' at the end of
  the word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils of the rules for using apostrophes. Only use an apostrophe if
  you can name and recognise the rule - for omission or possession."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106659Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-unaware-layout-features-formal
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may be unaware of the layout features of a formal letter."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils know that a persuasive letter starts with the date, a
  greeting, is organised by paragraphs and ends with a sign-off."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106664Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-familiar-ff-gh-digraph
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will be familiar with the 'ff' and 'gh' digraph so may spell words
  contain 'ph' making the /f/ sound incorrectly."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Talk about the origin of words and draw links between spellings containing
  the 'ph' spelling sounding like the /f/ sound and where it's most likely to go in the
  word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106670Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-one-way-read-poem-aloud
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "There is only one way to read a poem aloud."@en ;
  curric:correction """Reading poetry aloud invites the reader to inject their own emotions,
  personal interpretation and expression into it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106712Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-rely-one-method-developing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may over-rely on one method for developing comprehension of new or
  unfamiliar words."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that words can be understood in different ways (e.g. “sociable” could
  be understood by 'reading around the word' or 'identifying the word class'). Encourage
  pupils to use a range of methods where applicable."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106786Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-able-think-text-emotional
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may not be able to think of a text that they have an emotional
  connection with."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils of texts that they have shared in class during the year or
  previous years. Model an example using a shared text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106791Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-generate-rhyming
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to generate rhyming words associated with the
  heat."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils could work in partners, or as a whole class, to create a list of
  rhyming words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106824Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-describing-impact-poems
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find describing the impact of the poem's imagery and structure
  challenging."""@en ;
  curric:correction "Pupils could use the modelled example and elaborate."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106841Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-incorrectly-place-apostrophe-singular
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils incorrectly place the apostrophe in the singular or plural noun that
  possesses the second noun."""@en ;
  curric:correction """An apostrophe is placed before the s at the end of the first noun when it is
  a singular noun that owns the second noun. An apostrophe is placed after the s at the end
  of the first noun when it is a plural noun that owns the second noun."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106875Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-provoking-emotional-response
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that provoking an emotional response in an audience is about
  making them sad."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils know there is a wide range of emotional responses that
  audience members may have - and they may vary from person to person. These include anger,
  frustration, enthusiasm, determination, sadness, joy, hope and belief."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106881Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-integrating-factual-information-main-paragraphs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Integrating factual information into the main paragraphs can be
  challenging."""@en ;
  curric:correction """We can't tell the whole story in the introduction; the story of what happened
  is gradually revealed as the perspectives are given."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106886Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-root-word-hard-spell-leads
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Often the root of the word is hard to spell so this leads to incorrect
  spellings."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss words that children find hard and look for root words that you
  recognise, or parts of the word that are difficult."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107241Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-using-formal-fronted
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may struggle with using a formal fronted adverbial to contrast
  appropriately."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model a formal fronted adverbial of contrast used incorrectly (reiterate same
  point in main clause). Ask children to analyse and correct it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107246Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-identify-rhyming-words-subject
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may identify rhyming words that are not subject appropriate for the
  slogan."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model examples and non-examples in context. E.g. 'hall' would not be a
  relevant rhyming word for 'ball'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107279Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-familiar-ck-digraph-spell
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will be familiar with the 'ck' digraph so may spell words containing
  'ch' making the /k/ sound incorrectly."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Talk about the origin of words and draw links between spellings containing
  the 'ch' spelling sounding like the /k/ sound."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107306Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-finishing-piece-writing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that finishing a piece of writing is the end of the writing
  process."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When adults model enthusiasm for editing and improving, pupils will follow.
  Giving pupils a real outcome and audience for their writing also hugely increases the
  motivation to edit and improve."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107323Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-get-confused-writing-headline
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children can get confused when writing the headline and start to join the
  capital letters to the lower case letters."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model to the children that you think about the headline before writing it.
  Which words will have capital letters? When forming the capital letter, exaggerate the
  action of lifting your pencil after the formation to remind the children."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107331Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-identify-appropriate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to identify appropriate adjectives and verbs
  and develop their own pieces of personification."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Brainstorm as a class and create a shared bank of human adjectives and verbs
  that would be appropriate for personifying elements of the scene. Children can then use
  this bank to support them in forming their own pieces of personification."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107657Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-start-using-hyphens-prefixes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may start using hyphens for all prefixes."@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that not all prefixes require a hyphen - some prefixes use them
  more frequently, but others rarely do."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107704Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-make-generalisations-based-gender
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may make generalisations based on the gender of the parents."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that it can be harmful to make assumptions based on gendered
  stereotypes. Family structures are different and unique. Explain that both mothers and
  fathers can perform a variety of actions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107727Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-difficulty-recognising-different-types
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may have difficulty recognising that there are different types of
  complex sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Different types of complex sentence contain different types of subordinate
  clause, each starting with a different type of word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107741Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-poems-include-rhyming
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think that all poems must include rhyming words."@en ;
  curric:correction """Use 'Teetering Towers' to exemplify that not all poems include rhyming words,
  but they can still follow a pattern and have a rythmic, musical quality."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107747Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-small-object-good
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that any small object can be a good subject for poetry."@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that the subject of a poem should be something that inspires
  poetry and will be interesting to write about. Provide children with a range of ideas for
  them to decide whether they are inspiring or not."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107810Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-person-good-bad
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think a person can be 'good' or 'bad' at performing."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that successful performances need practice, like any skill. By
  identifying the elements that contribute to a successful performance, we can then practise
  them. You could show videos of real poets performing their own poetry."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107825Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-6-verbs-used
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think all 6 verbs can be used interchangeably."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand the nuances of each verb by studying the word pairs
  carefully. For example, 'guzzle' is the verb that is mainly associated with liquids."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107831Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-understand-vocabulary-particularly
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to understand the vocabulary, particularly in
  stanza six."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Give explicit definitions for any unfamiliar language, using visuals to
  support the explanations, to help pupils' understanding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107850Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-spell-past-tense-verbs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children can spell past tense verbs how they sound, ending them with 't', 'd'
  or 'id'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explicitly discuss the examples of words where the ending sounds different
  and remind pupils that the spelling is still -ed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107856Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confuse-adjective-submerged-verb
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might confuse the adjective 'submerged' with the verb 'submerge'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Look at the word 'submerged' being used as an adjective and a simple past
  tense verb and discuss the difference. This is a good opportunity to revise word class."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108302Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-inference-guess
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think an inference is just a guess."@en ;
  curric:correction "Inferences are built on evidence, but they also make use of empathy."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108313Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-integrate-techniques-increasing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to integrate techniques for increasing pace into their
  writing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model during oral rehearsal and shared writing how we can do this. For
  instance, ask pupils to consider what characters might be thinking at different points to
  generate rhetorical questions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108324Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-vacant-used-describe-eyes-used
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Vacant can be used to describe eyes, but it can also be used in many other
  contexts."""@en ;
  curric:correction "Ensure children can use the word 'vacant' in all its different contexts."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108338Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-hard-identify-sounds-word-makes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """It can be hard to identify the sounds a word makes when looking at the
  spelling."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage children to listen to the word without looking at the spelling.
  Stretch the word and identify each sound in turn."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108366Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-use-co-ordinating
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that any use of a co-ordinating conjunction creates a
  compound sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that sentences like 'We ate cheese and ham.' cannot be a
  compound sentence because it does not contain two main clauses."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108385Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-misspell-ough-letter-string
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children misspell the 'ough' letter string, like in irregular past tense verbs
  'thought' or 'fought'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use the phrase 'oh you grumpy hippo' to remember the sequence of letters: o u
  g h."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108393Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-many-pupils-misspell-words-multiple
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Many pupils misspell words with multiple syllables when choosing to double or
  not double the consonant."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Start off with simple examples of the rule, using single syllable words with
  short vowels to secure the doubling first, before moving on to multisyllabic words. Focus
  on the most commonly used words first."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108413Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-mix-ible-able-spellings
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children mix up the -ible and -able spellings."@en ;
  curric:correction """Use the rules shown in the lesson: Is there is a recognisable root word
  without the ending? Is this a modern word? Is there a related word ending in -ation? These
  will all help to identify the -able spelling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108424Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-root-words-take-suffixes-ful
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "All root words can take both suffixes -ful and -less."@en ;
  curric:correction """Show a variety of words with suffixes -ful and -less. Choose ones familiar to
  the pupils and put into sentences to demonstrate the meaning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108451Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-poem-contains-examples-antiquated-archaic
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The poem contains some examples of antiquated / archaic language."@en ;
  curric:correction """A definition sheet could be provided to support pupils in understanding what
  happens in each verse."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108457Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-get-confused-northern-southern
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may get confused with the northern and southern polar regions."@en ;
  curric:correction """Reiterate that Antarctica is the southern polar region, the Arctic, the
  northern."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-identify-key-points
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to identify what the key points are to summarise."@en ;
  curric:correction """Refer to the model letter - it summarises the mystery in only a couple of
  sentences, but we are still very clear what has happened. We need to do the same here."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108496Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-diary-entry-use
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may believe a diary entry can only use the past tense."@en ;
  curric:correction """The diarist will also explain what they are doing and feeling in the present
  moment."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108538Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-understand-plot
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to understand the plot due to all the nonsense
  words."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The nonsense words do not have a definition. We can read them alongside the
  real words to understand the plot."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108550Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-identify-key
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to identify which key information should be
  included in the notes."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Re-read the final pages from the text to discuss how she is feeling at the
  end of the story. Model making notes and identifying which thoughts and feelings are the
  most important."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108555Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-develop-show
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it hard to develop 'show-not-tell' ideas."@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to act out different parts of the build up and to show the
  character's emotions through body language and facial expressions, while others describe
  what they are doing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108561Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-words-verb-object
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may believe any words after a verb are an object."@en ;
  curric:correction """An object must be a noun, noun phrase or pronoun that the verb is done to
  directly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108591Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-concept-temperate-speech
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle with the concept of a 'temperate speech'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Give an example of a temperate speech and an impassioned one to help pupils
  understand the qualities of a temperate speech."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108614Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-s-words-ending
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might use 's after words ending in 'ch', 'sh', 'ss' or 'x'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that apostrophes are used for contraction or possession and to
  make these nouns plural we need to add the correct suffix."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108622Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-first-children-find-writing-full
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """At first, children might find writing a full sentence in cursive overwhelming
  and forget the correct joins. This would result in the words being joined in a random
  manner."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Give them time to think about their sentence before starting. Model writing a
  sentence slowly and thinking out loud about which joins to use. This will encourage the
  children to do the same."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109235Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-include-narrative-elements
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that they can **only** include the narrative elements in
  their writing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """There are other things we can write about - for instance, thoughts the
  characters have - but the narrative elements are a helpful structure we can use to
  generate ideas. There is no need to limit pupils to just these categories."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109286Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-prediction-pure-guess
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may believe that a prediction is a pure guess."@en ;
  curric:correction """Our predictions are educated guesses based on what we have read already; when
  we make a prediction, we should explain how it connects to what we know about characters
  and plot."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109317Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-try-use-many-persuasive
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may try to use too many persuasive techniques all at once in the
  introduction."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that evidence and veiled threat are not appropriate to include in the
  introduction because they are too specific."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109351Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-range-sentence-structures
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not use a range of sentence structures and openers in their plans
  for writing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils know the full range of sentence structures (simple, compound
  and a variety of complex). Full coverage can be found in the 'Year 5 Grammar: Five
  sentence types' unit."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109366Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-include-facts-details-specific
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may include facts and details that are too specific for the opening
  paragraph."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Learning cycle 1 and the success criteria explicitly reinforce the importance
  of keeping information in the opening general."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109372Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-letters-silent-digraphs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think letters are silent in some digraphs for example, the 'h' in
  'ch'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss difference between silent letters and digraphs. In 'chaos' the letter
  'h' is silent but the other letters make a sound. Whereas, in the word 'clench' the 'h' is
  part of the 'ch' digraph where the two letters together make one sound."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109421Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-expect-direct-translations-spanish
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may expect direct translations for Spanish text."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that untranslated Spanish is the author and illustrators intention.
  Meaning can be inferred by exploring the surrounding panels for clues and context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109427Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-try-include-full-details
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may try to include the full details from their research notes in their
  oral rehearsal."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that the purpose of the first task is to practise giving a summary
  of the whole argument, not to give all the evidence that supports it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109433Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-need-support-understanding-arctic
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may need support in understanding how the Arctic and Antarctica
  differ."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use maps and images to show that the Arctic is circled by land while
  Antarctica is land surrounded by sea."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-understand-difference-homophone-homonym
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may not understand the difference between 'homophone' and
  'homonym'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Give specific examples of homophones (e.g. hair and hare) and homonyms (e.g.
  bark) and discuss the differences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109502Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-many-homophones-common-exception-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Many homophones are common exception words and pupils often confuse homophones
  within sentences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Give pupils the chance to choose the spellings they find most difficult and
  give them the strategies to help them practise."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109509Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-statistics-forms-evidence
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may believe that only statistics are forms of evidence."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explanations and facts, as well as expert views and references to official
  reports, can be used as forms of evidence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109520Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-accidentally-develop-rhetorical-questions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may accidentally develop rhetorical questions in present tense or
  first person when imagining what Arrietty is thinking. E.g. instead of \"Was she safe?\"
  they might write \"Am I safe?\""""@en ;
  curric:correction """Gather ideas from students about what Arriety might have been thinking and
  model turning these into third person and past tense. Provide examples in a shared bank
  for children to refer to while writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.109551Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-describe-setting-solely-based
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may describe the setting solely based on what can be seen."@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils to use more than just one of their senses to create a more
  detailed description. Provide additional support e.g. playing beach sounds, bringing in
  sand for children to feel."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110236Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-forget-lift-their-pencil
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may forget to lift their pencil after forming the capital letter."@en ;
  curric:correction """Model and emphasise to the children that the capital letters do not join
  (hold hands) with any other letters. They like to stand alone."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110351Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-connect-determiner
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to connect the determiner to the noun when
  adjectives are in between."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that adjectives describe nouns - can they spot the noun the
  adjectives describe to help them find the determiner?"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110362Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-task-pupils-find-challenging-predict
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """In Task A, pupils may find it challenging to predict what might happen after a
  poem has seemingly ended."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Adults could verbally model possibilities, linking back to the poem. These
  are largely based on the speaker leaving their hometown or becoming trapped there."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110374Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-understand-structure-appear
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children might struggle to understand how the structure can appear different
  visually."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Differentiate between structure and layout. Journalistic reports should
  follow the same structure but may be laid out differently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110398Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-encountered-many-wordless-silent
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not have encountered many wordless or silent texts."@en ;
  curric:correction """Have a range of wordless or silent texts accessible in the class or school
  library."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110404Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-sorting-ee-spellings-children-assume
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When sorting 'ee' spellings, children can assume all the identified graphemes
  are making the 'ee' sound."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Stretch the 'red herring' words with an identified grapheme that makes a
  different sound e.g. qu-i-e-t. The same spelling can represent a range of sounds."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110444Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-advocating-yourself-means
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that advocating for yourself means that you will always get
  what you want or that it is always appropriate to do so."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to remember that their perspective is not the only one; they
  may be in the wrong! This is why being polite and respectful is so important."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110458Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-use-writing-relative
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may want to use 'who' when writing relative clauses about tigers."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explicitly teach that the relative pronoun 'which' is used when writing about
  anything other than a person."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110464Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-writing-irregular
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might find it challenging when writing in the irregular past tense."@en ;
  curric:correction """Refer to the Year 3 unit 'Tense forms: simple, progressive and perfect' for
  opportunities for further discrete grammar teaching around tense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110478Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-remembering-different-punctuation
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle with remembering the different punctuation rules in speech
  first and speech second sentences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide a visual scaffold of the speech first and speech second punctuation
  rules. Encourage pupils to use this when writing direct speech."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110484Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-misconceptions-around-iron-mans
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may have misconceptions around the Iron Man's character arc and think
  that this focuses on how he changes as a character."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that the main focus of the Iron Man's character arc is not how he
  changes, but how the way in which he is perceived by others changes. You can also explore
  the concept that acceptance allows people to show the best of themselves."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110492Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-develop-simple-questions-answer
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may develop simple questions where the answer can be retrieved from
  the text rather than involving inference to uncover."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model the difference between a retrieval and an inference question. E.g. For
  page 13, a retrieval question could be 'How did the King speak to Alina?' whereas an
  inference question could be 'What did the King think about Alina's declaration?'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110528Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-suffix-spelt-double
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think the suffix is spelt with a double 'l' like the word
  'full'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explicitly point out the difference between the spelling of 'full' and the
  suffix 'ful'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110534Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-spell-words-suffix-en
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may spell words with the suffix -en as they sound with 'in'
  or 'n'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explicitly draw comparisons to how words encountered are spelt and how they
  sound, particularly when there are differences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110550Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-splattered-verb-instead
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might use 'splattered' as a verb instead of an adjective. For example,
  'The raindrops splattered onto her forehead' instead of 'She wiped the splattered drops of
  rain off her forehead'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Allow pupils to also use the word as a verb; just make sure they understand
  that this is a different word class. Look at sentences where it is used as a verb and an
  adjective and ask pupils to identify the word class."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110561Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-text-one-theme
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think that a text only has one theme or main idea."@en ;
  curric:correction """Texts often contain multiple layers of meaning and can address various themes
  simultaneously. They will be personal to each reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111076Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-diminutive-minuscule-used-interchangeably
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Diminutive and minuscule can often be used interchangeably, but not
  always."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use the word pairs to help pupils see and hear the words in nuanced contexts.
  i.e. 'minuscule amount' works but not 'diminutive amount'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111082Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-feel-simply-read-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may feel they can simply read out their written journalistic
  report."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A radio broadcast will likely be shorter, more succinct and more informal
  than a written journalistic report. We also have the chance to include interviews directly
  with the people involved."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111088Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-friendship-sam-davey-wholly-positive
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The friendship between Sam and Davey is wholly positive or negative."@en ;
  curric:correction """The relationship between both boys is complex. You may wish to explore the
  theme of bullying in a separate lesson (e.g. PSHE) to acknowledge the traits that Sam
  exhibits and what could be done to resolve or address the behaviour."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111096Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-floellas-experiences-negative
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that Floella's experiences were only negative when arriving
  in England."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Experiences that Floella had in both countries were both positive and
  negative. Listing and discussing these either with talk partners, in small groups or as a
  whole class can be beneficial to build up an overall picture of Floella's life."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111122Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-add-er-est
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that you can add -er or -est to any adjective and use it to
  make comparisons."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make pupils aware that we cannot always add the suffix -er or -est to
  compare. For example, good - better - best or bad - worse - worst."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111166Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-select-facts
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to select which facts to connect using cohesive
  devices."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Give pupils plenty of time to orally rehearse grouping information together
  using different cohesive devices."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111172Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-unsure-definitions-synonyms-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may be unsure of some of the definitions and synonyms of words
  associated with the heat."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It would be beneficial to have completed the Y4 Mrs Wordsmith vocabulary unit
  on 'Weather: wind and hot words' ahead of this lesson, to support children with generating
  vocabulary."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111183Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-distinction-discussion-philosophical
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find the distinction between discussion and philosophical questions
  challenging."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage them to imagine asking the question to their parent or headteacher
  - if the person could answer without having read 'Romeo and Juliet', then it's a
  philosophical question. Model this process."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111197Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-distinguish-narrative
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to distinguish between the narrative
  elements."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The elements often overlap - we use action to show emotion, for instance.
  Encourage a relaxed approach to this; the main aim is to ensure that we have covered a
  wide range of content in our plans."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111219Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-understanding-difference-general
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find understanding the difference between 'general' and 'specific'
  facts challenging."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When reading aloud the model introduction, highlight the general facts. When
  reading sections one and two, highlight the specific facts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111236Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-longer-sentences-preferable
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that longer sentences are always preferable to
  short ones."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that text cohesion is best served by variety and that short
  sentences have a significant role in writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111260Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-maori-culture-confined-historical-practices
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Maori culture is confined to historical practices and traditions only. It is
  not present in contemporary society."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Maori culture continues to adapt and thrive in contemporary society. Maori
  people are active in politics, arts, business and academia, contributing to the broader
  New Zealand society and global community."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111278Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-see-word-relationships-referring
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may see the word 'relationships' as referring to romantic
  relationships."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explore the different layers of relationships we all have. Encourage pupils
  to share the relationships they have, including any changes, if they feel comfortable to
  do so."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111613Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-words-ambitious-vocabulary
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that all words are ambitious vocabulary."@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that there can be multiple options when selecting vocabulary and
  they need to carefully choose the most precise words in their writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111680Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-word-pairs-overwhelming
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might find the word pairs for 'overwhelming' difficult, such as
  'overwhelming majority' and 'overwhelming evidence'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model using all the different word pairs and discuss the meanings in
  context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111723Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confuse-first-person-writing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may confuse this first person writing with internal monologue and focus
  only on Addie's thoughts."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Here, we haven't used the term 'internal monologue' because we are describing
  events and observations from Addie's perspective and not just thoughts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111734Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-restrict-their-questioning-task
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may restrict their questioning in Task B solely to what is explained in
  the text."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage readers to interrogate the illustrations, as well as reflect on
  their own personal responses, to further develop questioning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111739Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-word-contain-hard
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may think that a word can only contain a hard c or a soft c."@en ;
  curric:correction """Look at some words that contain a soft c and a hard c, such as bicycle or
  access. Use sound buttoning to help identify the phoneme grapheme correspondences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111745Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-opinions-need-justified-debate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Opinions do not need to be justified in a debate."@en ;
  curric:correction "Opinions need to be justified to convince the audience."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111750Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-write-their-speech
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils often want to write their speech down word for word."@en ;
  curric:correction """There often isn't time to write a speech word for word when preparing for a
  debate. Therefore, notes should be used instead."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111758Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-fully-understand-context-song
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not fully understand the context in which the song was written."@en ;
  curric:correction """It would be useful to complete/recap the unit 'Coming to England: reading'
  prior to starting this unit, to further contextualise the experience from a biographical
  perspective."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111797Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-visualise-two
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to visualise the two settings being described
  by the poets."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Additional photographs could be provided to develop understanding of the two
  locations."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111811Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-understand-abstract-imagery
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not understand abstract imagery."@en ;
  curric:correction """It may be useful to discuss abstract nouns before the session. Abstract
  imagery can be defined as descriptions that evoke ideas, emotions or concepts rather than
  concrete, physical objects."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111822Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-misspell-words-prefixes-because
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils misspell the words with prefixes because they cannot spell the root
  word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Draw attention to tricky elements of the root words as necessary, e.g. the
  'ea' in healthy - unhealthy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111833Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-know-difference-different-types
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not know the difference between the different types of fronted
  adverbial."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that an ‘and’ formal fronted adverbial builds on a point, a
  ‘but’ formal fronted adverbial introduces a contrasting idea to the previous sentence and
  a fronted adverbial of cause tells the reader the cause and effect of something."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111845Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-start-scratch-their-notes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may 'start from scratch' with their notes in this lesson."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils have already generated ideas for descriptive and emotive details ready
  to use in this lesson and they should feed these details and ideas into their plans today."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.111873Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-develop-their-own
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may struggle to develop their own ideas for 'show and tell' to convey
  Scrooge's emotions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ask the children to recall a time when they have felt the emotions Scrooge
  does (e.g. nervousness or fear) and ask them what kind of physical sensations they
  experience during these moments. Examples to offer might be 'clammy hands' or 'tight
  chest'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112679Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-place-character-traits-inside
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may place character traits both on the inside and outside of the
  character outline."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that inner emotions and feelings remain inside, attributes
  that other characters can see go on the outside."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112702Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-use-words-provided
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may believe they can only use the words provided in the tasks."@en ;
  curric:correction """You may wish to list the words provided on a whiteboard during the lesson,
  but then encourage children to apply their own ideas in the tasks or to use a thesaurus to
  explore deeper."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112711Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-subject-specific-vocabulary-defined-explained
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """All subject-specific vocabulary will be defined, explained or supported by
  visual aids or captions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils may have to use other reading strategies to build understanding. These
  can be displayed in a classroom or modelled by an adult."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112720Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-apply-common-plural-rules
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will apply common plural rules to singular nouns that have irregular
  plural patterns."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use spelling strategies such as 'big letters' or 'colour blocks' to help pick
  out the tricky elements of irregular plural spellings and embed them in the memory."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112727Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-easily-confuse-vowels-ant
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may easily confuse the vowels in -ant and -ent spellings."@en ;
  curric:correction """Say the word clearly how it is spelt in order to emphasise the vowel
  spellings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112733Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confuse-spellings-homophones-eight
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils confuse the spellings of homophones: eight and ate, weight and
  wait."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When you review the spellings of these words, ensure to identify that they
  are homophones and suggest ways to remember which is which."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112739Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-understand-sequence-events
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to understand the sequence of events in the story or
  certain vocabulary in the text."""@en ;
  curric:correction """As you read aloud, you can provide brief interjections to show the meaning of
  challenging vocabulary. You can also talk as a reader, saying what you are **realising**
  about the plot as an aside as you read, e.g., 'Ah, he must have ...'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112756Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-include-relative-clauses-include
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils include relative clauses that include information that is not relevant
  to the main clause."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Task A and the quizzes specifically address the issue of relevance when
  selecting a relative clause."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112762Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-ck-representing-c
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may use 'ck' to representing the 'c' phoneme at the end of the word
  after a short vowel, like 'stick' and 'trick'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that in most words where the 'c' is at the end, it is represented as
  'ck'. As this is a suffix, it doesn't follow usual rules. If we can spot a root word, and
  know that the new word is an adjective it will most likely be spelt 'ic'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112780Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-include-specific-facts
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils want to include specific facts in the introduction."@en ;
  curric:correction """Use a 'general' and 'specific' visual during the lesson and the tasks to
  support pupils' understanding of the difference between the two."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113478Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-nouns-person-place
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think that all nouns are a person, place or thing that you can
  touch."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Show a range of different nouns, including common and abstract nouns. Show
  that they can be described with an adjective."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114224Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-difficult-know-words-hyphenated
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """It can be difficult to know when words should be hyphenated and when they
  should not."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Notice patterns such as vowel sounds and encourage the use of dictionaries to
  check words pupils are unsure of."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114405Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-understand-early
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it hard to understand the Early Modern English."@en ;
  curric:correction """There are numerous modern English 'translations' available online; you may
  wish to give some pupils access to these in addition to the scaffolding in the lesson. The
  priority is for pupils to engage with Juliet's emotions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114441Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-expect-see-features-other
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may expect to see features from other non-fiction texts they
  have read."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Non-fiction texts can vary greatly, both in terms of layout as well
  as form."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114449Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-get-confused-progressive-perfect
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may get confused between progressive and perfect tenses."@en ;
  curric:correction """Focus on the auxiliary verbs and main verb forms - 'to be' vs 'to have' and
  -ing forms vs past tense forms."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114461Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-confuse-pairs-words-compound
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children might confuse pairs of words with compound words. e.g. bus stop."@en ;
  curric:correction """Give examples of both and model mistakes e.g. write butterfly as 'butter fly'
  or bus stop as 'busstop' and discuss."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114477Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-decide-insert
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it hard to decide where to insert parenthesis into a
  sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The parenthesis will usually follow the noun or noun phrase it adds extra
  information about."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114493Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-remind-pupils-use-root-word
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Remind pupils to use the root word to help them spell the new word created by
  adding the suffix."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils have a good understanding of the vocabulary. If they do not
  know the root word, they will find it harder to spell. Use images."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114544Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-mix-linguistic-features-persuasive
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may mix up linguistic features with persuasive techniques."@en ;
  curric:correction """Linguistic features and persuasive techniques are addressed in isolation
  through the two distinct learning cycles. Build in more time for checking pupils'
  understanding if their knowledge is still not secure at the end of each."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114555Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-their-oral-rehearsal
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that their oral rehearsal has to be perfect or excessively
  detailed."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The oral rehearsal is a first attempt; it may not be perfect. It reduces the
  cognitive load when writing, allowing extra details to be added more easily."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114586Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-six-words-adjectives
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think all six words are adjectives."@en ;
  curric:correction "Keep reminding pupils that 'havoc' and 'commotion' are both nouns."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114786Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-text-autobiographical-features
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think the text has autobiographical features due to its tone and
  form."""@en ;
  curric:correction """'Walter Tull's Scrapbook' is a biography. It is a non-fiction text with
  factual evidence. It is presented as a fictionalised scrapbook."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114793Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-reporting-clause-direct
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that both the reporting clause and the direct speech begin
  with a capital letter."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that when the speech comes first, the reporting clause has no
  capital."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114799Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-revert-back-cursive-comparing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Sometimes children can revert back to cursive when comparing print and block
  capitals."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind the children that when writing in print, you lift your pencil after
  forming each letter. Emphasise this in your modelling to remind the children."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114804Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-formal-tone-biography
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find the formal tone of a biography challenging."@en ;
  curric:correction """You may wish to provide additional time for children to read a range of
  biographical writing to 'tune in' to the text type."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114837Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-try-include-information-introduction
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may try to include information in the introduction that is too
  specific."""@en ;
  curric:correction """'General information' is explicitly referred to throughout both learning
  cycles."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114890Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-include-steps-process-take
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might include steps of the process that take place outside of
  the hive."""@en ;
  curric:correction """This section explains the final three steps of the honey-making process that
  take place inside the hive."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114895Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-langauge-poem-hard
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find some of the langauge in the poem hard to understand."@en ;
  curric:correction """Talk through any new or unfamiliar language with pupils. Explain that this is
  not langauge we would use with each other, but is included in the poem for comic effect."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114949Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-free-verse-poems
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that free verse poems have no structure to them."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils read and re-read the poem many times. Each time they do
  so, they will hear more of the natural rhythms, beats and flow within it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114962Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-identifying-individual-aspects
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might find identifying individual aspects of the personal response
  challenging."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils who may need greater scaffolding to discuss similar quotes
  or moments to the examples given."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114974Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-speeches-need-specific
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may think that speeches do not need to have a specific purpose."@en ;
  curric:correction """A speaker must consider their purpose for speaking before they write their
  speech so they know what impact they wish to have on the audience"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114993Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-conclusion-review-detail
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may think that the conclusion should review every detail of the
  digestive process."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It is important not to repeat the explanation, but to highlight the key parts
  by reviewing the most important subject-specific vocabulary."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114999Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-cover-events-story
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may forget to cover the 'events' of the story while focusing on
  descriptive and emotive details."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that you emphasise the need to move the action forwards and that you
  model this in oral rehearsal."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115126Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-captions-shouldnt-reiterate-whats-obvious
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Captions shouldn't just reiterate what's obvious in the visual."@en ;
  curric:correction """Captions should complement diagrams by explaining the visual, highlighting
  key points and giving any additional facts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115190Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-identify-key
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to identify which key information should be
  included in the plan."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Offer opportunities for identifying appropriate note examples and identifying
  which events, thoughts and feelings are most important. Model taking notes and just
  capturing the most important information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115230Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-imagine-scene
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it hard to imagine the scene without having seen anything like
  it before."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Whilst it might be difficult to imagine it perfectly, we can use our
  imagination to create ideas that paint a vivid picture."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115236Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-shakespeares-plays-difficult-understand-inaccessible
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Shakespeare's plays are too difficult to understand or inaccessible due to the
  language used."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Many of Shakespeare's themes, emotions and characters resonate universally
  across time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115607Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-developing-appropriate-rhetorical
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may struggle with developing an appropriate rhetorical question and
  writing it in the correct tense. E.g. 'Will she make it?'"""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model appropriate examples in the past tense and highlight the ways in which
  it sounds like Lila is asking the question herself (despite the use of the 'she' pronoun).
  E.g. She decided to brave the heat. After all, wasn't she used to fire anyway?"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115627Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-turning-points-narrative
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that turning points in a narrative only have negative
  consequences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Note other examples of turning points in recently read narratives that have a
  range of positive and negative consequences. Pupils may wish to share examples from their
  own texts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115860Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-remember-features
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to remember features found in non-fiction
  texts."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Display/print out common non-fiction text features, alongside layout
  features, to support pupils when comparing and contrasting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115867Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-es-suffix-pronounced
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that the -es suffix is always pronounced as 'is'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Model saying words like 'dominoes' (domino-is) and 'wishes' (wishs)
  incorrectly. Talk about making meaning when we read and spell."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116114Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-favourite-character-someone
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that a favourite character should always be someone who
  embodies positive character traits."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that favourite characters can be characters involved in key moments
  in the text; characters who change the most in the story; or, characters who remind
  readers of someone they know."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116121Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-many-readers-interpret-poem-literally
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Many readers might interpret the poem literally."@en ;
  curric:correction """The listeners are non-human objects, described as phantoms by Walter de la
  Mare."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116145Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-choose-appropriate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to choose appropriate cohesive devices to connect
  ideas."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that often, we can choose from a wide range of cohesive devices
  that serve the same purpose; it is simply the writer's choice. Allow plenty of time for
  oral rehearsal before writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116151Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-word-excruciating-ineffectively
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might use the word 'excruciating' ineffectively - for something that is
  mildly painful."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss what you would and would not describe as 'excruciating'. For example,
  if I had a small paper cut, would that be excruciating?"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116156Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-use-apostrophe-s-hear
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children often use an apostrophe s, when they hear an 's' at the end of the
  word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind children of the rules for using apostrophes. Only use an apostrophe if
  you can name and recognise the rule - for omission or possession."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116162Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-editing-requires-them
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that editing requires them to rewrite the entire piece of
  writing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make explicit references to how to be selective with which elements of the
  writing to edit, for example vocabulary or sentence structure."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116167Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-understand-characters
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it difficult to understand the characters' emotions."@en ;
  curric:correction """Tell pupils that exploring what the characters say and how they act helps to
  infer what they are feeling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116173Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-identify-add-parenthesis
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to identify where to add parenthesis in a sentence."@en ;
  curric:correction """It is easiest to add parenthesis after nouns or verbs - encourage children to
  identify these if needed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116188Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-summarise-main-points
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to summarise the main points of their essay into their
  speech."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to add to their notes as they orally rehearse their speech,
  jotting down additional thoughts that come to them as they practise."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116239Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-identify-different
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to identify different poetic techniques or
  examples of figurative language."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils could text mark a physical copy of the poem with their thoughts and
  ideas. Highlighters could be used to mark rhetorical questions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116265Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-quote-page-3-refers-violence
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The quote on page 3 refers to violence, war and persecution. Pupils may be
  unsure about some/all of these terms."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Depending on the context of the class, appropriate definitions can be
  provided to better contextualise the introduction to the text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116300Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-focus-finding-rhyming-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The focus should be on finding rhyming words."@en ;
  curric:correction """Poets should aim for natural and purposeful rhymes that complement the poem's
  intent rather than forcing words to fit a specific pattern."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116314Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-one-right-way
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may think that there is one right way to deliver a presentation of a
  persuasive advert."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss how the target audience impacts the delivery. E.g. difference in
  delivering to investors (Dragon's Den style) or potential consumers"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116323Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-lift-their-pencils-part
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children will sometimes lift their pencils part way through the letter
  string."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model to the children that they should look at the word first and plan for
  when they will be lifting their pencil: usually at the end of the word or after a break
  letter. Model writing the word, emphasising the flow as the letters connect."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116329Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-much-knowledge-understanding-victorian
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not have much knowledge or understanding of the Victorian era."@en ;
  curric:correction """Prior to this lesson, provide an opportunity for pupils to conduct research
  into the Victorian era and what life was like for people at that time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116423Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-look-images-characters-themselves
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may only look at images of the characters themselves when trying to
  analyse them."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Anthony Browne leaves clues about characters throughout his illustrations,
  including in the settings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116432Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-expected-tell-detailed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe they are expected to tell a detailed story using various
  sentence types at this stage."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The oral storytelling here is the basis on which the more detailed, varied
  writing will be built - pupils should try to make their storytelling 'interesting', but it
  doesn't need to use all the grammatical structures they know at this point."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116799Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-heavy-handed-used
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think 'heavy-handed' can only be used in the physical sense."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that the word 'heavy-handed' can be used if someone
  is insensitive. For example, a heavy-handed remark."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116810Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-reading-restricted-book
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think reading is restricted to a book."@en ;
  curric:correction """By completing a reading treasure hunt, pupils can explore reading in a range
  of forms."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116815Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-unsure-use-different-types
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may be unsure of how to use different types of complex sentences."@en ;
  curric:correction """Learning cycle one models different complex sentence types that can be used
  in the main body of pupils' letters."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116827Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-refer-tubmans-activism-later
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may refer to Tubman's activism and later life experiences in this
  section."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explicit re-exposure to the information learned about Tubman's early life
  occurs in Learning Cycle 1 to keep pupils focused on this aspect of her life."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116838Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-diary-written-entirely
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that a diary is written entirely in the past tense."@en ;
  curric:correction """Examples of present and future tense are referred to and modelled in the
  examples given. Emphasise repeatedly to pupils that a range of tenses will be used in a
  diary."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116875Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-clear-understanding-sentence-types
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not have a clear understanding of sentence types."@en ;
  curric:correction """This is explicitly taught in Learning Cycle 1 and pupils are tasked with
  finding each type of complex sentence in a model opening."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116881Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-judging-debate-needs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children might think that judging a debate needs to be done by adults."@en ;
  curric:correction """Children can most definitely judge a debate themselves once they know what
  they're looking for."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116910Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-double-consonant-short
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils forget to double the consonant after a short vowel, such as fun -
  funny."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make links to other suffixes used, such as -ed or -ing, when the consonant is
  also doubled."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116928Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-choose-appropriate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to choose appropriate synonyms for the precise
  context in LC2."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Allow children to work in pairs or small groups to generate ideas. Mind map
  some more synonyms together as a class before they complete the task."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116940Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-easier-perform-play
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think it is **always** easier to perform a play with a small number
  of characters."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The difficulty of a play is not just down to the number of characters in it.
  Often, the most difficult plays are the ones with the most troubling or complicated themes
  - central messages that the playwright wants the audience to think deeply about."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116945Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-see-adverbs-saying
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to see adverbs as doing more than saying 'how' verbs are
  done."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Adverbs modify verbs by saying when, where, how or to what extent they are
  done - encourage pupils to look for words that modify the verb."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116959Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-task-pupils-need-support-identifying
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """In Task A, pupils might need support in identifying what each still from the
  animation is showing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Look at each image and prompt pupils with questions such as 'Who is this
  character?'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116971Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confused-crossover-fronted-adverbial
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might be confused by the crossover between a fronted adverbial of
  manner or time and a non-finite or adverbial clause, for example, 'Hunching over,...' or
  'As soon as they had spoken, ...'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Whenever a fronted adverbial of manner is also an adverbial or non-finite
  clause, make this explicit. For example, in slide 19, you could say 'Leaning towards her
  sisters,' is a fronted adverbial of manner, but it is also a non-finite clause."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116982Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-recognise-common-features-character
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might recognise common features or character types from other fairy
  tales leading them to think that the characters must conform to a stereotype."""@en ;
  curric:correction """'Blackberry Blue' uses a range of fairy tales for inspiration. Use the text
  to discuss how characters do not always conform to stereotypes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117209Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-spend-long-drawing-task
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might spend too long drawing in Task A, which is not the point of the
  task."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You could set a one-minute timer for pupils to draw. You could also model
  sketching a dagger yourself so that they see that it does not need to be perfect."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117215Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-story-pebble-found
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children might think that the story is only about a pebble being found and its
  story."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The author conveys the deeper meaning that everything that exists has a story
  to tell and builds our understanding of the world."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117238Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-possible-answers-question-perfect-landing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """There are a few possible answers to the question about the \"perfect\" landing
  (in the 'Landing on Mars' cycle)."""@en ;
  curric:correction """If pupils can justify how the landing went well, with evidence from their
  reading of the text, it is likely an appropriate justification."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117749Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-text-curation-focus-solely-personal
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Text curation might focus solely on personal preference."@en ;
  curric:correction """Identify a range of ways that pupils might curate, linking especially to any
  theme weeks or real-world events."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117756Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-furious-livid-raging-similar-meanings
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """As 'furious', 'livid' and 'raging' have similar meanings and word pairs,
  pupils answers may vary in Task C."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that there is more than one option that can work in the
  three sentences that contain these words. The word maps from previous tasks might help
  them to find the best answers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117776Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-purpose-text-map
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that the purpose of the text map is to learn a particular
  text word-for-word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Although text maps can be used in this way, in this case we are trying to
  learn the series of events; pupils should re-tell the events using simple language,
  pointing to the relevant picture as they do so."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118146Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-graphic-novels-comics-share-many
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Graphic novels and comics share many similar features. Pupils might use the
  term interchangeably."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Graphic novels have a clear beginning, middle and end, unlike comics which
  are usually released weekly in shorter comic strips."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118166Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-edits-make-better
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils sometimes think the more edits they make the better."@en ;
  curric:correction """Praise pupils not on the amount they have edited, but on how well they are
  working as a team to find things that need correcting or improving."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118171Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-feel-tempted-write-complete
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may feel tempted to write in complete sentences in their plan."@en ;
  curric:correction """Model and encourage note-taking; this gives pupils more flexibility when they
  come to write and it allows them to jot down more ideas - some of which they can reject
  later."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118177Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-understand-distinction
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to understand the distinction between hyperbole
  and metaphors."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that hyperbole always uses exaggeration and doesn't need to be
  metaphorical. E.g. 'That is the best news I have ever heard.' Metaphors can involve
  exaggeration but do not need to. E.g. 'That is music to my ears.'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118196Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-words-used-word
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that these words can only be used with word pairs to do with
  a fight or battle."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model how to use some of the different word pairs e.g. 'conquer fears/
  feelings'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118207Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-start-write-longer-paragraphs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """As children start to write longer paragraphs in cursive handwriting their
  hands can get sore which can lead to them making mistakes."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model to the children that it is good practice to take a break when writing
  to stretch your hand if it is becoming sore."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118224Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-suggest-ideas-main-non
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may suggest ideas for main or non-finite clauses that cannot be done
  simultaneously."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to imagine the two actions and consider whether they can be
  done at the same time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118231Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-feel-unprepared-debate-tasks
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may feel unprepared for the debate as the tasks leading up to Task C
  are verbal discussions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Plan an additional lesson where pupils prepare their speech using the PEPS
  structure and give them time to rehearse and write down their ideas. Then, conduct the
  debate in a separate lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118243Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-identify-points-used
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to identify the points being used to justify an opinion in
  a speech."""@en ;
  curric:correction """At the start of LC1, watch the speech together and pause to identify the
  following: 1. the main opinion or argument 2. the points being used to justify. Focus on
  how information is used to persuade."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118276Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-word-pairs-sparse
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might find the word pairs for 'sparse' difficult, such as 'sparse
  evidence' and 'sparse vegetation'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model using all the different word pairs and discuss the meanings in
  context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118301Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-unsure-noun-noun-phrase
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may be unsure which noun or noun phrase the relative clause should be
  placed after."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The relative clause is placed after whichever noun or noun phrase it provides
  extra, relevant information about."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118318Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-verbs-show
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think verbs can only show 'doing'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Verbs can show 'being' and 'having' as well as 'doing'. These are sometimes
  'hidden' in contractions (I'm, she's, they've, we've)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118332Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-recognise-adverbial-clause-one
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils do not recognise that an adverbial clause is one type of subordinate
  clause."""@en ;
  curric:correction """\"Subordinate clause\" is an umbrella term. Any subordinate clause is a group
  of words that contains a verb and does not make complete sense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118349Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-presume-past-participle-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might presume that the past participle is always the same as the simple
  past tense."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to hear what sounds correct, for example, 'it has flown
  off', 'it has flew off'. This should be 'it has flown off'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118355Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-single-verb-sentence
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that every single verb in a sentence always carries the same
  tense."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Avoid teaching that all verbs in a sentence always carry the same tense;
  maintaining tense does not always require this."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118360Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-verbs-ending-y
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils can think that all verbs ending in 'y' follow the rule remove the 'y'
  and add -ied."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Look at examples that add -ed and remove the 'y' and add -ied. Focus on the
  sound the 'y' is making and see if it is part of a digraph."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118366Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-two-wind-words-nouns-one
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Two of the 'wind' words are nouns and one is an adjective. Pupils might not
  know the difference."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss what word class the word pairs are and how this differs if the main
  word is an adjective or a noun."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118386Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-words-get-longer-children-rush
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """As the words get longer, children can rush, causing the letter spacing to
  become uneven and the writing illegible."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind and model to the children that the flow and movement of the pencil is
  the same at the end of the word as it is at the beginning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118597Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-think-themes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it challenging to think of themes."@en ;
  curric:correction """During Task B, discuss common themes and model thinking out loud some
  suggestions (e.g. collaboration, determination)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118617Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-authors-write-books-anyone-read
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Authors write books for anyone to read."@en ;
  curric:correction "Authors design and write their texts in order to reach certain audiences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118624Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-task-pupils-find-example-tension
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """During Task A, pupils may not find an example of each of the tension-building
  techniques."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Different techniques may be used on each page. You could share examples for
  the three double-page spreads after the task."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118663Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-remember-double-letters-start
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may not remember double letters at the start of some words with
  prefixes, such as illogical or dissatisfied."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Help the children to see that if they recognise the prefix and the base word,
  they can work out the spelling of the new word, as prefixes do not change the spelling of
  the root word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118674Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-back-their-points-arguments
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not back up their points or arguments using evidence."@en ;
  curric:correction """Learning cycle one reiterates the importance of writing credibility and how
  using evidence can enhance the credibility of the argument."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118709Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-grapple-morphology
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children might find it difficult to grapple with morphology that supports
  forming a headline."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide examples of catchy headlines and model using words in different ways
  e.g. bliss, blissful, blissfully."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118747Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-one-type-sentence
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may over-use one type of sentence, leading to poor text cohesion."@en ;
  curric:correction """The range of sentence types are reviewed in learning cycle one with relative
  and non-finite complex sentences reviewed in detail. Encourage pupils to vary the
  placement of the subordinate clause in their complex sentences to enhance text cohesion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118769Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-determiners-come-directly
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that determiners always come directly in front of a
  noun."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Adjectives may be placed between the determiner and the noun to provide
  description."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118775Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-coming-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging coming up with their own ideas for
  'personification'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You may wish to play a game using objects in the room and describing what
  they are doing using personification. E.g. the teacher's desk stood proudly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118843Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-non-finite-clauses
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that non-finite clauses always come at the start of
  sentences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that non-finite clauses can vary their position in a sentence
  and model a non-finite clause in both positions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118863Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confuse-progressive-perfect-tenses
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may confuse the progressive and perfect tenses as both use an auxiliary
  verb."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that the progressive uses 'being' auxiliary verbs and the perfect
  uses 'having' auxiliary verbs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118877Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-one-correct-answer
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that there is one correct answer in relation to the question
  posed in Task A."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that texts can offer us philosophical questions, which ask readers to
  reflect on their own opinions. Links could be made to the author's note and afterword to
  deepen understanding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118888Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-rhyming-words-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may think rhyming words have to have the same spelling of the
  repeated sounds."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that rhyme is repeated sounds, not spelling. Highlight the rhyming
  sections of the rhyming words within the poems. Look at the different spellings. Generate
  further rhyming words and identify the same or different spelling patterns."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118921Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-find-synonyms
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it challenging to find synonyms and antonyms of words."@en ;
  curric:correction """It would be useful to pre-teach or practise a word explosion before
  commencing the lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118932Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-flexibility-punctuation-bullet
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle with the flexibility of punctuation for bullet points -
  often, it is optional."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise the importance of consistency - choosing a method and sticking to
  it. Only complete sentences require capitals and full stops."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118944Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-form-predictions-without-basing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may form predictions without basing their ideas on evidence within the
  text."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model making predictions based on information provided in the text or wider
  reading and research."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118949Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-list-adaptations-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may want to list adaptations in their plan without explaining how they
  benefit survival."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make explicit reference to functions of adaptations throughout the planning
  stage and set aside space on plans to refer to each function."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118969Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-overgeneralise-applying-regular-ed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some pupils may overgeneralise applying regular -ed rules to irregular verbs
  such as 'buy' -'buyed'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Expose pupils to irregular past tense verbs in reading activities, encourage
  them to use mnemonics and hunt for words in sentences together."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118974Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-drab-bleak-used
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think that 'drab' and 'bleak' can be used interchangeably."@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to use the word pairs to help them use the words effectively
  in the right contexts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118988Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-try-include-detail-summarising
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may try to include every detail when summarising the story."@en ;
  curric:correction """Model how to summarise effectively, choosing only the key pieces of
  information from the plot. You may add some illustrations from the text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119366Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-consider-text-telling-omars
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may consider the text as telling Omar's story in one continuous
  narrative."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The graphic novel has two significant jumps in time, page 114 (two years
  later) and page 221 (four years later). The afterword and author's note both describe what
  happened to Omar after arriving in the United States."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119372Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-bad-weather-evidence
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that 'bad' weather is evidence against any drastic change
  in the climate."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Temperatures are rising, which leads to more extreme weather generally - not
  just to more dry and hot weather."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119383Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-incorrectly-introduce-new-information
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may incorrectly introduce new information in the conclusion."@en ;
  curric:correction """Specific reference to keeping information in the conclusion general and
  teacher guidance on appropriate information to include is given in learning cycle one."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119388Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-accidentally-include-much-detail
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may accidentally include too much detail of the recount in the
  opening."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Whilst some recount is important, reinforce to pupils that they must write
  from the personal viewpoint of the character, using feelings and thoughts to convey their
  character."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119396Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-change-order-devices
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may want to change the order of the devices in the poem."@en ;
  curric:correction """Joseph Coelho originally intends people to follow the set structure, but then
  you can allow pupils to play around with the structure of their poem and move things if
  they want to."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119402Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-clapping-beat-poem
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find clapping the beat of the poem challenging."@en ;
  curric:correction """A metronome could be used to support the reading. This would work best in 4/4
  - four beats per measure."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119467Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-add-word-co-ordinating
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils add a word after the co-ordinating conjunction not a main clause."@en ;
  curric:correction """A co-ordinating conjunction in a compound sentence must join two complete
  main clauses. Any main clause must make complete sense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119479Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-adults-make-speeches
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may think that only adults make speeches."@en ;
  curric:correction """It is very important for children to know how to share their opinions and
  feelings and making a speech is a good way to do this."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119485Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-use-shows-perfect
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may believe that any use of 'have' shows the perfect tense."@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind children that 'have' can be used as a main verb as well as an
  auxiliary verb. For example, 'I have three pets' = main verb."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119490Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-notice-start-discussing-climate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may notice that you could start off by discussing climate change,
  instead of deforestation, in this essay."""@en ;
  curric:correction """This is correct - we could come at it from either angle; however, since we
  are emphasising the Amazon rainforest in particular, it makes sense to start by referring
  to deforestation first."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119520Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-notes-plan-written-order
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Notes in a plan can be written in any order."@en ;
  curric:correction """The key moments in the opening are written in chronological order. Notes in
  the plan should be concise and follow this chronological order."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119573Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-generate-adjectives
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might find it hard to generate adjectives and description about a
  character they do not have a clear illustration of."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You could ask the children to draw their version of the main character,
  Tristan, at the start of this lesson. They will then find it easier to generate the
  descriptive vocabulary."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119579Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-know-lifestyle-means
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not know what 'lifestyle' means."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that 'lifestyle' encompasses all the ways that humans choose to live,
  from what they choose to include in their diet to how much exercise and sleep they get."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119674Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-based-lyrics-music-pupils-solely
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Based on the lyrics and music, pupils may have a solely optimistic view of the
  UK."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Reiterate that many people from the Caribbean experienced challenges and
  barriers, including discrimination."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119691Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-recognise-rhyming-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not recognise all of the rhyming words."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that some words may not rhyme based on the accent of the
  person reading them. Likewise, other words may rhyme when read in Dickinson's native
  American accent."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119697Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-questions-misconceptions-around-illusion
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may have questions or misconceptions around the 'illusion' element of
  the special ingredient and how Lila was still successful in completing her quest."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Do not delve too deeply into the 'illusion' element as it is not key for the
  writing of the climax. We can summarise that the true quest was to show no fear in facing
  fire in order to pursue her dreams which Lila demonstrated."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119726Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-piece-first-person
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that any piece of first person writing is internal
  monologue."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Internal monologue is first person writing that focuses on the inner thoughts
  of the person."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119948Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-use-wrong-vowel-letter
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may use the wrong vowel letter when spelling words with unstressed
  vowels."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Stretching the word and saying it slowly, how it is spelt, can help pupils to
  remember the correct spelling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119960Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-asked-one-impression-character-similar
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """If asked for more than one impression of a character, these may be similar or
  repetitive."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to think of two distinct characteristics or feelings. This
  could be explored by creating a mind map about the character in question."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119977Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-lift-their-pencil-letter
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some children will lift their pencil before the letter string has
  completed."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind the children that the letters want to hold hands and if they lift
  their pencil then the connection is broken. Speaking out loud, while modelling, to
  highlight this will support the children to apply it in their practice."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119988Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confuse-metaphors-similes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may confuse metaphors with similes."@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that metaphors compare things by saying one thing actually is
  another, while a simile uses the words 'like' or 'as'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119994Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-come-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it hard to come up with their own ideas for kennings."@en ;
  curric:correction """Brainstorm ideas about their object first (as shown in LC2), then support
  them to transfer these ideas into kennings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120000Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-create-believe-fronted-adverbial
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may create what they believe are fronted adverbial clauses, but they
  may omit the verb."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It is not wrong to omit a verb (this creates a phrase), but encourage pupils
  to circle or highlight the verb in a clause."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120005Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-omit-commas-speech-interrupted
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may omit the commas from a speech interrupted sentence or include an
  extra capital letter."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use the graphic included in the slides as a visual prompt for pupils when
  writing speech interrupted."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120011Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-single-verb-past
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that every single verb in a past or present tense paragraph
  has to stick to that tense."""@en ;
  curric:correction """We're writing from a present or a past tense perspective, but the way that
  language works means that not every verb will be in the same tense in a paragraph.
  Encourage the children to think about what 'sounds right' and to orally rehearse
  sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120017Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-task-pupils-place-character-traits
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """In Task A, pupils may place character traits both on the inside and outside of
  the outline."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that inner emotions and feelings remain inside, attributes
  that other characters can see go on the outside."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120023Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-use-word
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it difficult to use the word ‘howl’ in a sentence."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that as this word is a verb, we can change the tense to make it fit
  with our sentence. ‘Howled’ or ‘howling’ are alternatives."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120037Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-recognise-poems-structure-convey
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not recognise that a poem's structure can also convey meaning to a
  poem."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Highlight how the poem's lines in 'The Panther' form bars, similar to the
  ones imprisoning the panther in the poem. Pupils could read additional poems (such as
  concrete/shape poetry) to explore this feature further."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120252Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-include-elements-chulaks-interaction
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may include elements of Chulak's interaction with Lalchand in their
  recount because they know this as the reader but Lila only knows what Chulak tells her."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The diary is written from Lila's perspective. From her perspective, Chulak
  said he would visit her father and she doesn't find out anything about the interaction
  until he returns."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120264Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-expect-alliteration-words-placed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may expect alliteration to be when words are placed next to one
  another."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Alliteration also includes words that are placed close together. Pupils could
  text mark a copy of the poem to identify cases where the poetic device is used in the
  poem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120589Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-forget-add-lead-first
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Sometimes children will forget to add the lead in for the first letter in the
  letter string or the first letter after the capital letter."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use the 'Ready, line, go' technique to remind children to start on the
  baseline."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120607Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-words-similar-used-interchangeably
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "These words are very similar and can often be used interchangeably."@en ;
  curric:correction """These words have subtle differences in meaning and usage and are used in
  different contexts; so one can't always be replaced by another."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120690Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-explanation-texts-written
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils think that explanation texts can be written in any order."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explanation texts are written in chronological order; they explain a process
  in the order in which it happens."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120715Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-include-subject-non-finite
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not include the subject of the non-finite clause at the start of
  the main clause."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that the person doing the non-finite clause must be mentioned at the
  start of the main clause."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120720Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-remain-connected
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to remain connected to the different strands of
  the story. E.g. Lila has made it to the Grotto safely, but Chulak and Hamlet's journey is
  still crucial."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ask children to consider why a huge element of suspense remains even though
  Lila has made it to the Grotto. Answer: She may have overcome the challenge of getting
  there but if Chulak doesn't get the magical water to her then she is still in danger."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120726Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-mix-physical-mental-health
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may mix up physical and mental health benefits, leading to an unclear
  argument in the main body paragraph."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The first learning cycle task involves pupils categorising key arguments
  across the two main body paragraphs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120770Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-cursive-formation-letter-f-lead
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The cursive formation of the letter f, with the lead in and lead out loop, can
  be challenging for students."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When modelling, ensure to include examples of words with the letter f at the
  beginning of the word and in the middle. Remind pupils that the letter f is the only
  letter in the alphabet with an ascender and a descender, therefore two loops."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120833Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-keep-e-adding-y
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils keep the 'e' when adding -y to words ending in 'e', writing 'slimey' or
  'stoney'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Focus on the rule, remove the 'e' and add -y, and make links to other
  suffixes that use the same pattern."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120848Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-need-further-explanation-abstract
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will need further explanation on some of the more abstract word pairs.
  For example, a 'murky past' or 'stagnant wages'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """For each word pair that is more abstract, ask the pupils why something might
  be described in that way and put the word pair in a sentence to model to the pupils how to
  use it correctly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120865Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-ensure-their-show
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may struggle to ensure their 'show and tell' language is appropriate
  for each paragraph. For example, paragraph one is meant to convey concern but not complete
  fear yet."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model different examples of 'show and tell'. Ask children to identify whether
  they convey concern or fear. E.g. for concern, we might say 'chest tightened slightly at
  the strange sight'. For fear, we might say, 'heart pounded rapidly in her chest'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120871Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-use-recital
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it challenging to use all recital skills."@en ;
  curric:correction """Each skill of using projection, diction and body language should be
  explicitly modelled. Modelling non-examples are useful for pupils to see and hear what
  works and what doesn't in performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.122961Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-hard-infer-justify
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it hard to infer or justify an appropriate moral for the
  tale."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model linking examples back to the story to ensure it is an appropriate
  inference. E.g. I think the moral of the story is that good deeds are returned because
  after Antelope did a good deed for Anansi, Anansi returned the favour."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.122985Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-consider-sole-purpose-non
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might consider the sole purpose of a non-fiction text is to inform."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explore a range of reasons as to why the text might have been written. If
  possible, provide other non-fiction texts to allow comparison."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.122996Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-friendships-within-texts-positive-throughout
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Friendships within texts are always positive throughout."@en ;
  curric:correction """The friendships and relationships within 'Danny Chung Does Not Do Maths' are
  complex. They could be explored during a PHSE lesson - looking at how some friendships are
  not equal or balanced."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123016Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-pronounce-homonyms-incorrectly-sentences
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may pronounce homonyms incorrectly in sentences."@en ;
  curric:correction """Show pupils that we can use the context of the sentence to help us uncover
  the meaning of the homonym and therefore its pronunciation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123042Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-unclear-their-understanding-different
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may be unclear in their understanding of different complex sentence
  types."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils know that an adverbial clause is one **type** of
  subordinate clause. There are also relative clauses and non-finite clauses that pupils
  should be taught."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123056Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-their-speech-purely
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may think that their speech should be purely made up of rhetorical
  questions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Highlight and explain how rhetorical questions can be interspersed with
  statements and information that reinforce the point and help to achieve the purpose too."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123064Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-mark-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it hard to mark up their own poems."@en ;
  curric:correction """Model marking up the poem as a class, highlighting the different areas you
  might annotate. Pupils could mark up the poem in pairs or small groups."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123087Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-discussing-characters-search
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find discussing a character's search for identity challenging."@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss identity in relation to other characters that pupils have experienced
  in texts they have in common. Links can be made across lessons, particularly Lesson 1 and
  2."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123093Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-metaphors-real
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that metaphors have to be real."@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that metaphors are used when you make a comparison and say
  something is something else when it actually isn't."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123099Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-get-stuck-trying-make
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may get stuck on trying to make every line rhyme."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that free verse poems may use rhyme, but it's usually irregular and
  doesn't follow a particular pattern. Encourage pupils to include two rhyming words if they
  wish, but not to make this a focus of the poem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123107Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-improvising-scene-means
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that improvising a scene means taking a long time rehearsing
  it before a performance - like a normal play."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A cast of actors do not usually rehearse an improvised scene. They might
  spend only 30-60 seconds organising themselves on the stage and telling each other a very
  brief idea about how they are going to act."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123113Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-connect-complex-ideas
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to connect complex ideas with appropriate linguistic
  features."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model and encourage oral rehearsal and use shared writing to model the
  process of selecting between various possible linguistic features you could use."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123118Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-confuse-co-ordinating-subordinating
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may confuse co-ordinating and subordinating conjunctions."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that both conjunctions are taught within the context of full compound
  and complex sentences to avoid confusion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123137Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-three-words-used
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think that all three words can be used interchangeably."@en ;
  curric:correction "Use the word pairs to help pupils see each word and its nuances."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123142Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-internal-thoughts-rhetorical-questions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Internal thoughts are rhetorical questions only."@en ;
  curric:correction """Internal thoughts can be questions and statements. Ensure pupils use their
  plans with ideas for Paikea's internal thoughts and model how to write these in the third
  person."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123173Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-characters-using-same-language
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may have all characters using the same language in direct speech."@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to think about the 'voice' of each character - how might
  they speak?"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123185Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-change-letter-f
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may forget to change the letter 'f' to 'v' and may just add the suffix
  -es."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Share lots of examples and give pupils the chance to say the plurals aloud so
  that they can hear the different sounds e.g. wolfs, wolves."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123191Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-think-character
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to think of character traits to describe Tranio
  in Task B."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A list of common traits could be displayed or printed for pupils to refer to.
  These could include traits such as: courage, selflessness, honesty, compassion, integrity,
  determination and leadership."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123489Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-edward-isnt-likeable-protagonist
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Edward isn't a likeable protagonist."@en ;
  curric:correction """Edward Tulane is an anti-hero. An anti-hero is a flawed protagonist, often
  with ambiguous morals."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123511Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-expect-experiences-deafness-deaf
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may expect all experiences with deafness and the Deaf community to
  reflect this text."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to the children that the text explores an individual’s recount of
  their experiences; it is not reflective of every experience within the Deaf community.
  Pupils could read additional texts to develop greater awareness and empathy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123742Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-know-character-feeling
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think you can only know how a character is feeling by an explicit
  feelings word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """We can understand a character's feelings by inferring meaning through the
  character's actions, their words and their experiences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123750Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-convey-certain
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to convey certain emotions without explicitly
  stating the feeling."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explore common informal phrases used for certain emotions. E.g. \"I am down
  in the dumps\" to convey sadness."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123765Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-assume-mention-character-speech
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may assume that any mention of character speech is direct speech,
  because that has been the focus in the lesson."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model how speech can still be indirectly reported within the opening
  alongside direct speech. E.g. 'Scrooge muttered insults at all those he passed.'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123839Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-christian-find-hard-connect
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils who are Christian may find it hard to connect their faith to the one
  depicted here."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to children that religions evolve over time and that beliefs are not
  always fixed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123845Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-understand-idea-concept
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to understand the idea of a 'concept'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Spend a moment coming up with a list of concepts like 'hope', 'fear' and
  'happiness' that you can refer back to."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123856Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-essays-opportunity-writers
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that essays are an opportunity for writers to share their own
  opinions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make explicit reference to the word 'arguments' rather than 'opinions' or
  'viewpoints'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123861Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-believe-plural-nouns-end
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may believe all plural nouns end in 's'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss the plural nouns that do not end in 's' such as children, women,
  mice."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123867Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-evolutionary-changes-happen
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may believe that evolutionary changes happen rapidly."@en ;
  curric:correction "Evolution is a process that occurs over huge periods of time."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123883Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-know-pronounce-focus-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may not know how to pronounce focus words within the lesson, meaning
  they can't identify the stressed syllable."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use 'my turn your turn' to ensure children can pronounce focus words
  correctly, and also put into sentences so they can understand the meaning and word class
  in context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123888Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-identify-fer
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it very difficult to identify when 'fer' is stressed or
  unstressed."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model saying the words with 'fer' aloud and stressing the appropriate
  syllable. Ask pupils to copy you."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123896Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-know-meaning-words-root
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not know the meaning of words or root words."@en ;
  curric:correction """Spend time in the lesson discussing the meanings and links you can make
  between words and languages."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123935Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-fronted-adverbials-inaccurately
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may use fronted adverbials inaccurately by getting the 'and' and 'but'
  adverbials mixed up."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils to say their sentences out loud so they can hear if the fronted
  adverbial they've chosen to use sounds right."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123963Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-write-their-facts-incoherent
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may write their facts in an incoherent order."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils are following the order of the facts on their plans when
  writing full sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123971Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-know-shun-spelling
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may struggle to know which /shun/ spelling to use."@en ;
  curric:correction """If needed, refer back to the Year 4 content where the /shun/ spellings are
  introduced initially. Emphasise that -tion is the 'best bet' and most common spelling and
  use that as the focus for the lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123977Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confuse-speech-punctuation-rules
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may confuse speech punctuation rules when writing speech first and
  speech second in a narrative."""@en ;
  curric:correction """At the end of speech first, a full stop must not be used. At the end of
  speech second, a full stop can be used."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123991Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-switching-order-clauses
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may struggle with switching the order of the clauses in an adverbial
  complex sentence and remembering the comma rule."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide a model of an adverbial complex sentence. Example: 'Her heart raced
  as she tumbled backwards.' Ask children to identify the subordinating conjunction that
  begins the adverbial clause in order to switch the clauses."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124084Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-respect-sensitivity-subject
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to respect the sensitivity of the subject matter."@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils throughout to view the accused people as real people. You
  may want to refer to Addie's response to the school trip to help children understand this."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124569Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-traditional-fairy-tales
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may believe that all traditional fairy tales include stereotypes."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that stereotypes are formed as a result of many stories including
  similar features. Not all traditional tales include them. Stereotypes can also be found in
  contemporary texts too, which could be explored with pupils."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124608Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-stereotype-link-someones-race-cultural
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A stereotype always has to link to someone's race or cultural background."@en ;
  curric:correction """Stereotypes do not always relate to race or cultural background. Stereotypes
  can also be based on various other factors such as gender, age, religion, physical
  appearance and other protected characteristics."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124616Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-lose-sight-overall-structure
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may lose sight of the overall structure of the planned report."@en ;
  curric:correction """Constantly refer back to the idea of paragraphs focusing on a given theme
  (diet, habitat) after a general introduction."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124638Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-play-scripts-dictate-aspect-performance
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Play scripts dictate every aspect of a performance down to the smallest
  detail."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Actors and directors have creative freedom to interpret the text, bringing
  their own insights and ideas to the characters and scenes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124644Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-identifying-linguistic-features
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find identifying linguistic features of the text type
  challenging."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explicit explanations are given for key linguistic features and modelled in
  the example biography."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124655Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-include-information-mentions-keywords
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may include any information that mentions keywords in the question
  stem."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It is important to model re-reading the question and answer, checking
  evidence for accuracy and context in answers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124669Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-points-equally-effective
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may think that all points are equally effective in a debate."@en ;
  curric:correction """Whilst it is good to generate lots of points when preparing for a debate,
  they will vary in how effective they are."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124680Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-adjective-choices-descriptive
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may use adjective choices that are descriptive and subjective."@en ;
  curric:correction """Adjective choices are formal and technical in an explanation text rather than
  descriptive."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124688Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-place-apostrophe-correctly
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to place the apostrophe correctly after the 's' for plural
  possession."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that the apostrophe is placed after the 's' when showing
  possession for plural nouns that already end in 's'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124694Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-speeches-need-follow
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that speeches do not need to follow a particular
  structure."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Following a structure, such as PEPS, can help a speech to flow and make it
  easier to follow for an audience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124700Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-used-progressive-tense
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might think they have used the progressive tense simply by using a
  being verb like 'am'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """'I am happy today.' Ask pupils why this is not written in the progressive
  tense. The being verb must help the main verb that ends in -ing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124706Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-come-internal
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it hard to come up with internal thoughts for a character."@en ;
  curric:correction """Play a game of 'freeze frame' for different parts of the build-up and
  encourage children to share their thoughts and feelings, to support all children with
  ideas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124711Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-include-information-food-travelling
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might include information about food travelling into the
  intestines."""@en ;
  curric:correction """This section explains the process of food entering the body, moving through
  the oesophagus and to the stomach."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125019Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-characters-fairytales-either
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children might think that characters in fairytales are always either good or
  evil."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Some characters are more complex to understand and can show a range of
  characteristics which offers a great opportunity for debate."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125237Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-students-find-difficult-understand-elements
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Students may find it difficult to understand elements from the opening due to
  unfamiliar vocabulary, specifically vocabulary that is culturally specific (e.g. 'rupee'
  or 'rickshaw')."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pre-teach unfamiliar vocabulary from the opening using visual images to
  support student understanding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125270Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-understand-concept
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to understand the concept of challenging the
  idea of what is 'normal'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explore examples of how 'normal' looks different everywhere. Encourage
  children to consider things that may feel normal to them but not to others as a a tool for
  exploring the concept."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125364Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-omit-comma-reporting-clause
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may omit the comma after the reporting clause, or they may use a comma
  to end the sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Reinforce the point that commas are never used to close a sentence, even in
  speech second sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125392Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-think-authors
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it hard to think of authors, illustrators and books that
  inspire them."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure your classroom has a diverse range of texts on display for children to
  explore. Regularly discuss text choices with pupils. You may want to refer to 'Developing
  Reading preferences in Year 4' to inspire some discussions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125420Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-identify-effect-kennings
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to identify the effect of the kennings in the
  second task."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You may want to complete this task orally with partner talk, or as a class
  discussion, rather than as independent work."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125426Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-retrieve-partial-answers-skim
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may retrieve partial answers if they do not skim and scan
  properly."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Example: 'The Ganges River in India is sacred to Hindus' might lead children
  to think this is its only location. Check the spotlight box."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125871Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-identify-informal
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it difficult to identify informal language."@en ;
  curric:correction """Spend some time examining different ways that informal language appears in
  the model diary entry (e.g. exaggeration, contractions, capitalised words, informal
  vocabulary)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125913Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-vowel-sound-preceding
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may think that the vowel sound preceding the 'l' will always
  determine the spelling."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Showing examples of incorrect use of 'el' and 'le' alongside the correct can
  be very useful for children to spot the correct spelling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126180Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-six-words-used
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think all six words can be used interchangeably."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that these words all have nuanced meanings and some
  are different word classes. Use the word pairs to show each word being used correctly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126378Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-non-fiction-form
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think that non-fiction is a form not a genre."@en ;
  curric:correction """Non-fiction is a genre of text. It can be presented in many different forms.
  Provide pupils with examples to read."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126459Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-assume-hero-portrays-positive
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might assume a hero only portrays positive traits, an anti-hero only
  negative traits."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss a range of protagonists and reflect on their traits and
  characterisation. Not all characters will be heroes or anti-heroes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126486Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-write-relative-complex-sentences
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may write relative complex sentences where the relative clause does not
  describe the noun preceding it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Learning cycle 1 explicitly models ensuring that the relative clause adds a
  relevant fact to the noun before it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126589Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-see-differences
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it hard to see the differences between metaphors and
  similes."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that metaphors say something is something else and similes
  compare two things using 'like' or 'as'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126806Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-translate-shakespearean-language
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to 'translate' the Shakespearean language."@en ;
  curric:correction """Model your thinking as a reader, applying your knowledge of the scene to the
  words and drawing on your knowledge of familiar words to deduce the overall meaning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.127040Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-connect-ideas-cohesive
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to connect ideas with cohesive devices."@en ;
  curric:correction """Model the idea that there are often many appropriate ways to link the same
  ideas; refer to the Cohesive Devices Bank for more ideas and give pupils access to it
  during writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.127106Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-using-verb-means
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that using a being or having verb means they've written a
  sentence in each tense."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Being verbs as auxiliary verbs are for progressive tenses; having verbs as
  auxiliary verbs are for perfect tenses."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.127126Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-describe-nates-mother-negative
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may describe Nate’s mother in a negative light."@en ;
  curric:correction "Discuss the portrayal of Nate’s mother as you continue reading."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.127343Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-apostrophes-incorrectly-indicating
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may use apostrophes incorrectly when indicating possession."@en ;
  curric:correction """Supplement the content in Learning Cycle One with further teaching of the
  rules associated with using apostrophes for singular and plural possession."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.127349Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-identify-generate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to identify or generate appropriate exaggerated
  synonyms."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model the use of a thesaurus to identify appropriate exaggerated synonyms and
  create a shared bank of appropriate vocabulary for the children to use when writing their
  notes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.127366Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-verbs-based-auxiliary
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that verbs based on 'to have' and 'to be' are **always**
  auxiliary verbs."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that when these verbs are on their own, they are just a main verb -
  they only change the tense when acting as an auxiliary verb."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.127372Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-thinking-connections-greenling
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find thinking of connections between 'Greenling' and the rewilding
  non-fiction text challenging."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model making connections aloud, focusing on character, setting and plot. Some
  pupils may benefit from printed double-page spreads of certain illustrations to support."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130384Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-assume-detail-text-needs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may assume that every detail in the text needs to be literally depicted
  in the illustration."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Effective illustration often involves capturing the feeling or atmosphere of
  the writing rather than just visualising specific objects."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130540Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-hard-retrieve-answer
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it hard to retrieve an answer if it is not in the sentence
  that the keyword is in."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model checking the sentence before and after. E.g. For Task B 1. b), the
  answer to the question is in the sentences that follows the one with the keywords."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130738Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-facts-specific-introduction
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may use facts that are too specific in the introduction."@en ;
  curric:correction """General facts and information should be explicitly shared. Visuals that
  represent **general** versus **specific** information should be referred to throughout the
  planning process. Visuals help pupils 'see' which information belongs where."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130757Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-begin-retell-key-events
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may begin to retell key events or add too much detailed information
  about the day when planning the closing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make continued explicit reference to keeping information general; a visual
  aid of 'general' may help to support pupils remember this distinction."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130763Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-know-differences-childrens-rights
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not know about the differences in children's rights to education
  around the world."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that before beginning this lesson, you have developed pupils'
  understanding of how children's rights to education are different around the world. You
  could use PSHE sessions to explore this in more depth."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130985Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-stop-retelling
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it hard to stop retelling at the end of Chapter three and may
  continue to retell the rest of the story."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make it clear that we are only focusing on the first part of the story for
  this narrative writing unit. Model retelling the story first."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130990Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-assume-deluge-adjective-weather
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might assume 'deluge' is an adjective as most of the weather words have
  been adjectives."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Choose some words associated with the weather (take suggestions from the
  class and write them down). Look at each one and discuss if the word is a noun or an
  adjective. E.g. rain (noun), rainy (adjective), sun (noun), hot (adjective)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.131126Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-assume-words-ending-suffix
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often assume words ending in the suffix -ing indicate the present
  tense."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Refer to the Year 3 grammar lesson on 'being' verbs and give plenty of
  examples to show the verbs in both past tense and present tense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.131512Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-consider-chaos-greek-god
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may consider Chaos to be a Greek god."@en ;
  curric:correction """Chaos is considered a primordial being. It represents the formless, shapeless
  state from which everything else emerged."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132421Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-include-steps-process-food
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might include steps in the process from when the food arrives in the
  mouth."""@en ;
  curric:correction """This section of the explanation text is about what happens after the food
  leaves the stomach."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132426Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confused-statue-speak-used
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may be confused by how the statue can speak and used to be a living
  person."""@en ;
  curric:correction """'The Happy Prince' is a fictional text so the characters act in ways that are
  not usual for humans."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132543Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-relationships-within-text
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that all relationships within the text remain fixed or
  static."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It may be beneficial to verbally model an example for Task A to support
  pupils in their understanding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132726Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-show-elements-maggies
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may want to show elements of Maggie's story that are gratuitously
  graphic or violent."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that we are talking about real people and that we should
  consider how Addie reacted to this in the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132837Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-punctuate-direct-speech
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to punctuate direct speech correctly."@en ;
  curric:correction """Visual prompts for punctuating different types of direct speech can be found
  in our KS2 Grammar curriculum."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132871Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-identify-familiar-fairy
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may struggle to identify which familiar fairy tale characters the boy
  encounters in the forest."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ask questions to prompt children, e.g. 'Which fairy tale character do you
  know who sold a cow?' Also encourage children to look for further clues in the
  illustrations, e.g. There is a beanstalk in the illustration on page 10."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133116Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-speaker-need-follow-set-structure
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A speaker does not need to follow a set structure when making a speech in a
  debate."""@en ;
  curric:correction """There are many benefits to following a structure when making a speech in a
  debate."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133122Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-correctly-use-apostrophe
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to correctly use the apostrophe for plural possession."@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that whenever the noun doing the possessing ends in s, the
  apostrophe goes after the s."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133382Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-concept-manipulation-difficult
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might find the concept of 'manipulation' difficult to understand."@en ;
  curric:correction """You could provide pupils with a context that they might understand, for
  example, imagine a friend doesn't want to take someone else's packed lunch, but you want
  them to. How could you manipulate them? What could you say to convince them?"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133400Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-idea-jumping-past
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle with the idea of jumping between past and present
  tense."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that this is a common way of writing a diary: the person writing
  begins by saying how they feel right now before going back to explain the events that led
  up to them feeling this way."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133411Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-write-character
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it difficult to write in the character of the red crayon."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that you have additional resources like word banks for pupils to refer
  to that reference 'I', 'me', 'my', 'we', 'our' and 'us' words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133544Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-apply-comma-rule
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle with how to apply the comma rule in a relative complex
  sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide a visual scaffold of a relative complex sentence. Ask children to
  identify the relative pronoun that begins the relative clause and ensure that the visual
  highlights the comma rule."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133553Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-remembering-punctuation-rules
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle with remembering the punctuation rules in speech second
  sentences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide a visual scaffold of the speech second punctuation rules. Encourage
  pupils to use this when writing direct speech."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.133559Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-mission-succeeds-its
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that every mission succeeds in its aims due to the time,
  money and investment from scientists."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Draw reader's attention to the amount of time the team took to test the rover
  and the several failed attempts. Adults could link these processes to the processes the
  pupils complete in science (e.g. fair testing, hypothesising)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134068Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-imagery-appeals-one
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that imagery appeals to just one of the senses."@en ;
  curric:correction """Through interpretation, imagery in the poem may fall under more than one
  sense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134073Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-description-non-fiction
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may think that there is no description in non-fiction texts."@en ;
  curric:correction """In narrative non-fiction texts authors use literary devices such as imagery,
  similes and metaphors to enhance a reader's understanding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134085Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-look-illustration-first-identify-happening
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """You should always look at an illustration first to identify what is happening
  in a text."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Illustrations can be very helpful for supporting understanding, but using
  strategies to understand vocabulary first is really important."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134091Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-segment-addies
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to segment Addie's speech into three
  sections."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to think about past drama tasks where they looked at Addie's
  feelings before, during and after her speech."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134801Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-speech-debate-improvised
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that a speech in a debate can be improvised on the spot and
  not follow a structure."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that following a structure will help to make their speech flow
  better and be easier for an audience to follow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.135030Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-less-confident-readers-find-reading
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Less confident readers may find reading aloud challenging in a whole class
  context."""@en ;
  curric:correction """More confident readers could be partnered up with lesser-confident pupils,
  with a copy of the two double page spreads to refer to."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.135066Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-favourite-character-someone-embodies-positive
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A favourite character is always someone who embodies positive character
  traits."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Favourite characters can be characters involved in key moments in the text;
  characters who change the most in the story; or, characters who remind readers of someone
  they know."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.135145Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-think-counter
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it challenging to think of a counter-argument."@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to think of one strong point. When thinking of a
  counter-argument, pupils should consider the opposite idea to their point."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.135174Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-lot-subject-specific
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may use a lot of subject-specific vocabulary without clearly explaining
  its meaning to the reader."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils should be taught how to use parenthesis demarcated using brackets to
  add additional information to sentences. Brackets are a great tool with which to explain
  meaning of tricky vocabulary to the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.135247Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-set-rules-follow-comparing-poems
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "There is a set of rules to follow when comparing poems."@en ;
  curric:correction """Comparing poems often involves exploring similarities and differences, but
  remind pupils that it is a subjective process."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.135259Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-using-good-vocabulary-automatically-makes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Using 'good vocabulary' automatically makes writing better."@en ;
  curric:correction """There are no 'good' and 'bad words' in English. Rather, some are more precise
  and appropriate in certain contexts than others."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.135679Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-words-ending-ent
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Some pupils may think all words ending in -ent are the same word class."@en ;
  curric:correction """Whilst the suffixes -ent and -ence can change word class, not all words
  ending in -ent are the same word class. Give examples in a sentence to demonstrate, using
  the words contentment, (to) frequent, and silent."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.136170Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-assume-translations-offer-exact
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might assume translations offer exact word-for-word equivalence to the
  original."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Translators make choices to convey meaning in the target language, not always
  aligning precisely with the source text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.136249Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-spell-words-suffix-ful
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may spell words with the suffix -ful using a double 'l'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explicilty make the distinction between the word 'full' and the suffix -ful,
  which only has one 'l'. Practise spelling both in a sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.136329Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-characters-emotions-change
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that a character's emotions have to change drastically
  throughout a chapter."""@en ;
  curric:correction """In some chapters and with some characters, there will be less change as
  events that happen to them may not affect their emotions. You can explore this through the
  use of an emotions graph."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.136365Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-single-main-clauses
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that only single main clauses can be joined by
  co-ordinating conjunctions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Co-ordinating conjunctions can join groups of words that might be sentences
  on their own, including at least one main clause."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137082Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-initially-confuse-meaning-differences
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children might initially confuse the meaning and differences of genre and
  themes."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Although certain genres of text explore common themes, these themes can vary
  from text to text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137105Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-forms-poetry-rhyme
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that all forms of poetry must have to rhyme."@en ;
  curric:correction """Before the lesson, you might share examples of a range of poems in both fixed
  verse and free verse."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137111Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confused-antiquated-language-impact
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may be confused by some of the antiquated language. This might impact
  reading fluency."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to use reading strategies to support them in their initial
  understanding of the poem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137241Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-verbs-sentence-kept
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that all verbs in a sentence are always kept in the same
  tense."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Constantly encourage children to think about what 'sounds right' in a
  sentence and to try out different verb forms orally to see what works."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137267Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-informal-term-speech
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may use the informal term 'speech marks'."@en ;
  curric:correction """'speech marks' is a term that signals the same thing as 'inverted commas'
  i.e. the dialogue in a sentence, but it is better to use the grammatical term 'inverted
  commas'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137291Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-generate-range
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to generate a range of precise and ambitious
  vocabulary in order to avoid repetition in the build up."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model the use of a thesaurus for uplevelling vocabulary. E.g. Instead of
  'ran', when describing the movements of Hogarth and his father, show other examples like
  'raced', 'sped', 'sprinted', 'hurried', 'darted'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137296Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-climax-turning-point
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may think that a climax and a turning point are exactly the same
  thing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """As you continue to read the text, discuss the climax with pupils as the
  highest point of tension and discuss differences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137302Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-identify-informal
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may find it difficult to identify informal language."@en ;
  curric:correction """Spend some time examining different ways informal language appears in the
  model diary entry (e.g. exaggeration, contractions, capitalised words, informal
  vocabulary)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138191Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-understand-why-characters
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to understand why the characters take such drastic action
  in the play."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain the importance of familial obligations at the time the play is set;
  use analogies to describe the feud between the houses. Note also the difficulties around
  communication - there was no easy way to send messages!"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138301Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-spend-much-time-their
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might spend too much time on their sketch, not leaving them with enough
  time for their annotations."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model drawing a sketch yourself. You could also give pupils a timer of two
  minutes to complete their sketch in. For pupils who are struggling, you might provide a
  printed sketch of the witches to support them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139569Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-verb-meander-instead
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might use the verb 'meander' instead of the adjective 'meandering' in
  their sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that 'meander' is a useful verb to use, but be clear that
  it is different to the adjective 'meandering' which is used to describe a noun and not as
  an action."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139823Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-write-full-section-one
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may write the full section as one paragraph."@en ;
  curric:correction """Parts of the plan are explicitly allocated into paragraphs one and two. This
  is also modelled in the second learning cycle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139876Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-agree-placement
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to agree on the placement of the statements in
  Task A."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Consider printing the statements and the Venn diagram, to allow pupils to
  move them as they discuss and work in small groups or pairs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139881Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-choose-wrong-spelling-strategy
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may choose the wrong spelling strategy to practise a
  particular word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Help pupils to make informed choices about which spelling strategy is best to
  learn particular types of words. For example, 'naughty letters' is useful to learn those
  with unusual spelling patterns. Pupils will also develop their own favourites."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.140188Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-keep-language-formal
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to keep language formal when generating expanded noun
  phrases relating to the penguins."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model out loud the thought process of selecting and rejecting different
  adjectives, bearing in mind formality - e.g. rejecting 'cute' and selecting
  'instantly-recognisable'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.140851Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-points-involve-full
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that points should involve full and long explanations."@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that points are only one sentence long and use the word
  'because' to give one reason to justify an opinion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.140885Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-understand-duelling
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it challenging to understand the duelling terms."@en ;
  curric:correction """Model each to pupils - it does not matter if it is technically perfect - and
  have them practise acting them out repeatedly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.141024Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-conventions-rules-writers
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that conventions are 'rules' that writers must
  stick to."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Draw attention to how, even in this story, some of the conventions are broken
  - this doesn't mean it's not detective fiction! You may ask pupils to think of their own
  examples of broken conventions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.141041Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-uncertain-different-elements-science
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may be uncertain of the different elements of a science fiction
  text."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You may wish to have a selection of science fiction texts available in the
  classroom for pupils to explore. Spend time talking through the different features of this
  genre."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.141093Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-disability-deformity-interchangeable
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that disability and deformity are interchangeable."@en ;
  curric:correction """August's facial deformity does not directly impair his physical abilities or
  cognitive functions. The email conversation between Julian's mother and Mr. Tushman
  explores this on pages 162 and 163."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.141138Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-hard-understand-girls
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might find it hard to understand the girl's comparison to the migrating
  birds at the end of the story."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The girl is comparing the birds' journey to her family's journey. The birds
  are also migrating to another country, but the difference is that the birds didn't have
  any difficulty crossing borders. Explore this comparison with pupils in detail."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.142121Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-find-information-explicitly
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may think that they can only find out information explicitly written
  in a non-fiction text."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Using inference skills and having rich discussion can allow students to draw
  greater conclusions about the information given."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.142127Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-impressions-formed-readers-understood-text
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Impressions can only be formed from what readers have understood from the
  text."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that impressions can also be based on a reader's prior experience,
  however reasoning should be supported with factual evidence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.142468Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-poem-include-rhyme
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that every poem has to include rhyme."@en ;
  curric:correction """Rhyme does not have to be included in each poem. Should pupils wish to
  include rhyme, a list of rhyming words can be generated with the whole class, in line with
  the positive imagery."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.142974Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-macbeth-solely-depicts-triumph-evil
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "'Macbeth' solely depicts the triumph of evil."@en ;
  curric:correction """Shakespeare depicts the intricacies of the human condition and the
  multifaceted motivations behind characters' actions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.142980Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-understand-concept-characterisation
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to understand the concept of characterisation."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that the author is trying make us feel certain things about the
  characters; characterisation is just the process of doing that. If the author wants us to
  think Grendel is scary, they have to make that happen through their descriptions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.143325Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-forget-lead-loop-letter
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children can forget the lead-in loop for the letter f when it is at the
  beginning of a word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model and remind children that every lower case letter starts on the baseline
  for cursive handwriting. This will remind the children to add the lead in loop."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.143330Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-characters-traits-behaviours
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that characters' traits and behaviours remain fixed within a
  narrative."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss that several characters evolve emotionally over the narrative.
  Governor Adori begins the text very commanding, authoritative and selfish - he ends up
  redeeming himself by giving his daughter and Isabella time to escape."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.143376Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-life-victorians-positive
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that life for all Victorians was positive."@en ;
  curric:correction """Depending on social class, life was very different. There was a big divide
  between rich and poor, with many people living in poverty."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.143382Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-researching-author-automatically-improve-readers
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Researching an author will automatically improve a reader's experience with a
  text."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Researching an author can support readers in making connections,
  understanding influences and exploring how a text is created."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.143390Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-lesson-contains-lot-subject-specific
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """This lesson contains a lot of subject-specific language and information
  related to the civil war in America."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Information is chunked into small, accessible parts and subject-specific
  vocabulary is explicitly defined."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.143438Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-understand-nuanced
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to understand the nuanced difference between
  feelings and character traits."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Distinguish between a temporary feeling and a character trait. Explain that
  feelings become character traits if they are persistently displayed. E.g. Lila does not
  always feel frustrated but she has always shown determination."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.143538Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-one-right-answer
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children might think there is only one right answer to what message a story is
  trying to convey."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Authors understand that readers infer different meaning from their stories
  and are able to develop their own responses and opinions to them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.143543Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-include-steps-process-come
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might include steps of the process that come in section 1 of the
  explanation text."""@en ;
  curric:correction """This section explains the final three steps of the mummification process,
  starting from when the body was covered in oil."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.143563Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-forget-switch
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult or forget to switch from a character voice to a
  narrator voice when they have finished saying the speech and they are saying the reporting
  clause."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Print a copy of the speech section of the story that shows the speech and
  reporting clause in different colours to support children in their oral rehearsal for
  different character's voices."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.143728Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-remembering-comma-rule
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle with remembering the comma rule in an adverbial complex
  sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide a visual scaffold of an adverbial complex sentence. Ask children to
  identify the subordinating conjunction that begins the adverbial clause and ensure that
  the visual highlights the comma rule."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.143747Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-understand-stare
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might find it difficult to understand how a 'stare' or a 'silence'
  could be described as 'frosty'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand that 'frosty' can also be used to describe something
  as 'unwelcoming'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.143834Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-one-character-paikea-koro-s
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "One character (Paikea or Koro)'s perspective is entirely right or wrong."@en ;
  curric:correction """Both Paikea and Koro have valid reasons for their beliefs and actions because
  of their backgrounds, experiences and the cultural context of their community."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.143883Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-question-first-cycle-explores-letter
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A question in the first cycle explores the letter that Sophia's father writes
  to Queen Victoria. Pupils may find it hard to think of persuasive techniques that he uses
  to appeal for forgiveness."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It would be useful to link to prior learning to remind pupils of some
  techniques (such as emotional language, flattery, rhetorical questions etc.),
  alternatively adults could model some of the key points aloud."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.144270Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-identify-correct-punctuation
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to identify the correct punctuation for bullet points."@en ;
  curric:correction """There are very few hard-and-fast rules; the key is to select consistent
  punctuation throughout the list."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.144276Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-connect-ideas-using
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to connect ideas using a range of cohesive devices."@en ;
  curric:correction """Lessons about all the relevant cohesive devices can be found in our KS2
  Grammar curriculum; you could select slides to pre-teach particular concepts if needed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.144292Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-understand-concept-obligation
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to understand the concept of 'obligation' in relation to
  modal verbs."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Talk about how sentences are showing that the speaker thinks they or someone
  else are 'obliged to' do something."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.144298Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-see-evidence-based
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to see the evidence on which they have based their
  inferences about characters' emotions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """We automatically infer as we read; encourage pupils to look back and think,
  'What made you think that? What clues did the author give us?'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.144304Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-make-mistakes-their-repeat
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children often make mistakes in their repeat copying of spelling words by not
  checking properly."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Show children how to check by moving a finger along each letter of the word,
  checking the original against the newly written version."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.144485Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-ending-spelt-sounds
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think the ending is spelt how it sounds: 'iz'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Show pupils that the ending is spelt with the suffix -es, even though it can
  sound different."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.144646Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-narrator-story-remains-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The narrator in a story always remains the same."@en ;
  curric:correction """There can be more than one narrator in a story. A change in narrator can
  demonstrate a shift in time or offer a different perspective."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.146435Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-alliteration-occurs-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that alliteration only occurs when the words are next to
  one another."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Words do not necessarily have to be right next to each other, but the
  repeated consonant sounds should occur in close proximity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.146957Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-questions-genre-story-belongs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may have questions about the genre that the story belongs to and be
  unsure of what constitutes mythology. Children may also notice elements within the story
  that are similar to fairytales."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explore examples of myths that the children have been previously exposed to
  and ask them to identify any commonalities within 'The Moon Dragons'. Explore which
  features of the story are reminiscent of fairy tales."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.146972Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-pollution-rivers-affects
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may think that pollution of rivers only affects the animals and
  plants that inhabit it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model examples of how food chains are broken for other animals and humans if
  living things in rivers are destroyed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147161Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-recall-define
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to recall, define and use different figurative
  language structures."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide plenty of additional examples of effective figurative language. A
  display board or working wall of the different types of figurative language with examples
  that match the text type will be helpful."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147169Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-fronted-adverbials-place
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that all fronted adverbials of place are preposition
  phrases."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Some are ('In the distance,'), but others are not ('Everywhere,'). A
  preposition phrase contains a preposition followed by a noun phrase and preposition
  phrases can often be placed at the start of a sentence to make a fronted adverbial of
  place."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147175Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-walter-paid-well
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not think that Walter was paid well as a footballer. The value of
  currency was different."""@en ;
  curric:correction """In the 1900s, Walter's signing-on fee and weekly wage was very
  competitive."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147181Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-range-different-answers-final
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may have a range of different answers for the final question in
  Task B."""@en ;
  curric:correction """If pupils' responses can be justified with evidence from the text, they are
  likely to be good justifications. It may be beneficial to share an example for each option
  verbally."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147282Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-identify-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to identify which words should be included in
  bullet-point notes."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model non-examples, e.g., 'downhill' and ask which keyword might be missing.
  'Flows downhill' summarises appropriately."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147288Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-nouns-made-plural
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that all nouns can be made plural by adding an 's'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils that there are some other ways to show more than one, such as
  one mouse, two mice or one child, two children."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147338Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-identify-concepts-story
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to identify concepts from the story."@en ;
  curric:correction """You may prefer to provide a longer list of abstract nouns and allow children
  to make their own connections."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147344Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-imagery-appeal-senses
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that imagery must appeal to all of the senses for it to be
  effective."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that imagery may just appeal to one or two senses and provide
  examples. Look at examples of imagery in other texts so that pupils are able to identify
  these independently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147367Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-consider-themes-universally-understood
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may only consider themes that are universally understood."@en ;
  curric:correction """Highlight that there are many possible themes that can be drawn out from a
  text; readers may interpret these differently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147376Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-include-part-macbeth-sees
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might include the part where Macbeth sees the dagger, which is what
  they will write in the closing in the subsequent lesson."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make sure pupils understand that they are writing about the visualisation of
  the dagger in the next section of the soliloquy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147382Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-direct-speech-mimic-real-life
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Direct speech should mimic real-life conversation exactly."@en ;
  curric:correction """Direct speech should serve specific purposes, such as advancing the plot,
  developing characters or providing necessary information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147388Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-mix-vowel-spellings-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children mix up the vowel spellings in the words 'desperate' and
  'separate'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Saying the words slowly how they are spelt can help: sep-ar-ate,
  des-per-ate."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147393Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-vocabulary-used-describe-alinas-connection
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some of the vocabulary used to describe Alina's connection to nature and the
  moon dragons may be unfamiliar, e.g. 'intuitive'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explore the word 'intuitive' and its definition. Ask the children to consider
  moments that they feel a sense of intuitiveness and how this guides them to make
  decisions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147399Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-commas-indicate-pause
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that commas indicate a 'pause' in sentences, or 'taking a
  breath'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Commas have a number of specific functions, several of which are covered in
  this lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147405Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-punctuate-direct
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it difficult to punctuate direct speech correctly."@en ;
  curric:correction """Complete lessons on punctuating direct speech can be found in our Year 5
  Grammar curriculum; you may wish to briefly review a couple of these slides based on your
  assessment of pupils' work in the previous lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147411Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-similes-compare-two-similar-things
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Similes must compare two similar things."@en ;
  curric:correction """While similes often compare two things with some shared characteristics, they
  can also highlight differences for emphasis or contrast."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147420Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-learning-entire-poem
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find learning the entire poem off by heart challenging."@en ;
  curric:correction """The lesson focuses on learning the first two verses by heart. If pupils are
  successful, they could try committing the entire poem to memory."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147439Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-explain-why
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it difficult to explain why a motion is not effective."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain thoroughly the criteria of an 'effective motion': it should be clear
  and easy to understand; both sides must have an opportunity to make a fair point; it must
  be relatable, important and respectful."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147450Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-poetry-rhyme
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that all poetry has to rhyme."@en ;
  curric:correction """Have a wide range of different poetic forms available. Perhaps encourage
  pupils to discover more about the fixed verse forms at home."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147459Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-feel-prepared-enough-debate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not feel prepared enough for the debate."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils have completed the previous lesson 'Preparing for a debate'.
  Speakers should all have written notes and have been assigned roles in their teams. They
  should have rehearsed their speeches and roles."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147465Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-terms-peritext-paratext
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may use the terms peritext and paratext interchangeably."@en ;
  curric:correction """It can be helpful to think of the peritext as everything on the ‘outside’ of
  the book, the paratext as extra information 'inside' the book."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147473Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-texts-emotional-intellectual
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might think that texts can only have emotional or intellectual
  connections to readers."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that texts can connect both intellectually and emotionally. Provide
  examples from members of staff."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147498Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-encounter-new-unfamiliar-vocabulary
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may encounter new or unfamiliar vocabulary in the additional material
  resources."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pre-teaching specific terms with definitions or visuals will support less
  confident readers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147503Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-practising-spellings-children-practise-wrong
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When practising spellings, children can practise wrong by copying out
  incorrectly."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure to place emphasis on carefully looking and checking the spellings when
  practising. This can be done individually or in pairs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147686Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-language-new-unfamiliar
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find some of the language new or unfamiliar to them."@en ;
  curric:correction """An extended definition list could be created to support pupils in
  understanding. Explain that it is normal to not understand all the language in a poem,
  especially when we first read it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147692Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confuse-purposes-different-sections
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may confuse the purposes of the different sections of the story."@en ;
  curric:correction """Each section serves a different purpose for the reader or viewer. One section
  may intend to set a scene whilst another may increase tension."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147698Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-recognise-non-fiction-texts
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not recognise non-fiction texts in picturebook form."@en ;
  curric:correction """Non-fiction can take many different forms. If possible, have a range of
  non-fiction texts accessible in the book area or school library for children to explore
  and compare."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147764Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-see-structure-within
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to see the structure within such a long narrative."@en ;
  curric:correction """Note that structure is somewhat subjective, but that a lot of the plot will
  be taken up with the build-up towards the climax. Many plots intertwine and build tension."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147805Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-try-use-same-join
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may try to use the same join for every connection."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure the children are given plenty of reminders about the four joins and
  how the join used depends on the letters joining. Use the CFU's within this lesson to help
  explain this."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147817Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-word-prefix-meaning
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that for every word with a prefix the meaning of the prefix
  will be very literal."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Show a range of words with the focus prefixes in. Whilst with some words the
  meaning of the prefix may be clear, with others it is not. Explain this is linked to the
  complex way that language develops over time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147822Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-see-word-ending-separate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children can sometimes see the word ending as a separate word and lift their
  pencil which disconnects the letter string."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind the children to look and read the word before writing it. Get them
  feeling confident that this is one word and the flow needs to continue until the last
  letter in the letter string."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147848Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-identify-keywords
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it challenging to identify keywords in the question."@en ;
  curric:correction """Rehearse answering retrieval questions by modelling the process out loud.
  Encourage children to underline the keyword in the question and use skimming and scanning
  to find the answer."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147855Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-concept-ideas-closely
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle with the concept of ideas being 'closely related'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Semi-colons don't need to show cause and effect or contrast; they are
  versatile and we should interpret 'closely-related' broadly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147866Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-commas-instead-semi
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may use commas instead of semi-colons to separate detailed list
  items."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Reinforce the idea that it would be confusing to separate items containing
  commas using commas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147890Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-aware-non-finite-subordinate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not be aware that a non-finite subordinate clause can be used
  before and after a main clause."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that you say and model a variety of non-finite complex sentences where
  the non-finite clause is positioned both at the start of the sentence and at the end of
  the sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147912Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-feel-windrush-experience-overly
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may feel that the Windrush experience was overly negative. Many people
  from the Caribbean experienced racial discrimination and found themselves in very
  challenging circumstances."""@en ;
  curric:correction """There were some positives that occurred as a result, including the setting up
  of the Notting Hill Carnival. Pupils may wish to explore this further."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147917Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-draw-similarities
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to draw similarities between Walter's home life
  and life at war."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Modelling a few additional examples will support pupils e.g. he excelled in
  football and at war."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147923Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-identify-story-structure
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to identify the story structure within such a long
  novel."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that different problems may be resolved at different points in a
  story, but we can identify the air raid as the overall climax because it is the point of
  highest tension."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147929Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-recognise-different-subordinating-conjunctions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils do not recognise that different subordinating conjunctions have
  different meanings and uses."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Each subordinating conjunction has a specific meaning. Each subordinating
  conjunction is useful for different sentence contexts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147934Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-vocabulary-phrases-text-unfamiliar-even
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some of the vocabulary and phrases in the text may be unfamiliar and even
  confusing. E.g. the use of the word \"hollow\" to describe Arrietty's \"excitement\"."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make a bank of unfamiliar vocabulary from the text and provide definitions.
  Explore interesting phrase choices. E.g. using the word \"hollow\" to describe Arrietty's
  \"excitement\" could imply that this is the only emotion she can feel."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.147987Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-generate-ideas-role
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to generate ideas for role play."@en ;
  curric:correction """You might choose to hot seat each character in turn as a whole class,
  choosing children who feel confident sharing ideas to play each role."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148100Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-understand-nuance-involved-forming
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children might not understand the nuance involved in forming alliteration."@en ;
  curric:correction """Not all of the words in the phrase need to begin with the same letter/sound
  and the words don't always have to be 'next door neighbours'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148231Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-familiar-norse-mythology-references
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not be familiar with some of the Norse mythology references."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils could explore texts that develop their understanding of Norse myths,
  such as 'Norse Myths: Tales of Odin, Thor and Loki', written by Kevin Crossley-Holland and
  illustrated by Jeffrey Alan Love."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148577Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-immigration-uk-other
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that immigration is only **to** the UK and not into other
  countries **from** the UK."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Part of the reason for the post-war labour shortage was that Britons
  emigrated in vast numbers to other Commonwealth countries."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148583Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-develop-show
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to develop 'show and tell' ideas without
  stating the emotion."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Act out different feelings to encourage children to consider what happens in
  their bodies when they feel that emotion.E.g. What do you think or physically feel when
  you experience frustration? Answers could include 'chest tightens' or 'jaw clenches'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148644Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confused-difference-refugee-migrant
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might be confused by the difference between a refugee and a
  migrant."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that a refugee is a person who has been forced to leave their country
  in order to escape war, violence or natural disaster. A migrant moves from one place to
  another usually to find work or better living conditions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148654Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-picture-books-suitable-older-readers
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Picture books are not suitable for older readers to choose to read for
  pleasure."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Picture books can contain a range of complex themes and emotions. Display a
  range of texts for pupils to explore independently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148840Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-group-words-following
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think any group of words following a verb is an object."@en ;
  curric:correction """A noun, noun phrase or pronoun that directly follows a verb can be an
  object."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148873Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-concept-obligation-tricky
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find the concept of 'obligation' tricky to grasp."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that obligations are things we think we should do or that should
  happen or that others think we should do or should happen."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148878Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difference-index-contents
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children find the difference between an index and a contents page
  confusing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Clearly explain the key differences and look at examples of contents and
  index pages from a range of non-fiction texts to highlight this."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148893Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-include-direct-speech-sentences
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may only include direct speech sentences from their plans."@en ;
  curric:correction """One of the elements of the success criteria directs pupils to use adverbial
  detail and subordination in each reporting clause. This helps pupils remember to stretch
  their initial ideas in their plans when independently writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148935Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-correctly-punctuating-speech
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find correctly punctuating speech first and speech second sentences
  challenging."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use visual speech scaffolds to support pupils with correctly punctuating
  speech first and speech second sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148941Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-vocabulary-phrases-text-unfamiliar-present
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some of the vocabulary and phrases in the text may be unfamiliar. This may
  present a barrier to comprehension, particularly during dense sections of description
  involving high-level vocabulary."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Make a bank of unfamiliar vocabulary from the text and provide definitions in
  context beforehand. E.g. looking at a primrose leaf and identifying a \"furrow\"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148946Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-plays-put-quickly
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that plays are put on quickly without much preparation or
  work."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils understand how much work from a dedicated team of actors,
  directors and stage crew goes into putting on a play. You could tell pupils that
  professional theatre companies take, on average, between 8-16 weeks to put on a play."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148952Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-feel-anxious-themselves-enough
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may feel anxious that they are not themselves doing enough to tackle
  climate change."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Reassure pupils that their efforts are important, but that it is adults'
  responsibility to resolve the problem; take some time to discuss children's worries about
  this if needed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148958Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-unclear-position-addresses-date
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may be unclear as to the position of the addresses and the date in a
  letter."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that the features of a letter follow strict layout rules. Have
  some examples of written letters for the children to engage with."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148963Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-repeat-facts-included
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may want to repeat facts that were included earlier in the report."@en ;
  curric:correction """Detailed facts about a balanced diet, exercise and sleep come in the earlier
  themed sections."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148972Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-dashes-commas-used
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe dashes and commas are used interchangeably in fiction
  writing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """We favour using dashes when we are showing a dramatic effect and commas when
  simply adding detail."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148978Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-illustrations-merely-echo-repeat-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Illustrations should merely echo or repeat what the words convey."@en ;
  curric:correction """Illustrations can be an extension of the poem, adding layers of meaning or
  emotion beyond what words convey."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148989Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-range-sentence-types
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not use a range of sentence types and structures, leading to a lack
  of cohesion."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Success criteria, shared writing and modelled writing explicitly prompt and
  model use of a range of sentence types. You could also use visual scaffolds and checklists
  for each sentence type to remind pupils with."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148995Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-add-additional-new
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may want to add additional, new and specific information into the
  conclusion."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Information in the conclusion must be kept general and it must summarise the
  rest of the letter."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149001Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-concept-fate-raised
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle with the concept of 'fate' raised in the lesson."@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss the idea of being 'fated' to experience something, using examples -
  for instance, happening to meet a partner in a particular place might be described as
  'fated' to happen."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149009Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-way-convey-scrooges
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may think the only way to convey Scrooge's thoughts is to use the
  phrase 'Scrooge thought'. They may struggle to incorporate different ways to incorporate
  his inner thoughts."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Highlight the different examples that convey Scrooge's internal thoughts and
  ask the children to spot the different verbs used instead of 'thought'. Other examples are
  'considered', 'wondered', 'told himself'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149020Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-need-support-punctuating-direct
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may need support with punctuating direct speech in different forms."@en ;
  curric:correction """Visual structures to support punctuating direct speech can be found in our
  KS2 Grammar lessons."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149131Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-speakers-debate-reading
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that speakers in a debate are reading their speech word for
  word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that speakers in a debate should just be using notes to guide
  their speech, not reading it word for word. Model how to do this effectively while
  maintaining eye contact with the audience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149139Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-understand-relative-adverbial-clauses
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not understand that relative and adverbial clauses are two types of
  subordinate clause."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that relative and adverbial clauses are both subordinate, but they
  are differentiated by their starting word and use in sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149151Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-adjective-choices-describe
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may use adjective choices that describe the personality of the bee."@en ;
  curric:correction """Adjective choices are formal and technical in an explanation text rather than
  descriptive."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149162Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-role-play-hiccup
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find role play as Hiccup challenging."@en ;
  curric:correction """Note down initial impressions and character traits of Hiccup from reading
  Chapters 1 and 2. Discuss how pupils might 'show not tell' these before Task A."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149168Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-embed-relative-clause
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may struggle to embed a relative clause and they may forgot the
  necessary commas needed to demarcate a relative clause."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure there is a model of a relative complex sentence where the relative
  clause follows the main clause and one where the relative clause is embedded. Write the
  relative clause and commas in a different colour to make them visually stand out."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149174Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-think-orators
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to think of orators they know within certain
  professions."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Give supportive clues, e.g., \"Which young Swedish girl has done a lot to
  tackle climate change?\"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149183Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-free-verse-allows-entirely-random
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Free verse allows for entirely random writing without any consideration for
  form or craft."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Successful free verse poetry involves deliberate choices regarding line
  breaks, rhythms and imagery to create a meaningful poem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149189Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-recognise-meaning-associated-body
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not recognise the meaning associated with body language."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils could model some key aspects (such as eye contact, open/closed
  postures) beforehand to better understand underlying emotions that the characters in the
  text exhibit."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149195Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-choose-position-interrupt
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to choose a position in which to interrupt a speech
  sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to think of the complete sentence they want to say and
  interrupt it at a comma."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149200Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-understand-confusion-ewe-p
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not understand the confusion between 'ewe' and 'you' on p. 33."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ask the children to explain the confusion. If they do not know, explain to
  them that a 'ewe' is a female sheep."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149214Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-know-makes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to know what makes certain vocabulary
  ambitious."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that there can be many options when selecting vocabulary and
  they need to carefully choose the most precise words for each part of their writing. This
  is best explained by what effect they want to create for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149221Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-because-fairytales-magical
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children might think that because fairytales are magical they never touch on
  serious or dark topics."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Fairytales are stories that have been passed down through generations and
  often have deeper meanings related to serious topics."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149399Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-starting-strategy-pupils-copied-spelling
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When starting a strategy, pupils may have copied the spelling down
  incorrectly."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model the process of looking at it, considering what's difficult about the
  spelling and thinking about it. Then, model copying it for the first time, carefully
  checking each letter and verbalising what you notice."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149462Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-text-subtext
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Every text must have a subtext."@en ;
  curric:correction """Some texts are more straightforward and may focus on conveying their message
  or story in a more direct and explicit manner."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149477Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-deforestation-unique-amazon
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that deforestation is unique to the Amazon, or that it is
  purely done for destructive reasons."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that many countries (including the UK) have been heavily deforested
  over history; usually, this has been a result of increasing agricultural production."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149488Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-wrong-vowels-used-curriculum-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The wrong vowels are used in curriculum words: separate, popular and
  opposite."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Saying the words slowly 'how they are spelt' is a useful strategy to remember
  these tricky spellings, e.g. sep -ar -ate."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149511Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-word-prefix-root-word-recognisable
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Every word with a prefix will have a root word that is recognisable, such as
  'stroy' in 'destroy'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Some words have roots that we will not recognise or no longer use.
  Recognising the prefix can still help to spell and understand the word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149583Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-include-within-brackets-information
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may include within brackets information that is essential to the
  sentence's coherence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to cover the parenthesis in a sentence and see if what's
  left makes complete sense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149589Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-devious-mean-journey-route-way
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """'Devious' can also mean (of a journey or route) out of the way or not
  straightforward."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils understand this is why 'path' and 'course' are also word pairs
  of devious. It is not that a path can be 'sly'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149638Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-struggle-remembering-punctuation-rules
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may struggle with remembering punctuation rules for direct
  speech."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Leave a modelled example of correctly punctuated direct speech in view for
  children. Provide them with the speech first punctuation rules to follow as they write."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149646Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-sentences-task-c-question-9
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """In some of the sentences in Task C, question 9, there is more than one option
  as some of these words have a very similar meaning, such as 'famished' and 'ravenous'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss which of the sentences have a clear option to fit in the gap and then
  look at the ones left over. Discuss which words could fit here and why there is more than
  one option. Let pupils pick according to what they think sounds the best."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149753Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-understand-modal-verb-helps
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not understand that a modal verb 'helps' another verb."@en ;
  curric:correction """Draw attention to the fact that a modal verb comes before a main verb to
  modify it, e.g. 'will show', 'might help', 'should do' or 'would lead'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149759Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-mix-different-poetic-devices
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may mix up different poetic devices."@en ;
  curric:correction """The tasks in learning cycles one and two explicitly model how each poetic
  device is used in each stanza."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149765Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-switch-fluently
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it challenging to switch fluently between tenses."@en ;
  curric:correction "Practise saying sentences aloud to check tense is used accurately."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149808Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-draw-significant
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to draw out the most significant moments when
  summarising."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model eliciting the key parts of Walter's life - using the contents page to
  support. Have these accessible during the lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149816Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-counting-syllables-challenging
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find counting syllables challenging."@en ;
  curric:correction """Adults can model appropriate methods for syllable counting (including
  clapping, humming, tapping wrist)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149869Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-reading-angry-expression
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may believe that reading with an angry expression involves shouting or
  being loud."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model the fact that you can show an angry tone of voice using even a very
  quiet voice."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.150052Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-secure-madagascar
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils are not secure on where Madagascar is."@en ;
  curric:correction "Refer to Madagascar on a world map as part of the continent of Africa."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.150058Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-word-replace-unknown
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that any word can replace an unknown word."@en ;
  curric:correction """Replacement words should be based on contextual clues, which can be supported
  through inferring and reading around a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.150064Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-remember-order
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it challenging to remember the order of Edward's owners."@en ;
  curric:correction """You may want to note down the order of owners. This could be represented
  visually as a timeline within the classroom."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.150070Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-everyone-treated-fairly-equally
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Everyone is treated fairly and equally."@en ;
  curric:correction """By exploring the text and reading the author's note, it is clear that not
  everyone has equal rights. Pupils could explore charities like Amnesty International who
  campaign for equality."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.150110Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-one-way-respond
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children can think that there is only one way to respond to a poem and you can
  have the right or wrong understanding of it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Avoid posing questions which may lead children to the idea that there is a
  right or wrong answer when discussing the poem. Try to encourage open responses to the
  poem, celebrating each unique response from individuals."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.150800Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-distinguish-traditional
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to distinguish between a traditional myth and a
  modern myth."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Create a short list of the features of both genres. Draw out the contemporary
  adaptations in modern myths."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.150806Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-need-summarise-short-speech-because
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """There is no need to summarise a short speech because the audience have just
  heard it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Summarising an argument helps to reinforce the key parts and make the speech
  more convincing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.150861Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-start-using-spellings-place
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may start using these spellings in place of the most common
  spellings."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that 'ay', 'ai' and 'a-e' are the most common spellings and tell
  pupils to try those out first."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.150870Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-forget-common-spellings-use
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may forget the most common spellings and use the most recently learnt
  spellings."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Always emphasise prior learning. Show examples of words including incorrect
  and correct spellings to discuss (e.g. train and trean)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.150883Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-understand-archaic
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find it challenging to understand archaic language."@en ;
  curric:correction """Use your teacher assessments to inform how you have pupils read; you may wish
  to have the majority of the class reading in mixed-ability pairs while you read to a small
  group, having them say the next word when you pause to ensure engagement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151048Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-forget-silent-letter-forming
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children might forget the silent letter when forming the words in Tasks B and
  C."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind children that the purpose of the task is to write words with silent
  letters. Ask them to look back and ensure they have included the silent letter."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151057Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-start-focus-adding-emphasis
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """As children start to focus on adding emphasis, they can forget some of the
  routine handwriting expectations like lead-ins and lead-outs."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind the children before they start to look carefully at the sentence.
  Having a visual check-list, which includes handwriting prompts like lead-ins, lead-outs
  and the size of letters can help."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151065Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-bumbling-blundering-similar-words-pupils
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Bumbling and blundering are very similar words which pupils may find
  confusing."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Bumbling suggests a lack of skill or clumsiness where as blundering implies
  making specific mistakes or errors."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151071Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-need-read-entire
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that they need to read the entire text."@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that you do not have to read a non-fiction text from start to
  finish. Focus on certain pages that you want to find out more about."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151105Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-words-prefixes-recgonisable
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that all words with prefixes must have a recgonisable root
  word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Look at some words with the focus prefixes that do not have a recognisable
  root word. Discuss how the meaning of the prefix can still support children with
  understanding the meaning of the word, e.g. translate or transmit."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151125Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-valuable-witness-able
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children might think that a valuable witness must be able to provide details
  about the event."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that sometimes quotes from witnesses are used to gain an
  understanding of impact and can be primarily about emotions or feelings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151175Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-identifying-examples-imagery
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find identifying examples of imagery/language challenging."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils could use the modelled examples and further discuss the imagery and
  language used in those examples."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151181Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-their-second-point
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that their second point can be similar or a continuation of
  their first point."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that the two points used as arguments in their persuasive
  lettter should be different and appeal to the reader in different ways."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151201Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confused-use-comma-use
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils are confused with when to use a comma and when not to use a comma."@en ;
  curric:correction """A comma is used before \"but\" and \"or\" co-ordinating conjunctions. A comma
  is used after the adverbial clause if it is first in the sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151251Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-speak-fast
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils speak too fast."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils can use note cards to remind them when to pause for emphasis and to
  control speed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151257Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-understand-difference-cannot-find
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may not understand the difference on where you can and cannot find a
  root word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Show examples of where an obvious root word can support spelling. Words
  without an obvious root word need to be practised."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151300Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confuse-similes-metaphors
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may confuse similes with metaphors."@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that similes use 'like' and 'as' and metaphors are not comparing
  but saying something actually is something else."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151348Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-confuse-inference-prediction-while
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children might confuse inference with prediction. While a good prediction
  relies on inference skills, inference does not always involve predicting."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Rehearse the definition of inference a number of times and accompany with as
  many relevant examples as necessary (like the example on slide 19)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151928Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-understand-vocabulary
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to understand some of the vocabulary modelled
  (e.g. indifference) and they may struggle to generate their own vocabulary ideas to convey
  an ominous atmosphere."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model the use of a thesaurus to up level simple pieces of vocabulary. For
  example, instead of 'lonely', children might use 'isolated' or 'deserted'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151942Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-initially-get-cronus-confused
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may initially get Cronus confused with Chronos who they were introduced
  to in Lesson 2."""@en ;
  curric:correction "Cronus was the leader of the Titans. Chronos was the god of time."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151974Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-theme-myth-literal
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that a theme of a myth is literal."@en ;
  curric:correction """Themes usually have to be inferred by reflecting on the myth's complete
  narrative."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151979Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-feel-tempted-rush-plan
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may feel tempted to rush through the plan with too little detail in
  each paragraph."""@en ;
  curric:correction """This is the purpose of encouraging pupils to engage with the narrative
  elements - model and encourage reflecting on each event through these four lenses."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152002Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-distinction-fact-opinion
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle with the distinction between fact and opinion."@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to focus on the way information is presented: some things
  are adopted as fact by the journalist and others are presented as the perspectives of
  certain individuals."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152041Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-keywords-question-copy
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find the keywords from a question and copy out that exact sentence
  without checking."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure children reread the question and check that their answer answers that
  question."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152050Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-list-emotions-referring-character
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may list emotions when referring to a character trait."@en ;
  curric:correction """Emotions are temporary. Explain that character traits are linked to
  characterisation. They are relatively stable over time. Examples of common character
  traits could be shared with the children prior to Task A."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152072Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-able-spell-root-word
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may not be able to spell the root word of plural nouns that are being
  focused on."""@en ;
  curric:correction """For pupils who need more support, provide the root word (singular noun) as a
  starting point for Practise Task B, so they can focus on securing the rules around
  plurals."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152078Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-assume-curriculum-words-common
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may assume that all curriculum words are common exception words."@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss that the list is made up of words with the rules they have learnt or
  should have come across. Discuss the rules some words use compared to words that may be
  exceptions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152123Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-confusion-around-using-fictional
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may have some confusion around using a fictional tale to inform a
  non-fiction text."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Go through other examples, from fiction and real-life, that could be used as
  newsworthy events for newspaper articles."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152134Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-students-find-hard-understand-different
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Students may find it hard to understand how different tenses can be used in
  one sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Analyse example e.g. \"Currently, forensic officers are examining the crime
  scene and they have sent off pieces of evidence for testing.\""""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152154Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-students-think-use-fronted-adverbial
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some students might think that the use of a fronted adverbial phrase forms a
  complex sentence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model examples and non examples to demonstrate that a phrase doesn't contain
  a verb but a clause does."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152166Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-words-suffix-recognisable-root-word
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "All words with a suffix will have a recognisable root word."@en ;
  curric:correction """Show that not all words with suffixes or common word endings will necessarily
  have a root word that we can recognise."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152201Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-important-following-structure
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that it is not important to following a structure when
  writing their argument."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that by following a structure, such as PEPS, their argument will
  be more professional and flow better."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152224Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-generate-synonyms
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may find it difficult to generate synonyms for 'said'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage the children to use character perspective to understand how Lila
  and Razvani felt when they were speaking. Provide opportunity for partner talk and develop
  a shared bank of synonyms for 'said'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152241Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-spell-words-ize-suffix
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may spell words with -ize, how the suffix sounds and in the American
  spelling."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Discuss the difference between the American and British spelling of the
  suffix -ise."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152249Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-hear-ee-words-ending-ious
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You can hear the 'ee' in all words ending in -ious and -eous."@en ;
  curric:correction """You cannot hear the 'ee' in words ending -geous, like 'courageous' (the 'e'
  is making the 'soft g' sound) or words with 'xi' or 'ti'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152255Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-word-rustling-incorrectly
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might use the word 'rustling' incorrectly."@en ;
  curric:correction """A 'rustling' object implies a level of movement. If leaves weren't moving, we
  wouldn't describe them as 'rustling' but we would if the breeze was blowing them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152261Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-questions-misconceptions-around-red
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may have questions or misconceptions around how the 'red-headed
  female heroine' is portrayed within stories."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It is important to explain that in life we do not judge somebody's qualities
  or traits based on their appearance. However, authors do sometimes use appearance to
  communicate certain messages."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152725Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-forget-elements-punctuation-speech
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may forget all elements of punctuation in speech first and speech
  second sentences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Speech first and speech second sentence scaffolds are referred to throughout
  both learning cycles to support pupils."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152761Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-need-extra-explanation-word
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might need some extra explanation on some of the word pairs."@en ;
  curric:correction """Put the words 'aroma', 'odour' and 'scent' into sentences to model how to use
  them correctly. If you have time, ask the pupils to put them in their own sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152767Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-believe-relative-clause-starts
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may believe that a relative clause starts with a being verb e.g. 'who
  is' or 'which was'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """We can use a whole range of verbs to start the relative clause e.g. 'who
  has', 'which sits', 'who likes'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152775Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-believe-relative-clauses-placed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may believe relative clauses can only be placed in the middle of
  sentences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Relative clauses follow nouns/noun phrases; although we focus on the middle
  position in Y4, it can vary."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152784Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-use-cohesive-devices
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may struggle to use all the cohesive devices listed in the lesson."@en ;
  curric:correction """All these cohesive devices are covered in our Year 5 Grammar curriculum; some
  children may benefit from additional input using selected slides from that content."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152790Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-words-stay-prepositions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that words stay as prepositions irrespective of what follows
  them."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Some words are prepositions when followed by a noun phrase, but they can be
  conjunctions or adverbs in other circumstances."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152795Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-language-poem-difficult
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find some of the language in the poem difficult to understand."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pre-teach some of the language in the poem before reading e.g.
  \"adolescent\", \"gamelan\", \"dengue\" and \"dialects\"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152809Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-use-accurate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to use the most accurate, precise vocabulary
  when describing the historical and social context at the time."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Information about Tubman's activism and subject-specific vocabulary are
  reviewed and explicitly re-taught."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152848Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-forget-add-capital-letter
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Some children might forget to add the capital letter for the direct speech
  within a speech second sentence or might try to join the capital letter to the other
  letters."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model the habit of looking and thinking about your sentence before you write
  it. Where will my punctuation be? Where will my capital letters be? This way children will
  have the time to think about it before they start writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.152947Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-retelling-involves-reciting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils might think retelling involves reciting the myth word-for-word."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that pupils should use summary skills to include key information,
  such as crucial characters, main events and significant settings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.153612Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-put-less
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might find it difficult to put less frequently used words in sentences,
  such as 'sanguine' and 'auspicious'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide pupils with additional sentences using these words so they can hear
  how to use them in context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.153617Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confuse-authors-life-experience
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may confuse the author's life experience with those of the
  protagonist."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Learning cycle 1 draws explicit comparisons and discussion around the
  similarities between the two."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.153623Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-believe-non-fiction-text
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may believe this is a non-fiction text because it is about Vikings."@en ;
  curric:correction """Give clear explanations that this is a made-up narrative set in the context
  of a fictional Viking community."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.153658Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-vary-words
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to vary both words/phrases/clauses and
  time/manner/place/cause."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils have access to examples of both the different structures and
  purposes of fronted adverbials."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.153675Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-homophones-sound-same-pupils-rely
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Homophones sound the same so pupils may rely on previous spelling rules and
  so, spell them the same."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Spend time showing each word in a sentence, use images to support
  understanding and make sure each homophone is practised using a strategy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.153727Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-misspell-words-prefixes-spell
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children can often misspell words with prefixes as they spell them how they
  sound."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Help children to recongise when a word has a prefix and use that to support
  this with spelling, e.g. the prefix mis- has one 's'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.153922Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-either-good-bad
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that they are either 'good' or 'bad' at acting."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils know that **performance techniques** can be learnt,
  practised and developed and that 'real' actors work hard on their craft."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.153928Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-either-good-communicator
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that they are either a 'good communicator' or a 'bad
  communicator'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that pupils have a growth mindset when it comes to developing
  presentation and communication skills. All the presentation skills showcased in this
  lesson can be practised, including those that pupils feel confident in!"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.153952Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-inaccurate-verb-forms
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may use inaccurate verb forms when switching between the present and
  future tense."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Prompts are included on the planning document and slides to remind pupils to
  write in the correct tense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154036Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-want-include-quotes-bystanders
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may want to include quotes from bystanders or other interested parties
  at the event."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure pupils know that there will be a specific section devoted to quotes
  from bystanders in another part of the journalistic report."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154056Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-punctuation-rules-direct
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that punctuation rules in direct speech are optional or may
  apply them inconsistently."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that the reader must know where the direct speech begins and ends to
  understand what is being said. Display examples of speech with and without punctuation to
  emphasise this."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154068Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-see-distinction
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it difficult to see the distinction between the overall story
  structure and the structure of the mini-stories."""@en ;
  curric:correction """As pupils will be writing events from only one mini-story in this unit, focus
  on the idea of each of these as a complete, resolved story in itself. The larger, overall
  structure is less significant for our writing in this unit."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154310Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-speak-sufficiently-loudly
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to speak sufficiently loudly or clearly when
  presenting."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model the volume, stance and eye contact you expect. You may want to have
  children present to smaller groups if possible."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154316Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-infer-why
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to infer why citizens might take little or no
  notice of the tremors."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that the scientific study of volcanoes was not as it is today. Being
  near to a tectonic plate, Italy would have experienced earthquakes. Therefore, many people
  would have not treated the first signs of eruption as the danger it was."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154321Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-know-divide-extract-readers
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not know how to divide up the extract for Reader's Theatre."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that all members of the group should share in the process of reading
  aloud. Smaller sections could be highlighted for less confident readers (for example,
  Fishlegs)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154328Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-points-information-accepted-speaker
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Points of information always have to be accepted by the speaker."@en ;
  curric:correction """If points of information challenges are always accepted, a speech will be
  completely derailed, they should only accept one or two."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154333Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-think-rules-presenting-remain
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children may think that the rules for presenting always remain the same."@en ;
  curric:correction """Look at examples of presenting for different purposes and highlight the
  nuanced differences. Watch CBBC Newsround as a good model."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154339Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-hard-distinguish-features
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it hard to distinguish which features within the story are
  modern or traditional."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The illustrations within the story are a powerful tool for guiding students
  to identify modern versus traditional mythical features."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154345Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-find-difficult-combine-elements
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may find it difficult to combine all elements of oral presentation
  successfully. E.g. When focusing on projection, they may lose some of their expression."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure children practise the difference between projection and shouting. As
  they become more comfortable with projection, they should be able to juggle and maintain
  more elements of oral presentation successfully."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154353Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-give-consequence-instead-explanation
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may give a consequence instead of an explanation after the colon."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ask the question 'why?' about the part of the sentence before the colon - the
  answer should be an explanation not a consequence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154361Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-apostrophe-placed-s
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils think the apostrophe is placed before the s at the end of the first
  noun."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Repeat many times that an apostrophe is placed before the s at the end of the
  first noun only when it is a singular noun owning something. An apostrophe is placed after
  the s at the end of the first noun when it is a plural noun that owns something."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154367Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-fantasy-stories-entirely
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that fantasy stories are entirely built around fantastical
  elements and cannot have any parts that are based in real life."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that this is a fantasy story, even though there are large parts
  of it that seem quite naturalistic and real."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154376Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-pain-related-burning
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might think only pain related to burning can be described as
  'searing'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Use examples of sentences where 'searing pain' is caused by something other
  than heat."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154593Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-figurative-language-descriptive-writing-better
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "More figurative language in descriptive writing is always better."@en ;
  curric:correction """Overuse of personification, similes or other figurative devices can overwhelm
  the reader or dilute the impact of the description."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154602Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-use-formal
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to use formal fronted adverbials to link two
  sentences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise the clear link between the sentences the fronted adverbial is
  joining together."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154608Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-notice-subtle-shifts-intensity
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Children may not notice the subtle shifts in intensity and suspense at
  different points, e.g. how emotions may have shifted when the farmers waited and the Iron
  Man didn't arrive."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ask children to imagine or act out how they would have felt as the farmers at
  each point to support them in incorporating the appropriate 'show and tell' throughout."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154614Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-semi-colon-incorrect
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may use a semi-colon in an incorrect position."@en ;
  curric:correction """What is either side of the semi-colon must be capable of being a complete
  sentence; the two parts must be closely-related to each other in meaning and content."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154628Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-place-senders-recipients
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that they can place the sender's and recipient's address
  wherever they like."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that there are strict rules to follow in terms of the layout of
  a formal letter. Provide pupils with a range of examples of formal letters for them to
  explore in groups."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154640Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confuse-metaphor-simile
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may confuse a metaphor with a simile."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that both metaphors and similes are ways of using language to
  compare. Metaphors compare by saying something 'is' somthing else, whilst similes use the
  word 'as' or 'like'. There are no similes in this poem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154654Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-understand-chronology
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to understand the chronology of events within
  the time period."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Ensure that you use explicit modelling and give opportunities to pupils for
  them to be re-exposed to this chronology through tasks."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154809Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-forget-capital-letter-inverted
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Sometimes children can forget the capital letter after the inverted
  commas."""@en ;
  curric:correction """As you model, repeat the same words to remind the children that the capital
  letter comes after the inverted commas. For example, 'Let's start, inverted commas,
  capital letter, pencil off, lead in...'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154814Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-word-prefix-recognisable
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think every word with a prefix will have a recognisable
  root word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Show that some roots we don't recognise may have Latin roots that we don't
  know. We can call this a 'stem' or a 'root'. Recognising the prefix can still help with
  spelling and understanding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154848Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-opinion-include-my
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may think that an opinion has to include 'my' or 'I'."@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain to pupils that an opinion is a view or belief that a person has.
  'Tennis is the best sport' is an opinion because it is not a fact. Someone else may think
  differently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154854Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-think-two
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to think of two distinct similarities and
  differences."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils could mind map character traits of Toothless and compare these to
  character studies of Hiccup."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154860Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-place-main-clause-colon
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may not place a main clause before the colon."@en ;
  curric:correction """Emphasise that for questions and lists, we always have a main clause before
  the colon; for questions, we also have one after the colon."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154874Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-misconception-windrush-generations-experience
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may have the misconception that the Windrush Generation's experience of
  life in Britain was very positive."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The 'Life in Britain' learning cycle explores the challenges and
  discrimination faced by the Windrush Generation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154885Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-struggle-maintain-correct-tense
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may struggle to maintain the correct tense when converting between
  active and passive."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Encourage pupils to consider the different tense options and find the one
  that sounds best."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154891Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-children-cannot-remember-dictated-sentence
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Children cannot remember the dictated sentence because it is too abstract."@en ;
  curric:correction """Give context to the sentence, such as imagine someone is applying to be part
  of a netball team. This is what the coach asks. Add images."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154899Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-word-lashing-verb
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils might use the word 'lashing' as a verb E.g. 'The rain was lashing
  against the window'."""@en ;
  curric:correction """If pupils use the word as a verb, that is fine. Just make sure to explain to
  them that they have used the word as a verb because it is an action and not describing a
  noun."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154905Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-confused-why-joseph-heading
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may be confused as to why Joseph is heading into the city instead of
  away from it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explain that evacuation was not compulsory and many children stayed behind in
  the city (or were called back home after the 'phony war')."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154911Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-use-terms-commonwealth-british
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may use the terms 'Commonwealth' and 'British Empire'
  interchangeably."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide opportunity for pupils to conduct research into the Commonwealth and
  the British Empire to support their understanding of the context of the text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.155123Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-words-lesson-five-letters-long
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The words in this lesson are over five letters long, so children might
  struggle to be consistent with the letter formation or the joins used."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Model looking at the words carefully before writing them. Point out which
  letters have ascenders or descenders and what that will mean for the formation of the
  letters."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.155129Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-examples-given-fronted-adverbials-manner
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The examples given for fronted adverbials of manner are adverbs ending in
  'ly'. Children may assume this is the only way to write a fronted adverbial of manner."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Provide additional examples of fronted adverbials of manner that are phrases
  rather than individual words. E.g. 'With a grave expression on his face,...'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.155138Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-creating-vivid-imagery
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think that creating vivid imagery for the reader is not an
  essential part of poetry."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Teach pupils that a writer will want the reader to be able to visualise the
  different parts of the poem and this is achieved through creating vivid imagery."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.155189Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-initially-think-mum-says
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may initially think that 'Mum Says She Loves Me' is a poem which
  conveys a negative emotion."""@en ;
  curric:correction """'Mum Says She Loves Me' depicts love in a different family structure. This
  does not mean that the love is any less than the love depicted in 'You Are'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.157357Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-familiar-symbolism-especially-common
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Not all pupils may be familiar with symbolism, especially common symbols."@en ;
  curric:correction """To support pupils, adults could model out loud the associations that can be
  made about the objects ."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.159602Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-attribute-feeling
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it challenging to attribute a feeling or emotion to a
  metaphor."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Some pupils could have visuals of the imagery contained in the poem, to
  support when attributing the change in emotional state of the speaker from verse 1 to
  verse 3."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.160923Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-challenging-identify-themes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may find it more challenging to identify themes of hope and belonging
  in 'The Colours of My Dreams' due to its more abstract imagery."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Explore how dreams are often seen as symbols of hope. Belonging can link to
  human experiences and emotional connections."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.164025Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-understanding-symbolism-poems
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pupils may find understanding the symbolism in both poems challenging."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pupils may benefit from additional images to support understanding and help
  with representation of emotions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.164031Z"^^xsd:dateTime .
